title: chocolate cinnamon popcorn spice
directions: Combine all ingredients in a small bowl.
Stir until well blended.
Store in a large spice shaker.

title: lightning white clam sauce
directions: Heat
oil in nonstick skillet.
Saute onion until limp, about 3 to 4 minutes. Add garlic; cook 1 minute more.

title: spiced nuts(microwave style)
directions: In a deep 2-quart pan, combine first seven ingredients.
Heat, uncovered, on Full power 1 1/2 minutes; stir occasionally.
Add 1/2 cup nuts at a time to syrup mixture.
Stir until well coated.
With a slotted spoon lift out nuts; reserving the draining syrup.
Place coated nuts in a shallow 1 1/2-quart heat-resistant non-metallic baking dish.
Repeat procedure with remaining nuts.
Heat all the coated nuts, uncovered on Full power 5 minutes or until syrup begins to harden slightly.
Transfer nuts to greased wax paper to allow to cool and harden.

title: ice cream
directions: Mix together.
Add milk to freezer line.
Yields 4 quarts.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Brown and drain ground beef.

title: mom's apple crisp
directions: Butter a baking pan.
Fill with sliced apples, water and cinnamon.
Work together remaining ingredients until crumbly. Spread over apple mixture.
Bake 30 minutes in oven at 375°. Serve warm with milk or plain.

title: strawberry dream pie
directions: Combine
in
saucepan, vanilla pudding and pie filling, strawberry	flavor	gelatin,
water and lemon juice.
Cook and stir over
medium
heat
until
mixture comes to a boil.
Pour into
bowl and chill until thickened.
Blend in prepared Dream Whip
topping.
Stir in strawberries.
Pour into cooled, baked 9-inch pie	shell.	Chill
until
set (1 to 2 hours).
Garnish with additional whipped topping and strawberries.

title: cream puffs
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Heat water and margarine to rolling boil. Stir in flour.
Stir vigorously over low heat about 1 minute or until mixture forms a ball.
Remove from heat.

title: pumpkin spice muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease bottoms only of 12 medium muffin cups or line with paper muffin cups.
Blend pumpkin, milk and egg with fork in medium bowl.
Stir in remaining ingredients just until moistened.
Fill muffin cups about 2/3 full.
Bake 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: peach pie alaska
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add ice cream by spoonfuls.
Stir until melted and smooth.
Blend in whipped topping and fruit.
Chill, if necessary, mixture will mound. Spoon into crust.
Chill about 3 hours, or freeze until firm. Yields 8 servings.

title: cheese-garlic biscuits(makes 10 to 12)
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Mix baking mix, milk and cheese.
Drop by spoonful onto a greased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until golden.
Melt butter and garlic.
Brush over warm biscuits before removing.
Serve warm.

title: diabetic apple pie
directions: Mix Equal and cinnamon, then add to applesauce and mix well. Place crust in 9-inch pie pan.
Add the applesauce mix and dot with butter.
Cover with the next crust and cut slits for air to escape; press around edges.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Sliced sugar-free apples can be used.

title: collard greens
directions: Place turkey or ham hocks in large saucepan; add water, pepper pod and garlic.
Cover and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to low and simmer 30 minutes.
Add collards, sugar, salt and pepper. Cook 30 to 40 minutes or until greens are done.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: lemon cooler
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in blender.
Blend until smooth and frothy.
Garnish with lemon slices.
Makes 3 cups.

title: cherokee pie casserole
directions: Saute onion in oil.
Brown meat in sauteed onion.
Add spices, soup, tomatoes and rice.
Cook 3 minutes.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch casserole pan.
Cut cheese diagonally and place on top.
Arrange sliced olives on top of cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts and bubbles, about 30 to 40 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Use a large pot.
Add together the oil and flour, stirring until you have a brown gravy.
Add vegetables; cook until tender. Add tomato paste, water and seasonings.
Cook slowly for 1 hour. Add shrimp to sauce; cook another 10 minutes.
Serve on a bed of cooked rice.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Recipe is for a 6-quart freezer.

title: texas beef skillet
directions: In skillet, cook beef and onion.
Drain fat.
Stir in undrained tomatoes, undrained beans, uncooked rice, green pepper, chili powder, garlic salt, 1/2 cup water and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Bring to boiling; reduce heat.
Simmer, covered, for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Top with cheese.
Cover and heat 3 minutes or until cheese melts.
Sprinkle with corn chips around the edge.
Sour cream is good with this.
Serves 6.

title: rice and broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Put in casserole dish and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: healthy chicken chili
directions: Cut chicken into chunks; saute with onions in oil until brown.
Add all remaining ingredients; stir well.
Simmer 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
For thicker chili, omit chicken broth and add approximately 1 cup water.

title: baked salmon
directions: Combine bread crumbs and milk with egg and salmon.
Form into loaf and bake at 350° until browned.
Bacon strips may be placed on top of loaf when loaf is put in oven.
When done, place on platter and pour green peas around loaf and serve.

title: cowboy beans
directions: Wash beans and soak overnight.
Place beans in large kettle and cover with water, add other ingredients and cook until tender. Serves 12.
Half of recipe serves 6.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cook carrots until tender; drain.
Mix all ingredients, except carrots, and cook 5 to 10 minutes.
Pour over carrots and let stand.
Will keep 2 weeks in refrigerator.

title: jalapeno cornbread
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into a 9 x 16-inch baking pan.
Bake in 350° oven for about 1 hour.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together.
Mix flour and buttermilk in alternately with ingredients.
Add coconut, pecans and vanilla. Fold in egg whites.
Pour into 2 greased and floured 8-inch round cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: hot salsa
directions: Position knife blade in food processor bowl; add all ingredients.
Top with cover; pulse 5 to 6 times until mixture is chunky.
Cover and chill.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa together; gradually add vanilla, margarine, eggs and milk while whisking until mixed well. Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake at 325° for 45 minutes. Bottom crust will brown easier if baked on lower rack.

title: warm potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes and cube.
Mix together the onion, pepper and mustard and cook 15 to 20 minutes.
Drain
the ham; save broth. Tear ham into chunks and add to potatoes and onion.
Stir ham broth and cider vinegar into potatoes.
Simmer for 10 more minutes.
Remove from heat; let stand 10 minutes.
Add sour cream.

title: new orleans bread pudding
directions: Melt oleo.
Combine sugar and eggs.
Add oleo, pineapple and bread crumbs.
Pour into a 10 x 10-inch baking dish; bake at 350° for 1 hour or until lightly browned on top.

title: sausage balls(club member: john waters)
directions: Combine ingredients. Roll into balls about size of walnuts. Bake at 400° for 15 minutes; drain well on paper towel.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Sift together flour, spice, soda, salt and baking powder.
Beat together sugar and oil until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Beat in pumpkin.
Add dry ingredients alternately with water.
Pour batter into 2 greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 55 minutes, or until tests done.
Cool for 10 minutes, then remove from pans.

title: cinnamon munch
directions: Combine sugar and cinnamon.
Set aside.
In large skillet melt butter over low heat.
Add Chex, heat and stir gently until all pieces are coated.
Continue to heat and stir every 5 to 6 minutes.
Sprinkle 1/2 the cinnamon sugar mixture evenly over Chex.
Stir to bring unsugared pieces to top.
Sprinkle with remaining cinnamon sugar.
Heat and stir 1 minute longer.
Spread on absorbent paper to cool.

title: texas beans
directions: Saute onions lightly in butter.
In another skillet, brown 1/3 cup almonds in butter.
Remove onions and put 1/4 stick butter and beans.
Lightly brown.
Add onions, almonds and salt and pepper to taste.
Add dash of nutmeg.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Boil and debone chicken. Mix soup and chicken broth. Pour mixture into large pan and put chicken in with mixture. Stir well. Cut butter into thin pats and lay over chicken mixture. Mix together biscuit mix and milk and pour over top of chicken. Bake at 350° until crust is golden brown. Add salt and pepper.

title: breakfast pies
directions: Place sliced ham in a iron skillet with a small amount of grease, browning on both sides.
Remove ham from skillet.
Pour excess grease, leaving several tablespoons of grease and ham residue to the bottom of skillet.
Pour in a cup of strong black coffee and stir over medium heat for 5 minutes.
There you've got yourself red eye gravy.
Serve with biscuits and grits.

title: mini cheese cakes
directions: Mix crumbs and margarine.
Put in cupcake papers and press down with bottom of a glass.
Beat cheese, egg, sugar and vanilla until smooth.
Pour over crumbs in cupcake pans.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Cool completely.
Garnish with pie filling.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix sugar with cornstarch.
Add water and cook over medium heat until thick and clear.
Remove from heat.
Add jello and stir well. Cover bottom of baked pie shell with strawberries and pour mix over all.

title: sour cream enchiladas
directions: Cook until thick the butter, flour and chicken broth.
Add sour cream; do not boil.
Roll the cheese and onion in softened tortillas.
Place in greased pan.
Top with sour cream and 1 can chopped green chillies.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: broccoli and cauliflower casserole
directions: Boil cauliflower and broccoli for 10 minutes.
Mix vegetables together and place into a long casserole dish.
Add soup and place Kraft singles on top.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: leftover turkey casserole
directions: Combine turkey, celery, onion, mushrooms, eggs and almonds, noodles or chips.
Mix mayonnaise and soup together and fold into turkey mixture.
Put in 2-quart casserole dish and cover with noodles.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until mixture bubbles.

title: wesson oil fruit cake
directions: Sift together first 6 ingredients and set aside.
Combine next 4 ingredients in a large bowl.
Mix well.
Add 1 cup of the flour mixture.
Combine Wesson oil and sugar; beat until light.
Add eggs, 1 at a time.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Add dry ingredients alternately with 1 1/2 cups buttermilk.
Beat until smooth.
Add fruit-nut mixture.
Pour into a greased tube pan. Bake at 300° for 2 hours.
Decorate top of cake with candied fruit. Makes 1 tube cake.

title: lyn's red velvet cake
directions: Cream together in mixer the shortening and sugar.
Add to creamed mixture and mix well the eggs.
Add and beat well paste made from food coloring and cocoa, vanilla and salt.
Add alternately to mixture the flour and buttermilk.
Remove from mixer and add the vinegar and soda (which have been mixed together).
Mix by hand; do not beat.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
I use a 9-inch pan and split the layers for frosting.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Melt butter in 11 x 14-inch pan.
Pour rice over melted butter.
Mix 2 cans of soup and 2 cans of hot water; pour over rice.
Place chicken pieces over rice.
Bake at 325° for approximately 30 minutes.

title: spinach-mushroom salad
directions: Combine spinach and mushrooms in a salad bowl; set aside. Combine remaining ingredients in a small saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and cool.
Pour dressing over salad; toss. Serve immediately.

title: eleanora's peanut brittle
directions: Cook the first 4 ingredients for 12 to 15 minutes; turn off the burner.
Add soda and stir.
Pour up quickly into a buttered pan.
When cook, break into pieces.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch together.
Add egg yolks and a little milk.
Add the rest of the milk, water and vanilla.
Cook in a double boiler until thick.
Add butter and coconut.
Beat well. Use the rest of the coconut on the icing.

title: lemon icebox dessert
directions: Cream the sugar, cream cheese and vanilla together.
Mix Jell-O with 1 cup of boiling water, then set in the refrigerator until it begins to thicken.
Mix with cream cheese mixture, then add lemon juice and mix again.
Whip the Milnot until stiff peaks form, then fold into cream cheese and Jell-O mixture in a large bowl.
Melt margarine; mix with graham cracker crumbs.
Pat firmly 2/3 of this mixture on the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Pour the Jell-O mixture over this and even out, then sprinkle the remaining 1/3 of crumbs on top.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: triple decker fudge
directions: Line a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan with wax paper.
Into three separate medium microwave-safe bowls, place chocolate chips, peanut butter and vanilla chips.
Pour 3/4 cup each of sweetened condensed milk in the chocolate and peanut butter chips.
Pour the rest of the condensed milk onto the vanilla chips.
Microwave each bowl separately.
Spread chocolate layer into pan, then spread peanut butter mixture, then vanilla mixture.
Cover; refrigerate until firm.
Remove from pan; peel foil.
Cut into squares.
Makes about 8 dozen squares.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Microwave sugar, butter, syrup and salt on High for 4 minutes, stirring after each minute.
Then micro for 2 more minutes.
(Do not stir.)
Add soda and stir well.
Put cooked popcorn in brown paper bag and pour cooked syrup over it.
Shake and micro for 90 seconds.
Shake and micro for 60 seconds more. Spread out on pan and let cool.

title: kaye's rolls
directions: Blend flour and crisco. Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well. Drop by scoop on baking sheet.

title: catadoori chicken and fruited rice
directions: Unroll chicken breast fillets; remove skin.
In a 10-inch skillet, melt butter over low heat; add curry powder, onion and salt.
Cook, stirring, for 1 minute.
Stir in 1 tablespoon curry mixture into yogurt; set aside.
Cook chicken fillets in curry mixture remaining in a skillet 2 minutes, turning once.
Add water and fruit; heat to boiling, stirring.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 8 minutes or until chicken is fork-tender.
Sprinkle rice into liquid around chicken; remove from heat.
Cover and let stand 5 minutes.
Serve with green beans.
Serves 2.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Sift flour with baking powder, soda, salt, cinnamon and cocoa; set aside. In large bowl at high speed, beat eggs until very light and fluffy. Gradually beat in granulated sugar until very fluffy and light in color. Gradually beat in oil. With mixer at low speed, beat in flour mixture, alternately with buttermilk. Drain zucchini well; fold into flour mixture along with vanilla, nuts and raisins. Turn into greased and floured 10-inch Bundt cake pan. Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes. Cool in pan on wire rack 10 minutes. Turn out; sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: cherry delight pie
directions: Pour cherry pie filling into a graham cracker crust.
Mix rest of ingredients together in bowl and spread on top of cherries.

title: hash browns
directions: Lay hash browns in flat casserole.
Mix onions, sour cream, chicken soup and cheese.
Pour this mixture on top of the potatoes.
Melt butter and Post Toasties or croutons; sprinkle on top of the mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Bake, covered, for 25 minutes, then uncover for the least 10 to 15 minutes.

title: angel salad
directions: Take juice from pineapple and juice from lemon and add yolk of egg, sugar and flour. Cook until thickened. Add to 1 beaten egg white. Cool. Stir into marshmallows and pineapple. Add whipped cream that has been slightly sweetened.

title: party pinwheels
directions: Mix cream cheese and Hidden Valley dressing and spread on tortilla shells. Then put rest of ingredients on as desired. Roll up and chill in the refrigerator for an hour. Cut in 1-inch sections and serve.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Peel, dice and boil potatoes, then mash.
Brown meat (you can use beef, turkey or combination) with onion and garlic.
Cook carrot in microwave.
Add all veggies to meat; stir in soup.
Pour into casserole dish; top with mashed potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until golden.

title: broccoli bake
directions: Cook vegetables until barely tender.
Blend in sour cream, soup and onion soup.
Stir and drain vegetables.
Mix all together into buttered casserole dish.
Top with Rice Krispies that have been browned in the butter.
Cover and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook chicken for 1 hour.
Debone when cool.
Saute onion, bell pepper and celery in margarine.
(This can be done in the microwave.)
Cook spaghetti in chicken broth; add other ingredients.
Cook, stirring occasionally, for 15
minutes.
This is ready to serve or put in casserole and refrigerate.
Heat in oven when ready to serve.
Can be frozen.
Delicious!

title: chicken sauterne
directions: Sprinkle chicken breasts with salt and pepper.
Brown slowly in butter.
Place chicken breasts in shallow baking dish.
Reserve drippings.
Add soup to drippings.
Slowly add wine.
Stir until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients, except rice.
Heat to boiling. Pour over chicken.
Cover and bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Uncover.
Bake an additional 25 minutes until tender.
Serve over rice if desired.
Serves 6.

title: galatchie
directions: Use amounts of cabbage, meat and rice equal to size of crowd you want to feed.
Cook meatballs until nearly done.
Add salt, pepper and pepper seed.
Add rice and chopped cabbage, adding enough water to cover cabbage.

title: microwave bread pudding
directions: Place first 3 ingredients in 2-quart microwave dish.
Beat ingredients until sugar is dissolved.
Add bread, raisins and sprinkle nutmeg on top.
Cover and bake in microwave 15 minutes on High.

title: shrimp and avocado salad
directions: In a
large
bowl, mix shrimp with eggs.
In a separate bowl, mix
mayonnaise,
milk,
paprika,
lemon juice, salt and ground red
pepper.
Gently stir in shrimp mixture.
Line four chilled salad
plates
with spinach.
Cut each avocado lengthwise in half; remove seeds and peel.
Cut each half into thin slices and arrange around each plate of spinach.
Spoon equal amounts
of shrimp
mixture
in
center
of
avocado
slices. Sprinkle with bacon pieces.
Arrange 2 tomato wedges alongside each serving. Keep in refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: harvest potatoes
directions: Saute onion in butter until soft.
Stir in soup and sour cream.
Pour over potatoes and Cheddar cheese.
Stir until blended.
Pour into well-greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Can use 7 to 8 large cubed and cooked real potatoes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries, orange and sugar together and let stand overnight in refrigerator.
Next day, mix lemon jello and boiling water; let stand until it begins to thicken.
Add to the mixture the nuts and apples.
Let stand until jello is stiff.

title: pumpkin custard pie
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into pie shells. Bake at 425° for 10 minutes, plus 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sour cream cake
directions: Cream softened margarine well; add sugar and cream well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each one.
Add baking soda to sour cream and stir.
Add this mixture alternately with flour. When completed, add 2 teaspoons vanilla extract.
Bake in preheated oven at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: creamy chicken primavera
directions: In a large skillet, melt butter, add chicken and cook until chicken is no longer pink.
Add pasta, vegetables and water. Cover.
Cook over medium heat for 7 to 9 minutes, until vegetables are crisp-tender, stirring occasionally.
Stir in sour cream. Heat thoroughly.
Makes 4 servings.

title: baked burgers
directions: Combine bread crumbs and 1/2 can of soup. Mix well. Add beef and mix well. Form 6 patties.
Combine remaining soup, chili sauce and mustard. Place patties in baking dish and pour liquid mixture on top.
Cover with foil. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes!

title: christmas pie
directions: Pour condensed milk in a mixing bowl.
Add lemon juice.
When it thickens, add the Cool Whip.
Drain oranges.
Add to mixture. Add nuts.
Pour into pie shells.
Chill.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill.

title: blueberry yum-yum
directions: Combine
blueberries,
1 cup sugar and 1/4 cup water in saucepan.
Cook over low heat until berries are soft.
Combine cornstarch
and 3 tablespoons water.
Add to berries and cook, stirring constantly until it thickens.
Set aside to cool.

title: spiced bars
directions: Stir together flour, baking powder, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg. Cream butter and sugar; beat in eggs and vanilla.
Gradually stir in flour mixture, coconut, oats and nuts.
Turn into a greased 9-inch square cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool. Cut into bars.

title: anaheim chili rice
directions: Cook brown rice in water for about 50 minutes.
Will yield about 5 to 6 cups cooked rice.
This may be done the day before and then kept in refrigerator.
Saute onions and diced Anaheim chili in margarine on stove or in the microwave about 2 minutes. Mix rice (cooked), onions and chilies with all remaining ingredients.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch casserole at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour until bubbly hot.
Serve immediately.

title: date nut bars
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Sift next 3 ingredients.
Combine and mix in bowl.
Add nuts and dates.
Bake at 350° in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan for 25 to 30 minutes.
Recipe can be doubled and baked for 35 to 40 minutes for thicker bars.
Cool and cut into bars.

title: play dough - rainy day doings
directions: Bring water to a boil.
Stir in all ingredients and cook on the stove for a while.
Cool.
Add food coloring.
The dough will harden if left uncovered.

title: lemon-caper chicken breasts
directions: Rinse chicken and pat dry. Combine flour, pepper and paprika on a plate. Dredge chicken in mixture, coating evenly and shaking off excess.

title: chocolate cupcakes
directions: Put in bowl and mix in order given.
Do not mix until last item has been added, then beat well.
Bake about 20 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken cheese balls
directions: Mix chicken, salad dressing mix, hot sauce and cream cheese with mixer until well blended.
Roll into balls and roll in pecans.
Cover and chill until ready to serve.

title: barbecued lima beans
directions: Bring beans to a boil in the 4 cups water.
Let stand for 2 hours. Saute onion and garlic in butter for 5 minutes, stirring frequently.
Add remaining ingredients except ham.
Cook for 10 minutes longer. Combine beans and ham in greased casserole. Cover with sauce.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 2 to 3 hours.

title: tea cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Drop on cookie sheet with teaspoon. Cook at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: jiffy cobbler
directions: Melt oleo in shallow baking dish (9 x 12-inch).
Make a thin batter of remaining ingredients except fruit and pour over oleo. Pour fruit on top of batter.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: hamburger spaghetti dinner
directions: Brown hamburger and onions in skillet.
Add tomato soup and mix well.
Cook spaghetti and drain and mix with tomato mixture. Put in baking dish and put cheese on top.
Bake until cheese melts at 350°.

title: sweet lemon spareribs
directions: Place spareribs in Dutch oven.
Add enough water to cover spareribs.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 1 1/2 hours or until tender.
Remove spareribs to 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Stir together lemonade and barbecue sauce.
Pour over ribs.
Cover and refrigerate for 8 hours.

title: quick no meat italian pasta
directions: Simmer first 9 ingredients in a saucepan for an hour or more. While this is cooking, in a separate pan, prepare the noodles according to package directions.
Drain pasta, and add to mixture. Simmer for 15 minutes.
Sprinkle with grated cheese of your choice and serve.

title: hearty salmon chowder
directions: Drain salmon, reserving liquid for later use and flake salmon. Saute onion, celery, green pepper and garlic in butter.
Add potatoes, carrots, chicken broth and seasonings.
Cover and simmer for 20 minutes.
Add zucchini and cook 5 minutes.
Stir in flaked salmon, reserved salmon liquid, milk and corn.
Heat thoroughly. Garnish.

title: scallop creole(low cholesterol)
directions: Thaw scallops, if frozen; cut into 3/4-inch pieces.
Cook onion, green pepper and garlic in oil until tender.
Add tomatoes (cut up), tomato sauce, sugar and all seasonings.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes more.
Remove bay leaves.

title: hot spiced cider
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Simmer for 15 minutes. Let set in refrigerator for 12 hours.
Heat to serving temperature and remove cinnamon sticks.

title: delightful cheesecake(lo-cal style)
directions: Sprinkle 3 tablespoons graham cracker crumbs on bottom of 9-inch pie or cake pan.
Set aside.
Soften gelatin in 1/2 cup water.
Add water to pineapple juice to make 3/4 cup.
Bring to a boil; beat cottage cheese until nearly smooth.
(With mixer about 3 or 4 minutes.)
Add egg yolks, skim milk, lemon juice, sweetener, vanilla and salt.
Beat well.
Blend in gelatin at low speed.
Chill.
Stir occasionally until mixture is thick, but not set (about 1 hour).
Beat egg whites at highest speed until soft peaks form; fold in gelatin mixture by hand.
Spoon over crumbs in pan.
Sprinkle the remaining tablespoon of crumbs over filling. Add pineapple tidbits on top.
Chill in refrigerator overnight. Serves

title: pickled okra
directions: Poke okra in
pint
jars.
Bring to boil vinegar, water and salt.
Pour mixture
over okra; add dill seed to each jar. Seal and process 10 minutes.

title: coffee can pop up bread
directions: Combine all ingredients and blend well except for flour.
Add flour and mix well.
If batter is too thin, add more flour.
Put in a large bowl; let rise until doubled in bulk.
Punch down and divide into 2 one pound coffee cans, greased well.
Let rise until 1/2 inch from top or until lid pops off.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Remove and grease top and sides.

title: caesar salad dressing
directions: In a food processor or blender, puree anchovies, garlic and Parmesan.
Add mayonnaise, vinegar, lemon juice, mustard, pepper, Worcestershire sauce and oils and blend until smooth.
Makes about 2 1/2 cups.

title: easy baked beans
directions: Fry bacon and drain.
Mix all ingredients.
Crumble bacon and mix all ingredients.
Bake at 375° for about 30 to 40 minutes.

title: pot roast meat loaf
directions: In large bowl, combine ground beef, bread crumbs, egg, Worcestershire sauce, soy sauce, catsup, salt and pepper.
Shape mixture into a loaf in center of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch casserole dish. Place vegetables in layers around meat, topping each layer with parsley flakes and black pepper.
Cover casserole tightly with foil.
Bake in preheated oven at 375° for 1 hour or until vegetables are tender.
Remove foil.
Bake 10 minutes more to brown meat.

title: kane's crawfish fettucine
directions: Saute veggies in butter for 20 minutes.
Add seasonings and soup; simmer 5 minutes.
Add tails.
Saute 3 minutes.
Add cream and cheese chunks slowly.
Add mixture to cooked, drained noodles. Stir in parsley and Parmesan cheese.

title: salsa chops
directions: In large skillet, over medium heat, brown chops in oil on one side about 2 minutes; turn chops.
Add salsa and chiles in skillet.
Lower heat; cover and simmer for 8 to 10 minutes.
Good with buttered corn, cucumbers and red onion salad.

title: golden cheese bake
directions: Combine rice, carrots, cheese, milk, eggs, onion, salt and pepper.
Pour into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup shredded cheese.
Bake in moderate (350°) oven for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: bachelor's dinner
directions: Open can tuna; squeeze excess oil out.
Take top off.
Eat with fork.

title: pepe's favorite chili
directions: Heat oil in large pot.
Cook onion, celery, green pepper and garlic until soft.
In separate skillet, brown meat; drain off fat.
Combine meat with vegetables in pot.
Add remaining ingredients; cover and cook over low heat for 2 to 3 hours.
Stir every 10 to 15 minutes to prevent burning.
A spicy chili that is easy to make.

title: nutt house meat loaf
directions: Combine beef and eggs. Blend in onion, celery, salt, seasoning salt, pepper, crumbs and ketchup. Adjust seasoning. Mixture should be smooth and moist. Pack into a loaf pan. Bake in 300° oven for 1 1/2 hours. Serve with Tomato Sauce.

title: zucchini jack casserole
directions: Slice zucchini crosswise 1/4-inch thick.
In a large bowl, beat together eggs, milk, salt, baking powder and flour until smooth.
Stir in parsley, garlic, onion, green chilies, cheese and zucchini.
Spoon into a greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Toss croutons in melted margarine and sprinkle on top.
Bake, uncovered, 35 to 40 minutes at 350° or until squash is tender when pierced.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.
Makes 10 servings.

title: yankee pot roast
directions: Sprinkle salt, pepper, sugar and flour over a 3 or 4 pound chuck roast (with bone out preferred, don't roll).
Brown slowly in fat, adding more as needed.
Brown on all sides; adds flavor.
When brown, add enough boiling water to cover the bottom of the pot. Add bay leaf (broken into pieces), whole allspice, a little bunch of parsley and 2 onions cut in half.
Cover, simmer on low heat about 3 hours.

title: sock it to me cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together in mixing bowl.

Mix 2 tablespoons brown sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon in separate dish. Pour batter into greased and floured tube pan in layers with the brown sugar-cinnamon mixture between layers. Save some of the topping for the top of the cake.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cheese krispies
directions: Cream the cheese and margarine together.
Add remaining ingredients.
Form into small balls, then flatten with fork.
Bake for about 10 minutes at 350° or until done.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Mix in order given.
Roll in balls and flatten with a buttered glass bottom dipped in sugar.
Bake at 350° for 17 minutes.

title: make ahead breakfast bake
directions: Crumble sausage in medium skillet.
Cook over medium heat until brown.
Drain well.
Spread bread cubes in a buttered 12 x 8 x 2-inch dish.
Top with sausage and cheese.
Combine eggs, milk and seasoning; beat well and pour over cheese.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: grandma's chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch, flour and cocoa. Blend egg yolks and add to sugar mixture. Bring to a boil, stirring constantly, and cook until thick. Remove from heat and add margarine and vanilla. Mix well. Put in baked pie shell. Top with meringue. Bake at 350° until brown.

title: french onion soup
directions: Cook onion in margarine in 4-quart pot over medium heat; stir occasionally until tender.
Sprinkle with flour.
Gradually stir in 1 can of broth.
Heat to boil, stirring constantly.
Add remaining broth, water and Worcestershire.
Heat to boiling. Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, 30 minutes.

title: baked stuffed fish
directions: Wash fish inside and out in cold water.
Drain and pat dry.

title: microwave caramel popcorn
directions: Melt butter for 1 1/2 minutes.
Stir in sugar and syrup. Microwave 3 to 5 1/2 minutes until 280°.
Stir in vanilla and soda.
Pour on popcorn.
Microwave 4 to 6 minutes, stirring every 2 minutes.
Pour onto wax paper.

title: blueberry surprise breakfast
directions: The night before baking:
Crumble sausage in skillet; fry until brown.
Drain sausage on paper towels; allow to cool to room temperature while preparing remaining mixture.
Cream margarine with both sugars until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and sour cream; blend well.
Sift flour with baking soda, baking powder and salt; add to creamed mixture, blending well.
Add cooled sausage, then gently fold in blueberries.
Grease and flour 2-quart casserole or 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle chopped pecans over bottom of pan.
Pour in batter, spreading evenly.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: macaroni and cheese casserole
directions: Cook macaroni as directed on package.
Drain.
Put macaroni in casserole dish.
Add stewed tomatoes and mix.
Cut up cheese in cubes and mix with macaroni and stewed tomatoes.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top.
Bake in oven at 350° for 20 to 25
minutes, until light brown on top.

title: 5 minute fudge
directions: Mix milk, sugar and salt together in saucepan.
Heat to boiling, then cook 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir 1 to 2 minutes (until marshmallows melt).
Pour into buttered 9-inch square pan.
Makes about 2 pounds.

title: banana muffins
directions: Mix and put into greased muffin pans.
Bake at 350°.

title: safflower mayonnaise
directions: Combine egg, vinegar, lemon juice, mustard, salt and olive oil in blender.
Whip; with machine running, add safflower oil, one teaspoon at a time.
Refrigerate; keeps several weeks.
Yields 1 1/2 cups.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar.
Add egg yolks. Add soda in first cup of flour.
Add buttermilk, then rest of flour.
Add extract. Last, add stiffly beaten egg whites.
Bake in greased and floured Bundt pan.
Put in cold oven.
Bake 1 hour and 30 minutes at 325°.

title: pasta with artichokes
directions: Saute garlic in oil about 3 minutes.
Drain water from artichokes and add them with wine, salt and pepper.
Cook for about 10 minutes.
Meanwhile, cook pasta and drain, then toss with artichokes.
Sprinkle with cheese and serve.

title: herbed pork and apples
directions: Combine herbs, salt and pepper; rub over roast.
Cover and refrigerate for several hours or overnight.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Drain fat.

title: chicken squash casserole
directions: Slice squash and cook until tender.
Drain.
Boil chicken until tender.
Chop chicken into bite size pieces.
Melt margarine and mix with dressing mix.
After mixing, divide into 2 equal parts.
Combine half of the dressing mix with the cream of chicken soup, cream of mushroom soup, sour cream, onion, squash and chicken.
Pour into 3-quart buttered casserole dish.
Top with other half of dressing mix.
Sprinkle slivered almonds or Parmesan cheese on top of the dressing mix.
Bake in a 350° oven for 35 to 45 minutes.
This can be prepared and frozen before baking.
If you freeze it, do not put cheese on top until you cook it.
You can put the almonds on before you freeze it.
It will keep for 6 months.

title: no peek casserole
directions: Mix all together and throw in your crock-pot. Cook until meat is done. Serve over noodles.

title: cheese biscuit
directions: Mix all ingredients and drop by spoonfuls onto cookie sheet. Bake at 450 until done.

title: phronia jeffer's russian tea
directions: Steep cloves and cinnamon with the tea.
Mix the tea with the juices and 1 cup of sugar.

title: apple crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place apples in buttered baking dish (8 x 8-inch).
Combine remaining ingredients until well blended. Sprinkle over apples.
Bake at 350° until apples are soft and topping is crisp. Enjoy!

title: sweet and sour pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops in skillet over low heat using no additional fat.
Season with salt and pepper.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over chops.
Cover and simmer over low heat until meat is tender, about 45 minutes to 1 hour.
(Vinegar and water mixture will thicken a little.)

title: cucumber relish
directions: Grind the 3 vegetables and sprinkle on salt.
Stir in and let stand overnight.
Drain.
Add the other ingredients and cook 30 minutes.
Pour into pint jars and seal at once.

title: country applesauce cake
directions: Grease and flour a 10-inch tube pan.
Sift flour with baking powder, baking soda, salt and spices.
In a large mixing bowl, beat shortening with sugar.
When mixed, beat in eggs, one at a time until mixture is creamy.
Heat oven to 350°.
Add sifted ingredients to egg mixture a third at a time, alternating with applesauce.
If batter seems very stiff, add up to 1/4 cup milk. Stir in raisins, dates and pecans.
Transfer batter to prepared cake pan and smooth top so that batter is level.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours until well browned and a cake tester comes out clean.
Remove pan from oven, run a knife around cake and put pan on a wire rack to cool for 1 hour.
Remove cake from pan and let cool completely. Keep at least 1 day before cutting.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients; blend thoroughly.
Form into a ball.
Roll in finely chopped pecans.
Serve with crackers.

title: cider french dressing
directions: In food processor, with chopping blade, process carrot and tomato until finely chopped.
Strain vegetables through sieve over a 1 cup measuring cup, pressing with back of spoon firmly to extract as much liquid as possible; discard vegetables.
Add enough apple cider to make 1/2 cup liquid.

title: stir-fried pork with vegetables
directions: Cut meat into 1/2 to 3/4-inch cubes; remove fatty parts.
Set aside.
Partially thaw the green beans.
Add onions and peppers to butter in heavy, large skillet.
Saute for 1 minute.
Add meat and green beans and stir-fry over high heat until all pieces are heated through.
Add salt, paprika and black pepper.
Mix well.
Pour in the beef or chicken broth.
Cover and simmer for 15 minutes or until vegetables are tender and crisp.
Mix ketchup with cornstarch.
Stir into mixture pan.
Cook, stirring, until juices are thickened.

title: new england clam chowder
directions: Dice potatoes and onion.
Put in saucepan with water, bay leaf, celery powder and pepper.
Cook until potatoes are tender.
Reduce heat to simmer.
Combine milk, cornstarch and Butter Buds.
Add slowly to potato mixture, stirring constantly.
Add clams and juice.
Stir over medium heat until it begins to boil and thickens slightly.
Reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes.
Remove bay leaf and garnish with chopped chives before serving.

title: hush puppies
directions: Pour into crock-pot and cook on high for 2 hours. Turn to low and cook for 2 hours.

title: potato cheese soup
directions: In a saucepan, bring potatoes, onion, water and salt to a boil. Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer until potatoes are tender.
Do not drain.
Mash slightly.
Stir in milk.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown meat; add taco mix, tomato sauce and water.
Heat until boiling.
Line casserole dish with chips.
Pour meat mixture over chips.
Add chips to the top.
Place in oven until very hot.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Form into ball and chill.
Roll in parsley or chopped pecans before serving.

title: chocolate caramel squares
directions: Melt caramels and 1/3 cup milk.
Mix cake mix, butter and rest of milk; stir in nuts.
Press 1/2 of cake mix into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 5 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle chocolate chips over crust.
Pour caramel mixture over chocolate chips.
Pinch remaining cake mixture over top of caramel mixture.
Return to oven and bake 15 minutes more.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix in order given until well blended.
Grease and flour a loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: blueberry banana pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour, lemon juice and 1 cup of blueberries.
Cook over medium heat until thick; cool.
Add 3 cups fresh blueberries. Line bottom of crust with sliced bananas.
Add blueberry pie filling mixture.
Serve with whipped topping.

title: beef log
directions: Mix spices with water.
Add to beef.
Refrigerate overnight. Form rolls in wax paper and lift into the broiler pan that is sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 45 minutes.
Turn over about halfway through cooking if desired (in lower it will be done in one hour).
Cool and wrap in foil.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: jon marzetti
directions: Brown the beef, add the onions and peppers.
Add the Worcestershire sauce and 1 tablespoon salt.
Add soup and water. Cook noodles according to package directions with salt.
Drain. Stir in cream cheese, combine with the meat.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese over the top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: cornish pastries
directions: Coarsely chop potatoes and onions.
Add shredded carrot for color.
Add parsnip (if you like them).
Meat may be anything: hamburger, sirloin tips or stew meat, coarsely chopped.
Combine all ingredients.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Wrap 1 to 1 1/2 cups of mixture in a piece of pie crust.
Bake pastries at 375° for 40 to 50 minutes or until crust is golden.
Good hot or cold.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Mix sugar and cinnamon together in small bowl.
Dip each biscuit in melted butter and then roll in sugar mixture.
Place in ungreased cake pan.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: southern comfort punch
directions: Mix all of the ingredients in a punch bowl.

title: crispy chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients together; pour in a casserole dish.
Top with cracker crumbs, then melt butter.
Pour over the top of crackers.
Bake at 350° until crackers are brown.

title: swiss steak
directions: Mix salt with flour; pound into steak.
Sear steak in hot fat in a large skillet or pan.
Add vegetables.
Cover.
Simmer for 2 hours or until meat is tender.
Add tomato juice, if necessary. Serves 6.

title: cheese-sausage dip
directions: Brown and drain sausage, hamburger and onion.
Melt together other ingredients.
Combine all ingredients.
Serve in a crock-pot.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: meat loaf for 50
directions: Add seasoning mix, water and milk to meat; mix well. Put mixture into greased baking pans (form into loaves). Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 1 hour.

title: easter nests
directions: Stir together sugar and coconut; set aside.
Microwave chocolate in a 1-qt. bowl on High for 1 1/2 minutes, stirring twice; cool.
Whisk together egg whites, vanilla and salt.
Stir in melted chocolate and add this to coconut mixture, stirring well.
Drop by heaping tablespoons 2 inches apart onto a lightly greased, parchment paper lined baking sheet.
Make an indentation in the middle of each mound with thumb to form a nest.
Bake at 350 degrees for 14 minutes or until bottoms are crisp.
Centers will be soft.
Press 3 jelly beans into the center of each nest and cool for 10 minutes on baking sheet.
Remove to wire racks to cool completely.
Store in air-tight container.

title: meat-stuffed eggplant
directions: Cut eggplant in half lengthwise; scoop out center, leaving 1/2-inch walls.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Place cut side up in a large baking dish, shallow.
Chop scooped out eggplant centers and set aside.
Brown meat and drain off fat; stir in eggplant, onions, parsley and oregano.
Cook at medium about 10 minutes or until tender.
Add tomato paste and Worcestershire sauce; mix well. Spoon 3/4 cup of mixture into each eggplant shell.
Sprinkle with cheese; cover with foil and bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: arroz con pollo(spanish rice and chicken)
directions: Wash chicken and place in a large pot.
Fill halfway with water.
Add salt, pepper and vinegar.
Boil chicken until it is tender (when it can be easily removed from the bone).
Take the pan off the heat.
Remove the chicken from the pot.
(Save the cooked chicken broth.)
Remove all bones and put the chicken aside.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Peel and boil zucchini.
Drain well.
Mix all ingredients into a large bowl with zucchini.
Pour into a square baking dish and bake for 1/2 hour or until cooked at 350°.
Substitute vegetables and broccoli or spinach.

title: classic lasagna
directions: Beat with rotary beater or fork Ricotta cheese, eggs, parsley, salt and pepper until well blended; set aside.

Cook lasagna noodles 20 minutes according to package directions in salted water with 2 tablespoons oil (to keep strips from sticking together). Drain in colander, then turn back into pan of cold water for a few minutes, making it easier to handle strips.
Doesn't matter if strips break; they can be used.
Drain again.
Not to assemble.

title: cool whip cookies
directions: Melt bars; cool slightly.
Gently add Cool Whip and wafers. Drop onto waxed paper by spoonfuls.
Refrigerate.

title: chinese hash
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add onion to drippings and cook to soften. Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Bake in casserole for 45 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle chow mein noodles (canned) over the top and bake 15 minutes longer.

title: marinated baked chicken breasts
directions: Combine the first 8 ingredients.
Add chicken, coating well. Let stand in refrigerator overnight.
Remove chicken from sauce. Roll in crumbs and arrange in shallow pan.
Melt margarine.
Spoon half of it over chicken.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.
Spoon rest of margarine over chicken and bake 45 minutes more.
Serves 12. (This great party dish can be halved.)

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Mix all the ingredients and let stand overnight before serving.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream together sugar and shortening.
Add applesauce.
Sift together first 7 items.
Mix raisins and optional nuts to applesauce.
Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Put in well-greased tube pan.
Place in a heated 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: baked creamed cabbage
directions: Shred cabbage very fine and cook 9 minutes in boiling salted water.
Remove cabbage; drain well and place in buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Melt butter in saucepan.
Stir in flour and salt until smooth.
Add milk gradually.
Continue stirring until mixture thickens.
Pour this sauce over cabbage and sprinkle with bread crumbs on top.
Bake at 325° for about 15 minutes or until crumbs are browned.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: peachy coolers
directions: Beat egg whites and salt until soft peaks form.
Beat until stiff and glossy, adding sugar gradually.
Combine egg yolks, peaches, lemon juice and almond extract; mix well.
Add milk and ice cream; beat until smooth.
Fold in egg whites.
Serve in tall chilled glasses; garnish with whipped cream and peach slices.

title: spinach souffle
directions: Combine ingredients (spinach should be cooked already and drained).
Place in greased casserole and top with 1/2 cup grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: molasses cupcakes
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients with pastry blender; set aside 1/4 to 1/3 cup crumbs for topping.
Mix egg with molasses.
Add baking soda to sour milk.
Add milk to molasses mixture, then add to dry ingredients.
Pour into cupcake tin with cupcake liners.
Sprinkle with reserved crumbs.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.
A double batch will make 7 small loaves.
May need to bake loaves longer.

title: chocolate-butterscotch pie
directions: Combine sugar and flour.
Add to milk, stirring constantly. Add cocoa.
Cook over hot water, stirring constantly until mixture thickens.
Cover.
Cook 5 minutes.
Combine egg yolks, salt and water.
Add to cooked mixture, slowly stirring.
Add butter; cook 1 minute.
Cool.
Add vanilla.
Pour into baked pastry shell. Cover with meringue and brown.

title: egg and sausage casserole
directions: Spray a 13 x 9-inch pan with Pam and line with bread. Sprinkle with cooked sausage.
Pour egg mixture over all.
Add cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes with foil covering pan.
Remove foil.
Cook 15 more minutes.

title: monterey jack salsa
directions: Mix all together and chill.

title: sherry chiffon pie
directions: Make custard in double boiler with egg yolks, 1/2 cup sugar, salt and wine.
Take off stove and add gelatine; cool.
Beat egg whites and add 1/2 cup sugar gradually; beat stiff.
Beat in the custard mixture and pour in baked pie shell.
Put in refrigerator for 3 hours.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: coconut macaroons
directions: Separate 2 eggs.
Beat whites until stiff (not dry but shiny) with a pinch of salt.
Add sugar all at once to stiffly beaten egg whites.
With a wooden spoon, add cherries, coconut, vanilla, dates and cashews.
Stir all ingredients together.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto parchment paper in a jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes or until a light golden color.
Remove to a rack while still warm.

title: ham torte
directions: Press crust in bottom and up sides of pan.
Sprinkle 1/3 of cheese on bottom.
Top with half of ham, half of potatoes and half of onion slices.
Spread spinach evenly over onion.
Top with 1/3 cheese and remaining ham, potatoes and onion.
Sprinkle remaining 1/3 cup cheese over onion.
Gently press mixture into pan.
Top with second crust and pinch to seal edges.
Cut slits in top crust.
Mix egg and water well.
Brush top crust with egg mixture. Can be covered and refrigerated overnight.
Bake at 375° for 55 to 70 minutes until crust is golden brown and filling well heated.

title: brownie chip cookies
directions: Grease cookie sheets.
In large mixing bowl, combine brownie mix, eggs and oil.
By hand, stir 50 to 75 strokes.
Add chocolate pieces.
Drop by rounded teaspoon, 2-inches apart, onto prepared cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cookies will be soft to the touch.
Cool slightly before removing from cookie sheets.
Frost, if desired.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: zucchini pie
directions: *Use large mature zucchini.

title: 6 week muffins
directions: Mix together.
Batter will keep up to 6 weeks in refrigerator. Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes in sprayed with vegetable oil muffin tins.
Makes 36 medium muffins.
These freeze well if packed in metal tins in freezer.
Just reheat in microwave for breakfast.

title: italian tomato sauce
directions: Saute first 8 ingredients and mushrooms.
When onions are clear, add next 5 ingredients.
Cover.
Simmer 45 minutes, then add parsley.
Top with cheese.
Serve over spaghetti and meatballs.

title: hot pickles
directions: Cook hot peppers in vegetable oil until black; strain and set aside.
Let cucumbers set in salt water 2 to 3 hours.
Wash with cold water.
Mix all ingredients together.
Will last for up to 1 week.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water; set aside.
Cut in shortening and flour.
Add buttermilk, soda, sugar and yeast; blend well. Pinch off dough and roll biscuits; place in greased pan.
Let rise.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Leftover dough may be refrigerated for several days in airtight container.
Makes 2 dozen biscuits.

title: red pickled eggs
directions: Use juice from beets.
You can use some of the beets.
Add sugar, vinegar, water and salt; heat until sugar dissolves. Cool.
Place eggs in bowl or jar.
Pour in beet mixture.
Make sure eggs are covered (add more water if needed).
Cover and marinate in the refrigerator for 2 to 3 days before serving.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Blend well.
Roll into small balls (quarter size).
Place on shallow baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.

title: pork tender loin
directions: Marinate pork in marinade for at least 3 hours, longer if you have the time.
Bake pork in marinade uncovered at 400° for 30 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake, still uncovered for 45 minutes more.
Slice and arrange on platter.
Rosemary sprigs arranged on side look attractive.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Combine broccoli and onion; cook according to package directions.
Drain and add remaining ingredients; stir well.
Pour into greased 2-quart shallow casserole.
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.
(May be doubled.)

title: hamburger harvest casserole
directions: Heat oven to
Combine browned hamburger, onion, tomatoes and salt in skillet.
Drain and put into 1-inch layer in 3 quart casserole.
On top place in layers the potatoes, flour, corn and lima beans.
Bake about 1 hour and then sprinkle cheese. Let bake until cheese is melted or vegetables are tender.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Combine Cool Whip and Eagle Brand milk together.
Beat well. Add lemonade and mix.
This will become thick.
Mix well and pour into pie shell.
Chill well before serving.

title: connie's best ever brownies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add rest of ingredients.
In a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex pan, bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Do not let brownies bake too long.
Take out while still wet looking.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook noodles according to directions.
Rinse.
Cut cheese into 1-inch cubes.
Add rest of ingredients.
Serves 4.
Great to make ahead of time.
Bagels and cream cheese added to it make a nice lunch.

title: pumpkin pecan rum cake
directions: Cool slightly.
Make holes in cake with long pick; pour half of glaze over cake.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Invert onto plate and repeat with remaining glaze.
Cool.

title: mendocino fish stew
directions: Saute onions in olive oil for 5 minutes over medium heat.
Add garlic, stirring briefly.
Turn up heat; add the fish and toss it around, partially cooking all sides.
Add white wine and simmer for 1 minute, turning the fish.
Add peppercorns, tomatoes and olives, letting mixture simmer for 1 minute.
Stir in basil.
In heated bowls, place some potatoes, rice or noodles, then spoon the fish and some of the pan liquid into each bowl.
Grind pepper over the top and sprinkle with parsley.

title: bean casserole
directions: Saute onion and mushrooms in margarine.
Put all ingredients in casserole dish in layers.
Cover with cheese and bread crumbs. Bake at 370° for approximately 15 minutes.

title: perfect creamy baked cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Combine crumbs, sugar and margarine; press on bottom of a 9-inch spring-form pan.
In mixer bowl, beat cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in sweetened condensed milk until smooth.
Add eggs and lemon juice; mix well.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake for 50 to 55 minutes or until center is set; top with sour cream.
Bake 5 minutes longer.
Cool.
Chill.
Top with pie filling.
Refrigerate leftovers (if any).

title: ranch chicken wings
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place drummettes in a 9 x 13-inch or similar size pan.
Melt butter in microwave.
Add hot sauce and vinegar to melted butter and stir or whisk well.
Pour mixture over drummettes.
Sprinkle dressing mix evenly over drummettes.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: spoon bread
directions: Bring milk to a boil.
Add salt.
Slowly add corn meal, stirring constantly.
Cook to a soft mush.
Cool.
Preheat oven to 375°.
To the cooled mush, add egg yolks, butter, sugar and baking powder.
Fold in egg whites.
Turn into a buttered baking dish. Bake about 30 minutes and serve hot in baking dish.

title: homemade coconut pie
directions: Dilute cornstarch in 1/2 cup milk.
Cook mixture of the Pet milk, egg yolks, sugar and diluted cornstarch until thickened.
Let cool.
Add coconut and vanilla.

title: hearty vegetable soup
directions: In a large kettle or Dutch oven, combine shanks, water, bouillon and bay leaves. Bring to a boil; simmer, covered, 1 1/2 hours or until meat is tender. Remove shanks and bay leaves; cut meat into cubes. Discard bones. Cool stock; skim fat from surface. Add meat, tomatoes, carrots, celery, onion and thyme; simmer, covered, about 20 minutes. Add macaroni and zucchini. Cook 10 minutes longer or until tender. Refrigerate leftovers. Makes about 3 quarts.

title: albondigas(meat ball soup)
directions: Bring water to a boil.
In a large bowl, mix together meat, onion, pepper, tenderizer, salt, egg and rice together.
Roll mixture into round balls.
Put meat balls in flour and coat evenly.
Put the floured meat balls into the boiling water and add tomato sauce.
Cook until the meat is ready.

title: pineapple cottage cheese salad
directions: Mix Jell-O.
Add hot water.
Add mayonnaise and marshmallows. Mix well.
Add pineapple juice.
Let cool until partially set (1/2 hour or so).
Add other ingredients and pour into mold.
For color, add maraschino cherries.

title: scones
directions: Roll out flat.
Cut in different shapes.
Bake at 350°.
Serve with butter, jam or honey.

title: m&m cookies
directions: Mix flour, soda and salt; set aside.
Cream butter and sugars, then add vanilla and eggs.
Gradually add flour mixture.
Drop by spoonfuls and place on greased cookie sheet about 2 to 3 inches apart.
Bake at 350° for 9 to 11 minutes.
Makes 7 to 8 dozen.

title: lemony potatoes
directions: Wash potatoes and slice into wedges.
Arrange in buttered pie pan.
Combine butter, lemon juice and salt.
Heat in saucepan. Pour mixture over potatoes.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Sprinkle paprika on top.
Bake at 400° for 40 minutes.
Garnish with parsley.

title: sesame chicken
directions: Marinate chicken in soy sauce for a few minutes.
Roll chicken in mixture of flour and sesame seed.
Drizzle with margarine. Bake in 350° oven until done and golden brown.
Serves 10.

title: hot chocolate(spanish style)
directions: Mix together the milk, chocolate and sugar.
Heat over low flame, stirring with whisk until chocolate is completely dissolved. Turn up heat and bring to a boil.
Allow mixture to bubble up to the top of saucepan.
Remove immediately from heat and beat with whisk.
Repeat boiling and beating three more times, then tilt pan and beat the hot chocolate well with whisk until it is very frothy. Serve immediately.
Makes one cup.

title: mincemeat cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Heat mincemeat and milk to boiling in 3-quart saucepan.
Stir frequently.
Simmer until slightly thickened, about 10 minutes. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Drop dough by rounded teaspoonfuls 2 inches apart onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake until light brown for about 10 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen cookies.

title: hootenanny cake
directions: Grease bottom of tube pan.
Mix ingredients and beat for 5 minutes.

title: coconut delight
directions: Blend and press into 9 x 13-inch dish.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, milk and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Gradually add to creamed mixture.
Roll out on powdered sugar surface.
Dust cookie cutters with powdered sugar.
Cut and place on ungreased Teflon coated cookie sheet. Bake at 375° until a very light brown on the very edge of cookie.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Combine
dry ingredients.
Combine eggs and oil;
blend the dry
ingredients
and
egg	mixture just until moistened. Fold
in strawberries and nuts.
Bake at 350° in 2 greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pans about 1 hour.

title: brown sugar muffins
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Combine eggs and milk.
Add dry ingredients to sugar mixture.
Alternate with egg-milk mixture. Add nuts.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350°
in well greased muffin pan.

title: ham 'n cheese roll-ups
directions: Combine Cheddar cheese, cream cheese and margarine until well blended.
Spread 1/4 of mixture on each ham slice.
Roll up from short sides; chill for several hours.
Slice rolls into 1/2-inch thick slices.
Arrange each slice on a Ritz cracker.

title: pineapple duck a la theresa shea
directions: Cut duckling into serving pieces.
Place in a large wok and cover with boiling water.
Simmer, covered, until almost tender (about 1 hour).
Skim off fat.
Stir in salt, pepper, soy sauce and pineapple with syrup.
Cook 30 minutes or until duckling is done.
Serves 4.

title: breakfast
directions: Can be arranged in a 9 x 13-inch pan the night before and baked in morning.
Layer ingredients, ham first, then cheese and eggs on top.
Cover with cream, letting yolks peak out.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes; remove from oven and sprinkle generously with Parmesan cheese.
Return to oven and bake 8 to 10 minutes longer. Serve with English muffins or toast.

title: corned beef salad or spread
directions: Mix the jello and the boiling water.
Fold in the remaining ingredients; chill until set.
May use as a salad, sandwich spread or hors d'oeuvre with crackers.

title: fresh apple or pear cake
directions: Can add 1/2 cup raisins.

title: mexican dip
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In a baking dish, spread cream cheese over the bottom. Pour cans of chili con carne over cream cheese. Cover top of chili con carne with shredded cheese. Place in oven. When cheese on top is melted, take out. Serve with Tostitos.

title: michelle's baked chicken with mushrooms
directions: Put mushrooms and parsley in bottom of baking dish.
Place chicken on mushrooms.
Mix other ingredients and pour over chicken.
Cover.
Bake at 375° for 1 1/4 hours.
Uncover and bake 15 minutes more to brown chicken.
Makes 4 servings with 190 calories each.

title: chocolate bars
directions: In a saucepan, over low heat, melt the chocolate and butterscotch chips with the peanut butter.
Stir often.

title: nice and easy barbecue sauce
directions: In a saucepan, cook onion in butter until tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Simmer 5 minutes, stirring often.
Makes about 3 1/2 cups.

title: quiche
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together.
Pour into pie crusts. Sprinkle remaining ingredients on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: cranberry orange bread
directions: Mix ingredients.
Mix in thoroughly 2 tablespoons Crisco with a pastry cutter.
Add grated rind and juice of 1 orange plus extra orange juice if needed to make 3/4 cup.
Add 1 beaten egg.
Fold in 1 cup raw cranberries cut in halves.
Bake 1 hour at 350° in greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch pan.

title: coconut loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a greased and floured loaf tin.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes.
Test after 30 minutes by inserting a toothpick into loaf. If toothpick comes out clean, it is done. Do not overbake or it will be crumbly.
Serve as any hot fresh bread, sliced with butter and/or jam.

title: pork loin roast
directions: Rub salt and pepper over roast.
Sprinkle red pepper on top and sides.
Place in aluminum foil, uncovered at 250° for 2 hours. For last 45 minutes to 1 hour, cover tightly with foil.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Sift the first 3 ingredients into a 2 or 3-quart saucepan, then gradually blend in the cold water and lemon juice.
When smooth, add egg yolks and butter, blending thoroughly.
Stirring constantly, gradually add boiling water.
Bring mixture to a full boil, stirring gently.
As it begins to thicken, reduce heat and allow to simmer 1 minute.
Remove from heat and stir in 1 teaspoon grated lemon peel.
Pour into baked pie shell and cover with meringue.

title: cherry torte
directions: Cook pudding with milk.
Pour this pudding over cooled crust. Let cool.
Put cherries over top of cooled pudding and put in the refrigerator overnight.
Can be served with whipped cream, ice cream or as is.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix 2 cups of salad dressing with dressing mix.
Add to the salad.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix well the ground beef, onion, oatmeal, egg and crackers. Press into a loaf pan and add ketchup or barbecue sauce on top. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: taco salad
directions: In a large bowl, cut up lettuce and tomatoes.
In skillet, brown hamburger and onion.
Add chili powder, salt, pepper and hot sauce (to taste).
In another pan, melt cheese and Ro-Tel tomatoes.
Pour hamburger mixture over lettuce, then add cheese sauce.
Serves 4.

title: hot dogs
directions: Heat wieners for 15 minutes.
Heat chili about 5 minutes.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Brown hamburger in butter.
Put layer of meat in 2-quart casserole.
Top with a layer of each vegetable and rice.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Pour hot water over all ingredients.
Bake at 325° for 2 hours.

title: beef barbecue
directions: Combine ground beef, chopped onion and green pepper in frypan until beef is browned.
Add remainder of ingredients.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
Ready to serve on warm toasted rolls.

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift together and mix by hand the first 5 ingredients.
Then add remaining ingredients and mix well.

title: parmesan potatoes
directions: Place Parmesan cheese, olive oil, basil and red pepper flakes in large bowl.
Add potatoes and toss until well coated.
Arrange in single layer on baking sheet.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour, turning the potatoes after 30 minutes.

title: dutch apple pie
directions: Pare and thinly slice enough apples to fill pie pan heaping. Mix the sugar, flour and salt.
Mix thoroughly with the apples. Put in pastry lined pan.
Pour the cream over the apples. Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake at 425° until crust is light brown (10 minutes).
Reduce heat to 350° and cook approximately 45 minutes or until apples are done.

title: fat-free sweet potato corn muffins
directions: Combine the flour, cornmeal and baking powder. Stir to mix well. Add the sweet potatoes, orange or apple juice, molasses and egg whites. Stir just until the dry ingredients are moistened. Fold in the raisins or dates.
Coat muffin cups with nonstick cooking spray and fill 3/4 full with batter.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes or just until a wooden toothpick inserted in the center of a muffin comes out clean.
Remove the muffin tin from the oven and allow it to sit for 5 minutes before removing the muffins.
Serve warm or at room temperature.

title: wild rice chicken salad
directions: Prepare rice according to package directions; refrigerate until chilled.
Cut chicken into cubes.
In small bowl, stir together salt, mayo, milk and lemon juice.
In large bowl, combine chicken, grape halves, celery, chopped cashews, onions and chilled rice.
Fold in mayo mixture.
Refrigerate 2 to 3 hours.

title: cheese log
directions: Let the cream cheese and Velveeta stand at room temperature until soft.
Cut into small chunks and blend together.
Add pepper, garlic and pecans; mix well until blended.
Oil a large piece of foil and spread cheese out flat.
Sprinkle with chili powder. Chill in refrigerator until firm.
Roll into a log and slice as needed.

title: cheesy potato casserole
directions: Boil potatoes; cool and cube.
Heat soup and add butter until melted.
Blend in sour cream, onions and cheese.
Pour mixture over potatoes and mix gently.
Pour into a large casserole dish. Top with grated cheese and bake for 45 minutes at 350°.
Top with more sour cream, if desired.

title: coca-cola barbecue sauce
directions: Saute onion and garlic until soft (not browned).
Add all other ingredients and simmer (up to 1 hour).
Brush on chicken during final 10 to 15 minutes of grilling.
Also good on pork.

title: sue b's frozen cranberry salad
directions: Mix all together.
Freeze.
May be divided for smaller portions.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and salt.
Add 1/2 cup boiling water. Dissolve yeast in warm water and add egg and stir.
Pour this mixture into the shortening mixture.
Mix well with a fork.
Add 3 cups flour.
Mix well with a fork.
Dough will be sticky.
Cover tightly with Saran Wrap.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: lemon chicken
directions: Dip boneless chicken breasts in beaten egg and 1 tablespoon lemon juice. Then roll in flour, paprika and garlic powder. Brown in butter. Remove breasts. Stir together water, 2 tablespoons lemon juice and bouillon cubes. Bring to a boil. Reduce to simmer. Return breasts to sauce and cook until liquid is absorbed.

title: au gratin potatoes
directions: Spread frozen hash browns in a 13 x 9-inch baking pan. Cut up butter on top of potatoes.
Pour half and half on top.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Add cheese and bake 10 minutes longer until cheese is melted.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Lay on jelly roll size pan.
Press together.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 350°; cool.

title: buster bars
directions: Crush cookies and mix with 1/2 cup melted oleo.
Put all but 1/3 cup in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Freeze 1 hour.
Spread softened ice cream on crust.
Mix evaporated milk, chocolate chips, oleo and sugar and bring to a boil.
Boil 8 minutes.
Cool to lukewarm. Spread pecans on ice cream.
Pour sauce over pecans.
Freeze again.
Top with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with crumbs.
Freeze.
Wrap with foil.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Boil chicken and cut into pieces.
Cook rice according to package directions.
Drain rice and pour into baking dish or cake pan.
Mix soup and chicken into rice.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted.

title: s'mores
directions: Heat corn syrup, margarine and chocolate chips in saucepan. Remove from heat. Stir in vanilla.
Pour over cereal.
Toss quickly until coated. Fold in marshmallows, one cup at a time. Press in greased 9 x 13-inch cake pan with waxed paper.
Let stand 1 hour.
Cut into 48 squares.

title: rumaki
directions: Cut livers into halves.
Mix soy sauce and brown sugar; stir in livers and water chestnuts.
Cover and refrigerate for 2 hours; drain.
Fry bacon until almost done; drain.
Wrap a piece of liver and water chestnuts in bacon.
Secure with wooden toothpicks.
Microwave for 2 to 3 minutes until liver and bacon are cooked through.

title: mock jam
directions: Blend tomatoes to pulp consistency.
Do not drain.
In large pan, bring to a rolling boil.
Add
sugar; boil 15 minutes, stirring almost constantly.
Take off stove.
Add jello; stir until well mixed.
Put into jars and seal.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together in pan.
Mix in small bowl egg yolks and one cup milk.
Add to flour mixture.
Add another cup of milk to mixture and cook until thick.
Pour into pie crust.

title: crab stuffed manicotti
directions: Combine cheese, eggs, garlic salt, onion and parsley in a large bowl.
Stir in crabmeat.
Carefully stuff filling into cooked manicotti shells.
Arrange stuffed manicotti in a baking pan.
Melt butter and slightly cook mushrooms in butter; add pimento.
Pour this over manicotti, making sure to cover all with butter.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 to 50 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: escalloped pineapple
directions: Put bread into a buttered casserole dish.
Beat eggs and milk together thoroughly in a small bowl.
Add sugar to the pineapple, then add the egg mixture, stirring together.
Pour over bread cubes and dot with oleo.
Bake in 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes or until knife comes out clean.

title: pineapple slush
directions: Boil water and sugar together for 5 minutes.
Mix orange juice and lemonade together, then add boiled water and sugar.
Add pineapple juice.
Mix together and freeze.
Takes about a day. Equals 1 ice cream pail.
Add glass 1/3 to 1/2 full of slush, then add 7-Up, Mountain Dew or Mellow Yellow with slush in each glass.

title: chocolate cream delight
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients and place in a 9 x 11-inch baking dish.
Bake at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Let cool.

title: lemon pound cake
directions: Empty cake mix in bowl and beat in eggs, sugar and oil.
Mix in apricot nectar.
Bake at 350° in a greased 10-inch tube pan for about 45 minutes or until cake tests done.

title: kibbee khishk
directions: Soak bulgur in warm water for at least 15 minutes.
Squeeze dry and mix with ground beef and minced onion.
Add salt and pepper, mix well and form into balls of approximately 1 to 2 inches across. Set balls aside.
In large kettle, bring the water to a rapid boil and add the khishk stirring constantly.
Reduce heat to medium and stir on and off for at least 30 minutes.
Khishk should thicken slightly.
While Khishk is cooking, cut cabbage into 1/2-inch strips and par boil until almost done.
In small skillet, cook the mint in the oil on low heat for a few minutes.
Add to the Khishk by adding a spoon of Khishk to the skillet and then dump the contents into the kettle.
Add the Kibbee balls; let cook for at least 1/2 hour, add the cabbage and serve in large bowls like soup.

title: wacky cake
directions: Sift together flour, cocoa, baking soda, salt and sugar.
Mix together oil, vinegar, vanilla and cold water. Mix all together. Grease and flour cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
(It's not as thick as regular cake.)

title: shoestring apple pie
directions: Mix all together and put in unbaked pie shell.
Sprinkle cinnamon on top and bake at 350° until done.
Test like a custard pie.

title: verdi's oven fried fish
directions: Heat oven to 500° or 525° (yes!).
Wash and towel dry fish. Arrange in fairly thick portions on small baking sheet.
Drizzle with lemon juice.
Season with salt, pepper and paprika.
Combine melted butter with enough bread crumbs to make a soft mixture. Spoon/pat thickly on top of fish and press down firmly.
Bake for 15 minutes.

title: apricot chicken
directions: Mix together the dressing, onion soup and jam or preserves. Spread mixture onto chicken.
Cover dish; bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: apple oat crisp
directions: Mix all ingredients together and arrange in an 8-inch square baking dish.

title: dirt cake
directions: Grind cookies in blender.
Mix pudding with milk; then mix in Cool Whip.
Add cream cheese with margarine and mix into vanilla mixture.

For full effect, use "new gallonish" plant pot and layer 1-inch cookie mixture, then 1-inch vanilla mixture and repeat. Serve with fake flowers stuck in middle and dish out with a trowel. Gummy worms can be added for fun.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Brown chops in small amount of oil.
Slice onions and potatoes about 1/4-inch thick.
Layer chops, onions and potatoes in pan or covered casserole dish.
Salt and pepper.
Top with can of soup and 1 can water.
Cover pan with foil and bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: broccoli slaw
directions: Add dressing and mix.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Allow egg whites to reach room temperature.
Beat egg whites and add sugar 2 tablespoons at a time until stiff.
Fold in pecans and chocolate chips.
Line cookie sheet with foil and drop by teaspoon.
When ready to put in oven, turn oven off and leave cookies in oven 12 hours or overnight.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix all together and chill until ready to serve.

title: mary's chile
directions: Soak beans overnight.
Saute green peppers and onion.
Brown hamburger and place in crock-pot.
Start at night on High for 1 hour, then on low all night.
Add chili powder and tomatoes and then cook on high until tender.

title: spicy wine roast
directions: Mix all ingredients except roast.
Put roast in crock-pot. Pour mixture over.
Cover and cook on low for 8 hours or on high for 4 to 5 hours.

title: "italian drumstix"
directions: *Other chicken parts (breasts, thighs) can be substituted.

title: frozen peanut butter pie
directions: Whip cheese at low speed until soft and fluffy.
Beat in sugar and peanut butter at medium speed.
Slowly beat in milk.
Fold 3/4 of whipped topping into mixture.
Pour into pie shell.
Freeze until firm.
Put Cool Whip on top.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Heat tomato soup (undiluted) to boiling point; whip in cream cheese.
Add dissolved gelatine to hot soup.
Add rest of ingredients (except shrimp)
in mixture with mayonnaise.
Add shrimp; mix altogether well.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix together well the mayo, ketchup, mustard and cream cheese. Chop shrimp real fine. Make sure shrimp is drained.
Mix celery and onion. Line small bowl with Saran Wrap and fill with spread. Refrigerate a few hours.

title: chips ahoy brownie pie
directions: Cut 5 cookies in half; set aside.
Finely roll remaining cookies.
Combine cookie crumbs and 1/4 cup melted butter; press on bottom and up sides of 9-inch pie pan.

title: fudge pie
directions: Melt butter and add other ingredients.
Pour into greased pan and bake at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: jello salad
directions: Mix all together and chill.

title: great muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Spray 12 (2 1/2-inch) muffin pan cups vegetable cooking spray.
In small bowl, combine oats and water. In medium bowl, combine flour, dry milk, baking powder, salt and cinnamon.
In small bowl, beat egg whites, brown sugar and oil. Stir into oats and water.
Add to dry ingredients all at once, stirring just until moistened.
Fold in raisins.

title: potato wedges
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Combine cornflakes, seasoned salt, onion salt and garlic salt in small bowl.
Mix well and set aside.
Cut each unpeeled potato into 8 wedges.
Dip in vegetable oil; roll in cornflake mixture.
Place on greased baking sheet.
Bake for 30 minutes or until tender.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: divinity frosting
directions: Boil sugar, syrup and water until it spins a thread.
Beat egg whites and dash of salt until stiff.
Add boiled mixture and vanilla.
Frost cooled cake.
Garnish with nuts.

title: old world sauerbraten
directions: Place meat in deep ceramic or glass bowl.
Combine water, vinegar, onion, lemon, cloves, bay leaves, salt, pepper and sugar.
Pour over meat.
Cover and refrigerate for 24 to 36 hours, turn meat several times during marinating.
Place beef in slow-cooking pot; pour 1 cup marinade over meat.
Cover and cook on low 6 to 8 hours.
Place meat on serving platter.
Strain meat juices and return to pot.
Turn control to high.
Stir in gingersnaps; cover and cook on high for 10 to 15 minutes.
Pour over meat.
Makes 8 servings.

title: emily's delicious chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour Bundt pan.
Mix and bake for 45 minutes in a Bundt pan.
Cool 10 minutes in pan before inverting onto plate.

title: new orleans bread pudding, the lighter side
directions: Melt 1 teaspoon butter in a large skillet.
Add the apples and 2 tablespoons sugar; cover and cook over medium heat for 2 minutes.
Remove the cover; stir gently and continue to cook for 6 minutes longer until the apples are tender.
Sprinkle the cinnamon over the apples; stir gently until the cinnamon is absorbed.
Set aside uncovered.
Place one layer of bread slices in 13 x 9 x 2-inch buttered ovenproof pan, packing them close together. Sprinkle with half of the raisins.
Spread the apples and all their juice over the top.
Sprinkle with the remaining raisins. Make another layer of bread.
(Make only 2 layers.)

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cut meat into rectangular bite-size pieces.
Brown quickly in butter.
Push meat to the side of the pan.
Add mushrooms and onion; cook just until tender.
Add broth; heat just to boiling. Blend sour cream and flour; stir into broth.
Cook and stir until mixture thickens slightly.
Serve over cooked noodles.
Serves 4.

title: german potato salad
directions: Cook bacon in large skillet.
Drain off fat.
Measure fat and return 1/4 cup to skillet.
Add onion and cook 1 minute.
Blend in flour.
Stir in water and vinegar.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture is thick and bubbly.
Stir in sugar, salt and pepper.

title: apple ring fritters
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Add milk and egg.
Beat well.
Peel and core apples and slice in rings about 1/4-inch thick.
Dip rings in batter and drop into skillet containing 1/2-inch of hot melted shortening.
Fry until golden brown on both sides.
Drain on paper towel.
Mix sugar and cinnamon together and sprinkle over fritters.
Makes 16 to 20.

title: texas cake
directions: Bring to a boil margarine, cocoa and water.
Add to flour, salt, sugar, baking soda, eggs and sour cream.
Cream and pour onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: sugar-free fudge
directions: Melt margarine and chocolate; stir in sweetener and vanilla. Combine chocolate mixture with cream cheese; beat until smooth. Stir in raisins and spread mixture in a lightly greased 8-inch square pan spread with Pam cooking spray.
Refrigerate until firm; cut into 1-inch squares.
Yields 64 squares.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Boil syrup, sugar and cream of tartar until it forms a ball in cold water (236°).
Add butter and soda.
Form into balls.
