title: taco salad
directions: Brown ground beef, add taco seasoning, reserving 1 tablespoon for dressing.
Use a large bowl and layer ingredients in salad bowl, starting with lettuce and ending with cheese.
Cover and refrigerate.

title: dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Grab a chip, dip and eat.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream together Crisco, brown sugar and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla; mix well.
Add flour, salt and baking soda, then add chocolate chips.
If dough is too sticky, add 1/4 cup flour.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: sweet and sour mixed bean salad
directions: Drain all.
Wash kidney beans in strainer until all slick juices are off.
Mix them using spatula or wooden spoon.
Pour dressing over them.

title: strawberry daiquiris
directions: Combine all the ingredients in a food processor.
Blend to consistency desired.
Serve immediately.
Garnish as desired.

title: hot potato salad
directions: Mince bacon and fry until crisp.
Remove.
Cook onion in bacon fat until lightly browned.
Blend in flour.
Add bacon, vinegar, 1/2 cup water and seasonings; bring to boil.
Add potato, mixing lightly; heat.
Sprinkle with parsley; serve.
Or, cool, refrigerate and reheat before serving.
Serves 4.

title: hot chocolate
directions: Mix all together well.
Use about 1/4 cup mix to a mug of hot water.
Makes big batch.
Keep in airtight container.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Combine mushroom soup and sour cream soup.
Place meatballs in slow cooker.
Cover meatballs with soup mixture.
Add Parmesan cheese to taste.
Cook in slow cooker for 2 to 4 hours before serving.

title: dishpan cookies
directions: Cream first four ingredients.
Sift next four and add.
Sift and mix in last five ingredients all together.
Bake at 325° until golden brown, approximately 8 to 10 minutes.

title: crock pot chicken or steak
directions: Mix ingredients well in crock pot. Add chicken or steak. Start on high heat then turn down to low and let simmer for 2 or 3 hours. Do not salt.

title: cornbread mexican casserole
directions: Saute ground beef; drain.
Add picante sauce and enchilada sauce.
Keep on low heat in the skillet.

title: saucepan rice pudding
directions: In a heavy medium saucepan, bring milk to boiling.
Stir in uncooked rice, raisins and salt.
Cover pot and cook over low heat, stirring often, for 30 to 40 minutes, or until most of the milk is absorbed.
Mixture may appear curdled.
Take pot off heat and stir in butter, vanilla, sugar and cinnamon.
Cool and refrigerate or enjoy warm.

title: quick italian bake
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease 9-inch pie plate.
Cook ground beef until brown.
Drain.
Stir in tomato and seasoning.
Spread in plate.
Stir baking mix, milk and eggs with fork until blended. Pour into plate.
Bake 25 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 2 or 3 minutes longer or until melted.
Serve with pizza sauce.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: caramel corn
directions: Mix sugar, butter and buttered pecan syrup; boil.
Add soda and vanilla; stir and pour over corn and almonds.
(Almonds are optional.)
Cook one hour at 200°.
Stir every 15 minutes.
Store in gallon jars for snacks.
This recipe will serve 15 people.

title: chinese pepper steak
directions: Trim and cut meat in slivers.
Put oil, salt and pepper in electric frying pan or skillet.
Add meat and cook until brown. Add 1 cup beef bouillon, garlic, celery, onion and green pepper. Simmer until vegetables are to desired doneness, approximately 20 minutes.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Chop cabbage in large pieces; place in bottom of greased baking dish.
Brown meat and onions.
Pour off fat and stir in rice and tomatoes.
Place this mixture on top of cabbage and add 1 cup of water if you think it is too dry.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
I usually double this recipe and serve it with garlic bread for a hearty winter meal.

title: sweet and sour sauce dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and cook, stirring constantly, until thickened and translucent.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt oleo in a 13 x 9 1/2-inch pan.
Combine flour, 1 cup sugar and milk.
Pour mixture over the melted oleo; do not stir.
Combine peaches and remaining sugar in saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Pour over batter in pan; do not stir.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes, or until top is brown.

title: brazilian chocolate
directions: Combine chocolate syrup, salt, cinnamon and coffee in saucepan.
Stir in 1/4 cup hot water.
Cook over medium heat until heated through.
Add 1 1/2 cups of hot water and milk.
Cook until heated through, stirring occasionally.
Add vanilla.
Beat with rotary beater until foamy.
Serve immediately. Yields 6 servings.

title: easy shrimp spread
directions: Combine all ingredients with a mixer.
Chill.
Serve with crackers or breadsticks.

title: pink party punch
directions: Mix and chill.
Makes 1 1/2 gallons.

title: dream puffs
directions: Beat egg whites in small bowl until stiff peaks form. Gradually add sugar, 1 tablespoon at a time, beating well until blended.
Fold remaining ingredients into meringue.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 250° for 30 minutes.
Remove from sheet to wire rack to cool.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: california casserole
directions: Boil vegetables; drain. Melt 1/2 of the margarine in saucepan. Crumble crackers, then add to melted margarine. Set aside. Melt other half of margarine and add to soup and cheese to make sauce. Place vegetables in dish. Pour sauce over vegetables and sprinkle cracker mixture on top. Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water or pineapple juice from crushed pineapple.
Add crushed pineapple, nuts and cranberry sauce to jello mixture.
Pour into individual molds or a mold. Serve on lettuce.

title: quick fudge glaze
directions: Put sugar, butter and milk into a saucepan.
Bring to a boil over medium heat; boil 1 minute.
Add chocolate chips; stir until melted and combined.
Pour and spread over brownies, cake or cookies.
This will set up very quickly like a soft fudge.

title: macaroni salad #1
directions: Cook macaroni as directed on package; drain.
Combine all ingredients, stirring gently.
Cover and refrigerate.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix peanut butter with powdered sugar until "pea size". Sprinkle bottom of pie shell with 3/4 of the mixture.
(Set aside remainder.)
Make pie filling.
Pour over peanut butter mixture in pie shell.
Top with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle remainder of peanut butter mixture on top of Cool Whip.
Refrigerate several hours before serving.
(My family's favorite dessert.)

title: strawberrioca
directions: Combine pudding mix, jello mix and water in saucepan.
Cook and stir over medium heat until it comes to a full boil and is clear.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Prepare Dream Whip.
Add to chilled pudding mixture.
Chill 3 hours.
Top with sliced strawberries.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Cook broccoli according to package direction; omit salt, set aside.
Combine milk and margarine in a saucepan; cook over medium heat, stir constantly until heated through (don't boil).
Stir in potato flakes and onion.
Place in blender; add broccoli and process 30 seconds, until smooth.
Return to saucepan.
Stir in broth, salt and pepper; simmer 10 minutes, stir often.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Sprinkle the cucumbers with salt; let stand 15 minutes.
Drain liquid.
Add onion, vinegar and pepper.
Just before serving, stir in sour cream.
Yields 6 servings.

title: salsa
directions: Mix all together.
Cook 1 to 2 hours until thick.
Cool.
Put in containers and freeze.
Serve with tostada chips.

title: morning glory muffins
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking soda, cinnamon and salt.
Stir in carrot, raisins, coconut and pecans. In a separate bowl, combine eggs, oil, apple and vanilla.
Add to flour mixture.
Stir only until combined.
Spoon into greased or lined tins.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes.
Makes 18 muffins.

title: russian tea cakes
directions: Mix thoroughly, butter, sugar and vanilla. Sift together flour and salt and stir in, then mix nuts, mix well. Chill dough. Roll into 1in balls. Place 2 1/2 in. apart on ungreased baking sheet. Bake 400 degrees until set, but not brown, (10-12 min.).

title: taco dip
directions: Mix cream cheese, sour cream and seasoning mix and spread in pan.
Mix the rest of ingredients and spread on top.
Top with shredded Mozzarella cheese and black olives.

title: granola fruit crisp
directions: In a bowl combine first 4 ingredients.
Cut in oleo until mixture resembles coarse crumbs; set aside.
Arrange fruit in a 10 x 6 x 2-inch dish.
Combine orange and lemon juice; pour over fruit.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Top with granola mixture.
Bake in a 375° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Put each ingredients in layers.
Leave in layers and chill for 12 hours to 24 hours.
When ready to serve, toss the layers. Excellent.

title: hawaiian fruit cake
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients until smooth.
Chop nuts and fruit; dredge in flour and add to batter.
Mix and pour in 4 layer pans. Bake at 275° for 1 hour.

title: baked beans with ham and maple syrup(microwave)
directions: Place ham in center of an ungreased 11 x 9 x 2 inch microwave dish.
Arrange carrots single layer around ham.
Combine maple syrup and Dijon mustard.
Pour over ham and carrots.
Cover with plastic wrap, venting one edge.
Microwave on high for
8 minutes (7 minutes if over 1000 watt), stirring once.
In a separate bowl, mix beans, ketchup, dry mustard and chili powder.
Combine with ham and carrots.
Microwave uncovered for 8 minutes, stirring midway.
Sprinkle bread crumbs and butter over casserole. Microwave 2 more minutes or place under broiler 4 inches from the top for 1 minute.
Serves 4.

title: yummy bars
directions: Mix cake mix with margarine and 1/3 cup evaporated milk. Spread 1/2 in pan and bake at 350° for 6 minutes.
Melt caramels with 1/3 cup evaporated milk.
Sprinkle chocolate chips and nuts over cake.
Drizzle caramel mixture over cake.
Crumble rest of cake mix over top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Enjoy!

title: applesauce cake
directions: Mix; bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes. (I use Bundt pan.)

title: coconut pie
directions: Combine milk, sugar, biscuit mix, eggs, butter and vanilla in electric blender.
Cover and blend on low 3 minutes.
Add coconut and pour into 9-inch greased pie pan.
Let stand a few minutes. Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.

title: holy guacamole
directions: Peel and mash 1 avocado.
Mix with lemon juice, cilantro, garlic, basil and salt.
Dice remaining avocado and fold into mixture with red pepper, salsa, green onion and chopped almonds. Garnish with sour cream.
Serve with tortilla chips and fresh vegetables.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Trim excess fat from chicken.
Place chicken on board and flatten to 1/4-inch thick.
Place chopped jalapeno and grated cheese on each breast.
Roll lengthwise, tucking edges under. Secure with toothpicks.

title: roast beef salad with horseradish sauce
directions: Twenty minutes before serving, mix tomato with horseradish sauce, parsley and lemon juice; set aside.
In large salad bowl, tear romaine and leaf lettuce into bite size pieces.
Cut roast beef into 1-inch wide strips.
Put on top of lettuce.
Drizzle dressing over salad.
Drain olives and slice.
Sprinkle over salad.
Toss before serving.
Makes 4 servings.

title: 3 bean salad
directions: Drain beans well; add chopped pepper to beans.
Combine the remaining ingredients and mix well.
Now mix all together and let stand in the fridge for 24 hours.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake for 45 minutes in a greased pan.
Bundt or 9 x 13-inch or bread pans.

title: magical crystal garden
directions: Mix salt, water, bluing and ammonia in a bowl.
Put charcoal in a clear glass container.
Pour the mixture over the charcoal. Sprinkle drops of food colorings on charcoal to give color.
Set container in warm place.
Carefully water a little when liquid is absorbed.

title: ginger pancakes with maple pecan sauce
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients in a large bowl; make a well in center of mixture.
Combine buttermilk, water, eggs, margarine and brown sugar.
Add to dry ingredients, stirring just until dry ingredients are moistened.
For each pancake, pour 1/4 cup batter onto a hot, lightly greased skillet.
Cook until tops bubble and edges look cooked.
Flip.
Top with Maple Pecan Sauce.

title: mrs. bozarth's salad
directions: Bring the pineapple, sugar and Jell-O to a boil.
Remove from heat and add 2 cups ice and water.
Stir.
Place in refrigerator. Continue to stir and check until slightly congealed.
Add the nuts, cheese and whipped topping.
Mix and return to refrigerator. May be poured into mold now.

title: poor man's sausage
directions: Mix well.
Refrigerate 3 days.
Mix every day.
On 4th day shape into logs.
Place on broiler pan or rack with drip pan under it.
Bake 8 hours at 160°.

title: a slushy punch for christmas
directions: Mix all this together; then freeze.
When you take it out, as it begins to thaw, add 1 to 2 liters of ginger ale.

title: layered salad
directions: Layer in a deep clear glass bowl.
Layer the ingredients in alternating colors.
This salad is very pretty as well as tasty.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Blend sugar, oil and eggs.
Stir in zucchini.
Add the remaining ingredients except nuts.
Beat.
Add nuts.
Grease and flour two 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: 3-layer delight
directions: Crust:
Melt butter.
Add flour and nuts.
Mix well and press into pan.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: sylvia's cheesecake
directions: Have all ingredients, except cream, at room temperature.

title: ham and vegetable roll-ups
directions: Mix the croutons with 1/4 cup butter; spread in bottom of 9-inch baking dish.
Combine soup, mayonnaise and lemon juice. Spoon half of mixture over croutons; set remainder aside.
Mix together spinach, sour cream, onion and Worcestershire sauce. Spread spinach mixture on each ham slice.
Place asparagus spear on top; roll up.
Place rolls seam side down in baking dish. Spoon remaining sauce over top.
Saute mushrooms in butter. Sprinkle over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly. Serves 4 to 6.

title: cheesy lasagna
directions: Grate all cheeses.
Boil noodles until tender; drain.
In large glass baking dish, spread a dipper full of sauce to cover the bottom.
Place a layer of noodles, then top with Mozzarella cheese.
Top again with sauce.
Repeat with noodles and then Swiss cheese and sauce.
Repeat with noodles, Mozzarella cheese and sauce.
Lasagna should be 4 layers thick.

title: sugar-free lemonade
directions: Combine lemon juice and Equal.
Stir in water.
Add ice cubes. Garnish with lemon slice.
Makes 1 (8-ounce) serving containing 32 calories.
Diabetic Exchange:
1/2 fruit.

title: m&m cookies
directions: *If using self-rising flour, omit soda and salt.

title: deviled shrimp eggs
directions: Slice eggs in half lengthwise.
Remove yolks and mash.
Mash shrimp, setting aside 12 tiny shrimp.
Combine celery, carrots, onion and vinegar; mix well with salad dressings.
Stir in eggs and shrimp; mix well.
Fill egg whites.
Place a shrimp on each top, then sprinkle with paprika.
Yields 12 stuffed eggs.

title: rhubarb cobbler
directions: Put rhubarb in a baking dish; pour sugar over fruit and then cover with crust.
Bake.
This will work with any fruit.
Bake for 40 minutes at 350° or until crust is done.

title: shrimp, eggplant dressing
directions: Brown beef and pork in oil.
Add onion, bell pepper and celery; saute.
Add roux and eggplant (diced).
Stir well and add water.
Let cook on medium-low for 3 hours, adding small amounts of water as needed.
Stock will get brown and thick.
Add shrimp and cook 20 minutes longer.
Add cooked rice and green onions. Mix well and cover.
Let sit for 10 minutes.

title: seafood gumbo
directions: Roux:
Combine flour and oil; cook over medium heat until dark brown, stirring constantly.
Stir in onion, celery, green pepper, garlic, black and red peppers.
Cook over medium heat until vegetables are tender.
Stir often.

title: parmesan halibut
directions: Combine cheese and flour.
Dip the halibut in the mixture and saute in butter until fish flakes when tested with a fork.
Remove halibut from frying pan and place on platter.
Pour pan drippings over fish and sprinkle with parsley.
Makes 4 servings.

title: sausage balls *
directions: Mix sausage, cheese and biscuit mix.
Shape into 1-inch balls. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes on ungreased cookie sheet.

title: jello fruit mold
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water in a blender.
Add cream cheese, fruit and sugar.
Mix in blender.
Put in a greased bowl and fold in Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.
Top with more fruit.

title: chicken paprika
directions: Dice onion.
Melt butter in a large frying pan.
Fry onion in butter until tender.
Add chicken.
Brown lightly on all sides. Add salt and pepper.
Cover and cook over medium-low heat for 5 minutes.
Add soup and milk.
Make sure soup and milk are blended. Add paprika.
Cover and cook about 30 to 45 minutes or until done. Serve plain or over hot biscuits.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni as directed.
Add chopped celery, onions, and peppers in large bowl, then add boiled eggs.
Mix well.

title: sombrero dip
directions: Brown meat; add catsup, beans and the seasonings.
Place in a chafing dish and layer the onion, cheese and olives on top.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: pumpkin walnut date bread
directions: Combine all dry ingredients in a large bowl.
Add wet ingredients and beat at medium speed about one minute.
Fold in walnuts and dates.
Pour batter into a 2-quart (9 x 5-inch) loaf pan.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: creamy cucumber slaw
directions: Toss cucumber and onion until mixed.
Blend remaining ingredients thoroughly and pour over vegetables.
Chill for at least 8 to 10 hours before serving.
The best ever eaten!

title: creme mints
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a bowl.
Mix with fork until moist.
Add evaporated milk.
Mix with hands until workable. Don't make it too moist.
Roll into pea-sized balls or slightly larger.
Flatten with fork.
Let dry.

title: dill spread
directions: Chop shrimp; reserve a few.
Combine cream cheese, mayonnaise, garlic powder, Worcestershire sauce, lemon juice and onion; blend. Chill several hours.
Shape as desired.
Garnish with few shrimp and fresh dill (optional).

title: dyer's hot potato salad
directions: Soak gelatine in cold water, add boiling water and stir to dissolve.
Add lemon juice and sugar; strain.

When beginning to stiffen, put a layer of jelly (jello) in a dish, then layer of sliced bananas, another layer of jelly, then one of sliced oranges, another of jelly, one of sliced pineapple, and finish with jelly.

title: strawberry cobbler *
directions: *Other fresh or frozen fruit may be substituted.

title: wild rice-chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 30 minutes, then cover and bake 30 more minutes.

title: st. joseph spaghetti
directions: Put bread in blender.
Mince garlic very fine.
Chop parsley. Mix all ingredients except spaghetti together until well blended (with your hands).
Cook spaghetti or linguine al dente.
Drain and mix with bread crumb mixture.
Happy St. Joseph's Day.

title: thrifty rice sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage in skillet, breaking up with fork.
Arrange layers of rice, sausage and onion in greased casserole dish, ending with rice on top.
Pour tomato soup over all.
Season with salt and pepper.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: finnish pancakes
directions: Melt butter in 8 x 8-inch pan.
Mix milk and eggs lightly with beater.
Add sugar.
Pour mixed batter over melted butter.
Bake in 450° oven for 20 to 23 minutes.

title: baked caramel corn
directions: Melt butter; stir in brown sugar, corn syrup and salt.
Bring to boil, stirring constantly.
Boil without stirring for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat; stir in soda and vanilla.
Pour over popped corn, mixing well.
Turn into two large shallow baking or roasting pans.
Bake in 250° oven for one hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Store in tightly covered container.

title: lemon dump salad
directions: In large bowl, pour condensed milk, lemon pie filling, pineapple, Cool Whip and marshmallows and stir.
Refrigerate.

title: eggplant parmigiana
directions: Cut eggplant into 1/4 to 1/2-inch slices. Sprinkle lightly with salt. Let drain for 30 minutes. Pat dry and sprinkle lightly with flour. Dip into beaten eggs. Mix bread crumbs with oregano. Dip slices in bread crumbs. Combine butter and oil in skillet and heat. Add eggplant slices and sprinkle with salt and pepper. Saute to a medium brown, about 5 minutes on each side.

title: chocolate souffle with vanilla sauce
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Grease six 5-ounce custard cups with vegetable oil.
In a small saucepan, cook orange juice and sugar over medium-high heat until mixture has a syrup consistency, then reserve.
In a large bowl, beat egg whites until stiff.
Pour syrup over the egg whites and continue beating for 2 minutes.
Add cocoa and liqueur and beat only until well mixed.
Pour into prepared custard cups.
Bake for 12 minutes or until puffed.
Do not overbake.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix together and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Cook sweet potatoes in skins; peel and mash.
Stir in both quantities of sugar, salt and water.
Add peanut butter, mixing thoroughly.
Place half of this mixture in baking dish and cover with crushed pineapple.
Add remaining potato mixture and bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Top with marshmallows for last 5 minutes of baking, if desired.

title: picante pizza
directions: Smooth softened cream cheese onto the bottom of a large cookie sheet.
Layer other ingredients in order given.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes or until everything bubbles.
Serve immediately with corn chips.

title: crunchy chicken casserole
directions: Lightly mix together chicken, celery, chestnuts, cheese and salt.
Blend mayonnaise and sour cream and toss with chicken mixture.
Turn 1/2 mixture into 1 1/2 quart casserole.
Top with 1/3 cup crushed crackers.
Top with remaining chicken and crackers.
Bake in a 375° oven for 15 to 20 minutes or until heated through.
Makes 6 servings.

title: a big kiss
directions: Grease funnel.
Place foil over bottom hole of funnel.
Invert funnel in a cup.
Melt chocolate in microwave on 50% power for 30 seconds at a time until melted.
Do not overcook.

title: zucchini parmesan
directions: Wash and trim off ends of zucchini. Cut lengthwise into 1/8-inch thick slices.
Heat olive oil in a large saucepan.
Add zucchini, onion and mushrooms. Cover saucepan and cook vegetables over low heat 10 to 15 minutes or until tender, stirring occasionally. Remove vegetable mixture from heat.
Stir in about half the cheese.
Combine the tomato paste, garlic, salt and pepper.
Pour into the vegetable mixture, blending lightly but thoroughly.
Turn mixture into a 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: orzo primavera
directions: Combine
water and salt in a large Dutch oven; bring to a boil.
Add
orzo and cook 5 minutes.
Add asparagus and cook 4 minutes.
Drain
and
set
mixture aside in a large serving bowl.

title: chicken deviled eggs
directions: Cut eggs lengthwise in half. Remove yolks and place in a small bowl.
Mash yolks with a fork. Add rest of ingredients.
Blend well. Stuff egg whites with yolk mixture. Sprinkle tops with paprika to garnish. Cover and refrigerate until serving time.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Cook chicken until tender; remove chicken and reserve broth. Cut chicken into cubes. Place in casserole dish. Add peas and carrots, soup, broth, salt and pepper.

title: chicken breasts
directions: Brown chicken in butter.
Stir in mushrooms, seasonings and soup. Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until tender. Remove chicken and stir in sour cream. Serve over rice or noodles.

title: perfect fried chicken
directions: In a paper bag, combine the flour and seasonings. Add a few chicken pieces at a time and shake.
Remove the chicken to a plate and let the coating dry. In a skillet, heat 1/2-inch of oil. Lightly brown the meaty sides of the chicken first.
Lightly brown the other side. Reduce the heat and cover. Simmer for 30 minutes. Uncover for the last 10 minutes.

title: popcorn cake
directions: Mix popped corn and salted nuts in a large bowl.
In a saucepan, melt butter and marshmallows; add oil.
Pour butter mixture over popped corn mixture.
Mix until the popcorn and nuts are well coated with the butter mixture.
Add the M&M's and mix well.
Press into a well-greased (Pam) tube pan.
Refrigerate for 1 hour. Turn out onto cake plate.

title: cream cheese cupcakes
directions: Beat cream cheese until smooth.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add sugar and vanilla and beat.
Fill muffin tin size paper cups to 1/8-inch from top.
Bake for 1 hour in 350° oven.
Remove from oven and cool.
An indentation made in the top of the cake is to be filled with your favorite filling.
Makes 12 cakes.

title: better than almost anything cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Bake cake as directed on pkg for 9 x 13 pan. Cool 15 minutes.

title: creamy chicken and broccoli bake
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Cook broccoli as directed on package. Drain. Grease oblong baking dish, 10 x 6 x 1 1/2-inch. Layer chicken and broccoli in dish. Mix soup and milk. Pour over broccoli and chicken. Arrange chicken slices on top of soup mixture. Mix Bisquick and margarine or butter until crumbly. Sprinkle over cheese. Bake until golden brown, 25 to 30 minutes.

title: mrs. biddle's key lime pie
directions: Combine milk and egg yolks; mix at low speed.
Slowly add juice, mixing until well blended.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.
Top with whipped cream.

title: turkey chili
directions: Saute onion, pepper and garlic in oil about 6 minutes; then add turkey and cook until browned.
Add to mixture and cook 1 minute the chili powder, cumin and oregano.
Next add green chilies, tomatoes, tomato paste, broth, beans and salt.
Simmer until serving time.
Best served on rice with grated cheese on top, if desired.

title: freezer pickles(do try these pickles.  delicious!)
directions: Cover cucumbers, onion and salt with water.
Allow to stand overnight in cool place.
Drain well and pack in freezer containers, allowing 1-inch at top.
Mix sugar, vinegar and celery seed thoroughly but do not cook.
Pour mixture over cucumbers. Cover and freeze.
They will be ready to use in a couple of weeks and will keep all winter.

title: eggplant parmesan
directions: Peel and slice eggplants.
Dip each slice in eggs or milk. After dipping in eggs, dip each slice in a mixture of bread crumbs, salt, oregano, flour and Parmesan cheese.
Fry the eggplant patties in oil, covered with a lid to steam cook.
Make sure they are cooked through, but not burnt.
Layer in a casserole:
tomato sauce, eggplant patties and Mozzarella cheese. Continue layering until patties are used up.
Top with sauce and cheese.
Heat thoroughly.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Press crescent rolls into pizza pan.
Bake as directed on package.
Mix remaining ingredients and spread on cooled crust. Top with favorite vegetables.

title: oatmeal cookies(diabetic)
directions: Mix all of the ingredients together with a spoon.
Form into circles on a sprayed cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes. Makes 10 cookies.

title: hardee's biscuits
directions: Sift together dry ingredients and mix in Crisco.
Add butter, milk and egg together.
Add to flour mixture.
Work fast and knead lightly.
Roll out and cut into biscuits.
(I like to drop mine in melted butter and place in pan.) Bake for 10 minutes at 400°.

title: cheese straws
directions: Cream the cheese and butter.
Mix dry ingredients and add cheese and butter.
Mix well and form into desired shape with cookie press.
Bake at 350° for about 8 minutes.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Place 1/3 of sliced zucchini and onion in casserole dish. Slice 1/3 of margarine on zucchini.
Place 1/3 of cheese on zucchini.
Place 1/3 of potato chips on cheese.
Alternate for 3 layers.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: pasta salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill thoroughly.
Serves 10 to 12.
Better when it stands overnight.

title: peanut butter bites
directions: Combine sugar and syrup in a medium saucepan; cook over medium heat until mixture comes to a boil, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; add peanut butter, stirring until smooth.
Stir in cereal.
Drop mixture by tablespoons onto wax paper; let cool completely.
Yields 3 dozen.

title: kristy's easy bake cookies
directions: Mix all well and bake at 325° for about 10 to 15 minutes until done.

title: pepper steak stir-fry
directions: Trim fat from beef.
Cut beef along grain into 2-inch strips. Cut strips across grain into 1/8-inch wide slices.
In bowl toss beef, 1 tablespoon vegetable oil, 1 teaspoon cornstarch, 1 teaspoon salt, 1 teaspoon soy sauce and 1/4 teaspoon white pepper. Refrigerate for 30 minutes.

title: debby's pizza crust
directions: Dissolve yeast in large mixing bowl with warm water.
Grease 2 cookie sheets.
Stir in sugar, salt and olive oil.
Beat in 2 cups flour until smooth.
Stir in 1 1/2 cups flour.
Set in a warm place to rise 45 minutes or double in size (you should cover with a damp towel).
Spread dough onto the greased cookie sheets (if dough is sticky, flour hands).
Spread pizza sauce over pizzas. Add ingredients and Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix altogether, then chill.

title: tacos
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Fry corn tortillas.
Put 2 to 3 tablespoons ground beef in tortilla while frying.
Fold tortilla in half and fry until hard.
Set on plate to drain grease.
Top with remaining ingredients.
Enjoy.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Boil noodles, then rinse in cold water.
Also boil frozen vegetables and rinse in cold water.
Put all in bowl.
Cut up tomatoes, celery and cucumbers.
Mix with noodles, then add salad dressing and chill 1 hour.

title: turkey cutlets
directions: Slice turkey breast very thin.
Mix a ratio of 2 eggs to 1/4 cup of water.
Dip each slice of turkey in flour, then egg/water mix, then bread crumbs and fry in about 1/4 inch of hot oil until golden brown.

title: squash dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Using 9 x 13-inch pan, spread crumbled, cooked sausage and cubed bread.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over sausage and bread cubes.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: baked beans
directions: Soak beans overnight.
Next morning, put on stove in cold water and bring to boil.
Blanch, then put on in boiling water with generous piece of butter and boil until soft.
Remove from fire and add 2 tablespoons molasses and ketchup.
Put in casserole and cover with slices of bacon.
Top with 3 tablespoons brown sugar.
Bake, covered, at 250° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
If too much liquid, pour some in cup and add to beans when half done.

title: rice krispy chicken
directions: Place cereal in a large bowl.
Melt margarine or butter.
Dip chicken into butter and then into crushed cereal.
Put on a cookie sheet line with aluminum foil.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Bake at 350 for 50-60 minutes.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Layer in dish, probably an 8 x 14-inch.

title: rich and chocolate brownies
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, flour, butter and salt in large bowl.
Add vanilla and melted chocolate.
Pour in greased 8 or 9-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle chocolate chips and nuts on top.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Don't overbake!

title: baked beans doctored
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: dried beef dip
directions: Combine all ingredients in bowl.
Mix well.
Chill in refrigerator.
Serve with chips.

title: hot fruit casserole
directions: Layer fruit in casserole dish with apple rings on top.
Cook other ingredients until creamy and pour over fruit.
Let sit in refrigerator overnight.
Next day, bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mountain pie *
directions: Melt butter in a deep, good-sized baking dish.
Mix dry ingredients; add milk, mix into a batter and pour into the melted butter without stirring.
Add 3/4 cup sugar to a can of sour cherries and pour the cherries and juice into the middle of batter.
Do not stir.
Bake at 375° for about an hour.
Serve with whipped cream, topped with a cherry.

title: braunschweiger ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together and serve at room temperature or chilled.
Roll in pecans, if desired.

title: blueberry coffee cake
directions: Beat butter and sugar. Add eggs and then flour with baking powder. Spread into 9 x 13 inch greased pan.

title: northern bannock bread
directions: Mix ingredients
with a few tablespoons of water.
Form into a loaf in the
bottom
of
a	Dutch
oven and bake for 30 minutes.

title: pineapple cheesecake pie
directions: Beat cheese until smooth. Gradually beat in sugar.
Blend in sour cream and vanilla.
Fold in whipped topping, blending well. Spoon into crust. Chill until set, at least 4 hours. Spoon 1 can (8 ounce) crushed pineapple, drained, in center of filling.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Stir in remaining ingredients and heat through.
Serve on hamburger buns.

title: brown sugar
directions: Mix together.
Yields 1 cup brown sugar.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Core green tomatoes.
Cut into 3/8 inch thick slices.
Mix flour, sugar, salt and pepper.
Coat tomatoes with mixture and let sit 15 minutes.
In a cast-iron skillet, heat 1/2 inch oil and bacon grease over medium heat.
Lightly re-coat tomatoes with flour mixture; brown on both sides for 3 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: cajun chicken and tasso jambalaya
directions: Cook rice according to package directions and set aside.
In a 3-quart saucepan, cook onion, celery, green pepper and garlic in butter or margarine until tender.
Stir in undrained tomatoes, tomato paste, tasso or sausage and seasoning.
Bring to boiling. Reduce heat, cover and simmer 30 minutes. Stir in chicken and hot pepper sauce.
Simmer, covered, about 15 minutes more or until chicken is tender.
Stir in rice. Cook, stirring occasionally, until heated through.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Cook syrup to soft ball stage.
Pour over popcorn.
Wet or butter hands and shape into balls.

title: kenny's spaghetti sauce
directions: Fry hamburger and onion together.
Cook tomato sauce in crock-pot.
Add all the rest of the ingredients.
Simmer on low all day.
Cook spaghetti and eat.

title: chicken-pasta salad
directions: Cook macaroni as directed on package, except add pea pods about 2 minutes before macaroni is done; drain.
Rinse macaroni and pea pods with cold water; drain.
Mix mayonnaise and French dressing in large bowl.
Add macaroni mixture and remaining ingredients; toss. Yields 4 servings.

title: self-filled cupcakes
directions: Batter:
Follow directions for devil's food cake.

title: caramel sweet rolls
directions: Place rolls in greased tube pan.
Sprinkle with pudding.
Mix butter, sugar and cinnamon.
Cook slightly and pour over rolls. Add nuts, if desired.
Put in oven overnight.

title: mother's hot rolls
directions: In 1/2 cup warm water, add yeast and 1 teaspoon sugar.
Set aside.
In bowl, put 1 cup boiling water, 3 rounded tablespoons shortening and 1/2 cup sugar.
Dissolve and then add 1 cup cold water.
Add yeast mixture and 1 tablespoon of salt.
Add 5 or more cups flour and stir good.
By hand, knead, but leave soft (just enough to work in flour).
Grease bowl; put in dough.
Let sit overnight in refrigerator or several hours.
Form into rolls and bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Stays in refrigerator well for several days.

title: raw vegetable dip
directions: Mix ingredients together and chill overnight.

title: chocolate nut bars
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine crumbs and margarine; press firmly on bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake 8 minutes. Reduce oven temperature to 350°.

title: jellied salad supreme
directions: Dissolve raspberry jello in 1 cup boiling water.
Stir in the pie filling.
Chill until firm in 9 x 9-inch pan.
Dissolve lemon jello in 1 cup boiling water.
Cool.
Beat cheese and mayonnaise until well blended.
Gradually add lemon jello.
Stir in pineapple and marshmallows.
Chill until partially set.
Fold in whipped Dream Whip.
Spoon this over cherry layer.
Top with the nuts and chill.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Cook the broccoli as suggested on box and put in the bottom of casserole dish.
Pull chicken off the bones and place on top of the broccoli.
Mix remaining ingredients and spread on top.
Put bread crumbs on top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pecan fingers
directions: Mix shortening and confectioners sugar thoroughly.
Stir in flour and press evenly into ungreased oblong pan and bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: bobbi's lima bean casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cook beans according to package.
Drain. Soak bread in milk.
In separate bowl, mix salt, egg and finely chopped garlic.
Squeeze extra milk out of bread.
Mix with meat and egg mixture with fork gently.
Shape into walnut size meatballs.
Fry in 1 tablespoon butter until browned.
Transfer to bottom of casserole dish.
Pour water into skillet.
Stir and pour over meatballs.
Season beans with salt, pepper and butter. Pour over meatballs.
Bake 30 minutes.
Spoon sour cream over casserole.
Bake another 5 minutes.
Sprinkle top with paprika.

title: cold oven pound cake
directions: Have all ingredients at room temperature.
With electric mixer, beat sugar, margarine and Crisco for 3 minutes; add 3 tablespoons of the flour and beat one more minute.
Add eggs one at a time; beat after each egg.
Alternate milk and flour with flour last.
Add lemon and vanilla; beat 5 minutes more.
Pour in a greased tube pan.
Cook for 1 hour and 30 minutes in a 325° oven.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add beaten eggs.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Mix in rest of ingredients.
Bake at 325° until done.

title: bob's biscuits
directions: Blend
together
dry
ingredients.
Cut
in
shortening until mix
resembles a fine meal.
Make a well in center, pour in buttermilk	and stir until well blended.
Knead lightly on floured board
until
light and tender, about 1 minute.
Roll 1/2-inch thick;
cut into biscuits.	Bake in hot oven, 425° to 450°, for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.

title: fruit cobbler(microwave)
directions: Combine 2 tablespoons brown sugar and 1 tablespoon flour in a microwave-safe casserole.
Mix well.
Add apples and strawberries. Mix well.
Microwave on High 5 to 7 minutes, or until heated. Combine oats, remaining brown sugar, flour and cinnamon in medium bowl.
Mix. Stir in butter or margarine until crumbly.
Spread crumb mixture over fruit.
Microwave on High 4 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Serve plain or with ice cream or yogurt.
Serves 6.

title: oven baked rice
directions: Heat
oven to 375°.
In ovenproof skillet over moderate heat, saute onion in oil until golden brown.
Add celery, salt and pepper.
Cook
more minutes, stirring constantly.
Add rice and stir until coated with oil.
Stir in stock and bring to boil. Cover and place in oven; bake 17 minutes.

title: split pea casserole
directions: Simmer split peas in 1 quart water for 1/2 to 3/4 hour, until tender.
Drain.
Make Sloppy Joe by frying together hamburger and onion.
Add salt and other seasonings.
Mix in whole tomatoes. Add carrots, celery and drained peas.
Mix all together.
Bake in a covered casserole dish at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Bake cake according to directions on box.
Cool. Crumble into pieces and put in bottom of large bowl.
Cook pudding according to directions on box.
Cool.
Add chocolate chips to pudding.
Layer cake, pudding, Cool Whip and Heath bars; repeat layers.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Chop artichokes into very small pieces and mix all ingredients together.
Add garlic powder, lemon pepper and onion flakes to taste.
Pour into non-stick sprayed casserole. Spread 1/4 cup melted butter or margarine on top, then sprinkle with grated Parmesan cheese.
Bake in 375° oven until cheese is melted and top is brown.

title: pasta delight
directions: Cook and stir zucchini in hot oil in large skillet over medium-high heat.
Reduce heat to medium.
Add shallots and garlic; cook 1 minute.
Add tomato; cook and stir 45 seconds.
Add basil and cheese.
Pour vegetable mix over penne in bowl; toss gently to mix.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: divinity candy
directions: Cook sugar, Karo, water and salt until forms hard ball in cold water and will crack on side of a cup.
Pour over egg whites which have been beaten stiff.
Add vanilla and beat in mixer until loses its shine and will hold its shape when dropped on waxed paper.

title: boston-style baked corn
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine mustard, salt, sugar and catsup in medium bowl.
Add onion and corn; mix thoroughly.
Pour into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with bacon.
Bake for 40 minutes, or until bacon is cooked.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: christmas punch
directions: Mix ingredients. Add 2 qt chilled ginger ale before serving. Top with pineapple sherbet.

title: barbecue chicken or pork
directions: Pour barbecue sauce mixture over chicken or pork in microwave baking dish.
Cover with lid or plastic wrap, turning one corner up to let steam escape.
Bake at High power for 25 minutes or until tender.
Serves 4.

title: underdones
directions: Mix in given order and bake about 20 to 25 minutes in 325° oven.
Bake in a square greased pan.
Allow to cool in pan.
Cut in squares and sprinkle with 4 tablespoons powdered sugar.

title: florentine crescents
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a saucepan; cook on low until cheese melts (will be very dry at first).
Unroll and separate rolls; cut to make 32 triangles.
Spread each with 1 teaspoon of mixture and roll up.
Place on a greased cookie sheet and bake at 375° for 11 to 13 minutes or until golden brown.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Cut up margarine in bottom of cooking pan.
Pour juice off of 1 can of peaches and spread all of peaches over the margarine in pan.

title: pickled peaches
directions: Bring all ingredients except the peaches to a boil.
When it reaches boiling stage, add peeled cling peaches.
Boil about 15 minutes or until peaches look clear.
Pack hot peaches in sterilized jars; cover with the syrup and seal.
They look real pretty if you put some of the spices in the jars.

title: pumpkin chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, vanilla, pumpkin, spices, baking soda and baking powder and mix together.
Add flour, chips and nuts (if using).

title: shrimp velvet
directions: Saute shrimp and Cajun spice in butter until plump and tender. Add heavy cream and all cheese. Simmer until thick and creamy. Serve over hot pasta.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Blend zucchini and onions together.
Sprinkle salt over mixture and let set overnight.
Drain and rinse twice.
Stir together the sugar, vinegar, mustard, turmeric, cornstarch, nutmeg and celery seed.
Heat until it boils.
Add zucchini and onions. Heat again until it boils about 30 minutes.
Makes 6 pints.

title: tortellini salad
directions: Follow directions on package of frozen tortellini.
Mix all ingredients together and then add your choice of dressing and mix again.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Place pineapple in bottom of large dish. Mix sugar, flour and cheese. Sprinkle over pineapple. Mix crumbled crackers with margarine. Sprinkle on top. Bake at 350° about 25 minutes.

title: delicious rice
directions: Mix all together.
Bake, covered, for 1 hour at 400°.

title: fruit cake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Grease well 2 (4 1/2 x 8-inch) or 5 smaller baking pans with vegetable shortening.
In large bowl mix fruit, nuts and orange juice.
Let set while preparing rest of ingredients.
Beat together eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Mix flour, baking powder and stir into fruit mixture.
Then stir in egg, sugar and vanilla mixture.
Bake for 1 hour.
If it browns too fast, cover with foil last 20 minutes.
Smaller aluminum pans do not take as long.
Test with toothpick.

title: blueberry torte
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff, then add sugar.
Mix well.
Add saltines, pecans and vanilla.
Pour into a buttered baking dish. Bake at 350° until light brown.
Let cool.

title: lemon nut cake
directions: Mix together pecans, cherries, pineapple and flour; set aside.
Cream together butter, sugar and salt. Add eggs, one at a time. Add flour and lemon extract. Add the nut and fruit mixture. Pour in greased and floured tube pan. Bake 2 hours at 300°.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spread cranberries in 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Pour sugar over cranberries.
Cover tightly with foil.
Bake for 1 hour.

title: spinach balls or casserole
directions: Cook spinach; drain thoroughly, being sure no water is left. Mix all other ingredients, then add spinach.

title: cottage cheese spread
directions: Combine all ingredients in a small bowl; cover and refrigerate until chilled.
Makes 1 cup.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise, sugar, vinegar and salt.
Pour over broccoli, onion and cheese.
Toss and refrigerate.
Add bacon just before serving.

title: broccoli-cheddar scalloped potatoes
directions: In a skillet over medium heat, melt margarine and cook onion until tender. Stir in soup, milk and pepper.
Heat to boiling. Add potatoes.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover, simmer 5 minutes or until hot and bubbling, stirring occasionally.
Makes 4 servings. (For cheesier flavor, add 1/2 cup shredded Cheddar cheese with soup.)

title: swiss tuna quiche
directions: Pierce pastry shell thoroughly with fork.
Bake in 375° oven for 10 minutes; remove.

title: cheese chorizo dip
directions: Spread chorizo between paper towels on microwave-proof plate. Microwave on High until brown and crisp, 3 minutes.
Mix chorizo, cheese and chilies in bowl.
Transfer to shallow 3 cup microwave-proof serving dish.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Turn back a corner to vent.
Microwave on medium until cheese is thoroughly melted, 6 to 8 minutes.
Stir quickly.
Serve warm with tortilla chips.

title: one step lasagne
directions: Combine water, sauce and hamburger.
Spread enough to cover bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan (about 1 3/4 cups).
Arrange layers of uncooked noodles, slightly overlapping, on top of sauce, spread 1/2 of cottage cheese and Mozzarella cheese over noodles. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Add another layer of noodles, sauce, etc.
Cover tightly with foil.
Refrigerate overnight or 8 hours.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: original m & m cookies
directions: In a large bowl, mix together shortening, brown sugar and sugar. Beat in vanilla and eggs. Add flour, soda and salt. Mix well. Add M & M's.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix crushed pretzels, melted margarine and 3 tablespoons sugar in 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Bake 8 minutes at 400°.
Cool.

title: delicious fruit salad
directions: In large glass bowl, mix pie filling, fresh sliced strawberries, bananas, pineapple and white grapes.
Chill.

title: kraut salad
directions: Wash and drain kraut in colander.
Mix other ingredients, then add oil and sugar.
Marinate overnight before eating.
Will keep a month in refrigerator.

title: quick "n" easy chicken in wine(low-fat)
directions: Brown chicken in oil. Drain off oil. Add all remaining ingredients to skillet. Cover and simmer over low heat for 30 minutes or until chicken is done. Add water, if necessary. Remove cover and continue cooking until most of the liquid has evaporated and mixture is thickened.

title: diabetic barbecue sauce(low calorie)
directions: In small saucepan, combine first 8 ingredients and simmer, uncovered, for 10 minutes.
Stir every 2 or 3 minutes.
Remove from stove; add sugar substitute and mix well.
This will keep in refrigerator several weeks.
This recipe makes 8 (2 tablespoon) servings.
Each serving is 32 calories, 1/2 vegetable and fat exchange.
Use for chicken or any kind of meat.

title: old fashioned tea cakes
directions: Cream together sugar, margarine, oil and eggs.
Mix in dry ingredients, then the vanilla.
Chill mixture in refrigerator for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: pasta sauce
directions: Saut sausage, onion, garlic, carrot and celery. Add bouillon and pepper strips and cook until tender. Add tomatoes and simmer until hot. Serve over linguini and top with fresh Parmesan.

title: chicken noodle soup
directions: In 3-quart saucepan, combine chicken broth, water, celery, carrot, onion, parsley, poultry seasoning and thyme.
Over medium heat, heat to boiling, stirring occasionally.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Mix peanuts, sugar, syrup and salt in a glass bowl.
Microwave on High for 7 to 8 minutes until bubbly.
Gently stir in butter and vanilla and cook 2 to 3 minutes more.
Add soda, stir well and pour immediately (have pan buttered before beginning candy) onto buttered cookie sheet.
Let cook 15 minutes or so.
Break in pieces.
Store in airtight container.

title: ham-cheese ball
directions: This is usually doubled to make a larger Ham Ball.
May substitute green onions for minced onions.

title: haitian fruit salad dressing
directions: Mix thoroughly and serve over fresh fruit salad.

title: chinese salad
directions: Combine salad.
Mix dressing and shake well to let flavors blend.
Toss greens and noodles with dressing just before serving. Add almond and sesame seed and mix lightly.

title: manicotti
directions: Follow directions on box of manicotti noodles.
While noodles cook, mix all other ingredients except pepperoni.
When noodles are done, drain off hot water and rinse with cool water.
Fill shells with cheese mixture.
Put filled shells in 9 x 13-inch pan. Pour spaghetti sauce over noodles.
Top with pepperoni slices. Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: bread stick appetizers
directions: Sprinkle cheese on flat dish.
Lay bacon strips on cheese. Wrap bacon around bread sticks, cheese side in.
Bake on top of paper towel for 4 1/2 to 6 minutes in microwave for 10 sticks. Then roll in cheese again.
Serve hot.

title: easy chicken pot pie
directions: Place bottom crust in large pie plate.
Place cubed chicken in crust.
Cook soup as directed.
Let cool about 10 minutes.
Pour soup over chicken.
Top with frozen vegetables.
Cover with top crust.
Make slits in crust for steam.
Top with 2 pats margarine. Bake in 325° oven on cookie sheet, in case of overflow, for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: hot dog meat loaf or mock ham loaf
directions: Mix and shape into loaf.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: ham salad
directions: Mix well. Best if made and refrigerated for several hours.

title: squash patties
directions: Combine squash, pepper, sugar, salt and flour.
Beat eggs. Add to mix along with butter and onion.
Drop by tablespoon into skillet containing oil, over medium heat.
Fry until golden brown.

title: chicken delicious
directions: Mix bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese, parsley, salt and pepper together.
Mix garlic and melted butter.
Dip the chicken breasts in the butter and garlic, then in the dry mixture.
Place in 8 x 10-inch glass baking dish, skin side up and bake about 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Bake until golden brown; do not turn.

title: strawberry jello dessert
directions: Make Jell-O first with 2 cups of hot water; set aside. Prepare 2 packages of Dream Whip according to box directions; set aside.
Thaw frozen strawberry slices, but not completely.

title: economy punch
directions: For use in punch bowl.
Freeze some in a ring with the sliced lemons and limes.

title: jello rolls
directions: Mix flour, yeast and 1 cup sugar together.
Add warm water until dough is firm.
Let rise 2 times.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Shred Cheddar cheese.
Combine dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening.
Stir in cheese and add buttermilk.
Stir until dough clings together.
Knead dough lightly and roll into 12-inch circle.
Cut into 8 wedges.
Begin at wide end of wedge and roll toward point.
Place biscuit (point side down) on a greased baking sheet and bake at 450° for 12 to 14 minutes.
Yields 8 biscuits.

title: plymouth rock holiday mold
directions: In small bowl, dissolve lemon gelatin in 1 cup boiling water. Stir in 3/4 cup cold water.
Chill until thickened.
Spoon 1/4 cup gelatin in bottom of 4-cup ring mold.
Arrange apple slices and pecans in gelatin.
Carefully spoon remaining lemon gelatin over fruit and nuts.
Set aside.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cut a thin slice from the stem end of each pepper.
Wash outside and inside.
Remove all seed and membranes. Cook peppers in boiling salted water 5 minutes.
Drain.
Mix rest of ingredients.
Stuff peppers lightly with meat mixture.
Stand upright in small baking dish.
Bake covered 45 minutes.
Uncover and bake 15 minutes longer.
I top with a slice of cheese after baking.

title: loaf pot roast a la ina
directions: Mix together well the first 7 ingredients. Shape into a loaf. Brown on all sides in melted shortening in a frying pan.
Place in a Dutch oven or large pot.
Mix liquids and pour over meat. Cook over moderate heat for 1/2 hour. Add carrots and green pepper. Cook another 1/2 hour. Serve hot with rice or mashed potatoes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: easy homemade ice cream with oreos
directions: In a large bowl, beat yolks.
Stir in milk, water and vanilla. Mix well, then fold in cookies and whipped cream.
Pour into aluminum foil-lined 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Cover and freeze for 6 hours.

title: surprise casserole
directions: Mix taco seasoning into ground meat as directed on package. Butter casserole dish. Pour corn into dish.
Crumble meat over top of corn. Mix potatoes with sour cream; pour over meat evenly. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes. Sprinkle cheese over top. Let melt and serve.

title: mixed greens and fennel with ginger dressing
directions: Blend first 7 dressing ingredients in food processor. With machine running, gradually add oil and process until well blended. (Can be prepared 1 day ahead. Cover and refrigerate. Let stand 30 minutes at room temperature before using.) Toss fennel and greens with dressing. Enjoy!

title: cranberry pie
directions: Prepare Jello using 1 c. boiling water and stirring until dissolved.
Add cold water and refrigerate until mixture begins to thicken, about 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Soften cream cheese with milk and spread into baked pie shell.
After Jello has begun to thicken, whip until fluffy.
Stir whole cranberry sauce to break apart and fold into Jello mixture.
Pour into cream cheese lined pastry shell and refrigerate until set.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: peach smoothie
directions: Place into smoothie maker in order listed.
Blend on low 1 minute and high until smooth.

title: baked chicken
directions: Melt margarine in pan.
Roll chicken in flour, sesame seed, salt and pepper.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Take out of oven and turn.
Drain pineapple and add green peppers, chopped onion, olives, chunk pineapple and shrimp.
Mix pineapple juice, soup and chili sauce and pour over chicken.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
The temperature may be lowered after this time and the chicken can be left in the oven for 3/4 to 1 hour.

title: beef stew
directions: Place meat in a medium roaster.
Add both soup mixes.
Add enough water to almost cover meat.
Cover with roaster lid and cook in a 350° oven for 3 to 4 hours, depending on size and tenderness of meat.

title: crabmeat casserole
directions: Melt butter, stir in flour.
Add milk and seasoning.
Add rest of ingredients.
Put in greased quart dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, uncovered.

title: dried beef spread
directions: Combine all ingredients.
May be served with rye bread, crackers or chips.
Chill overnight.

title: hamburger stuffed zucchini
directions: Cut zucchini in half lengthwise.
Scoop out seeds and discard. Scoop out as much squash pulp as possible without destroying zucchini shell.
Set aside.
Brown hamburger, onion and green or red pepper; add squash pulp, cover and cook until squash is soft. Season with salt, pepper and garlic salt.
Remove from heat.
Stir in egg, cracker crumbs, 1/4 cup cheese and enough tomato sauce to moisten.
Season squash shells with salt and pepper.
Place in shallow baking pan; spoon filling into squash halves.
Spoon a small amount of tomato sauce on top and pour remaining sauce around halves.
Cover and bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Remove cover and top with remaining cheese.
Bake an additional 15 minutes or until squash is tender and top is toasted.

title: golden westerner cake
directions: Have butter and eggs at room temperature.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Place all ingredients in a crock pot and stir well. Simmer for several hours. Serve over hot spaghetti.

title: curry dip
directions: Blend well and chill.
Serve with carrot strips, celery sticks, cucumber sticks, etc.

title: award winning spaghetti sauce
directions: In a saucepan, saute onion, pepper and garlic in cooking oil. Stir in basil, oregano and crushed tomatoes and tomato paste. Bring to a boil.
Add remaining ingredients.
Reduce heat and simmer about 20 minutes.

title: sweet potato and sausage stuffing
directions: Cook sausage until half done, breaking into small pieces.
Add onion, celery and seasonings.
Continue to cook until done.
Drain off fat.
Combine sausage mixture with crumbs and potatoes; mix well.

title: delicious cheesecake
directions: Cream together well all
ingredients.
Pour into graham cracker pie crust.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until set. Spread favorite pie filling on top.

title: corn-sausage casserole
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients; pour into greased, deep 8-inch casserole.
Spread catsup over top; place in pan of water 1-inch deep.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Yields 6 servings.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until tender. Mix all ingredients in bowl; add some broth if dry. Pour into greased casserole dish. Sprinkle with cracker crumbs and place thin pats of butter on top. Bake at 350° until bubbly brown.

title: mock apple pie
directions: Boil 2 minutes, then add 25 Ritz crackers (regular size and unbroken).
Boil 2 more minutes.
Add nutmeg or cinnamon or both, if desired.
Put in unbaked pie shell; dot with butter.
Put lattice top on pie.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.

title: hot corn casserole
directions: Saute onion in small amount of margarine.
Add onion soup and Ro-Tel; stir well and add corn.
Simmer about 5 minutes; add pinch of sugar.
Then put in casserole dish and top with cheese.	Cook for 20 to 25 minutes at 300°.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: broccoli corn casserole
directions: In a bowl, combine broccoli, corn and egg. Transfer to a greased 1 qt. baking dish. Sprinkle with stuffing mix and drizzle with butter. Bake uncovered at 350° for 30 to
35 minutes or until golden brown and bubbly.

title: flip-top deviled eggs
directions: Peel eggs.
Cut slice from wide end of each egg.
Carefully remove yolks and mash.
Mix yolks with deviled ham and remaining ingredients.
Refill whites and replace "lid".
Makes 6 eggs.

title: fire and ice tomatoes
directions: Combine tomatoes, green pepper and onion rings in medium bowl. In small saucepan, combine remaining ingredients except cucumber slices; bring to boil 1 minute.
Pour hot mixture over vegetables in bowl.
Let stand at room temperature until cool.
Add cucumbers.
Refrigerate several hours, stirring once or twice until well chilled.
Drain before serving.
Serves 6 to 8.
Serve as salad or relish dish.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Place vegetables and broth in saucepan.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat, cover and cook until vegetables are tender.
Mix milk, flour and salt; add to cooked vegetables.
Cook, stirring constantly until soup is lightly thickened.
Remove from heat.
Add cheese and stir until melted.

title: corn sauce
directions: Cut the corn off the cob and scrape the cob.
Mix all the ingredients except sugar and cook about 15 minutes in a pot, then add sugar and cook until tender.
Put into sterilized jars and seal.

title: teriyaki catfish
directions: Melt margarine.
Mix with teriyaki sauce and garlic powder. Pour over catfish and let marinate for at least 30 minutes.
Grill until tender.

title: garlic chicken
directions: Combine seasonings with soft butter and lemon juice.
Spread over chicken.
Bake skin side up without turning for 1 to 1 1/4 hours at 350°.
Serves 6.

title: creamy dijon sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in 1-cup glass measure.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Cook at 50 (Medium heat) 2 to 3 minutes.
Serve with meat, spread on sandwiches or stir into your favorite casserole.

title: chicken breasts with vegetables(and wine cream sauce)
directions: Cut vegetables into
very
small
cubes.
Cook in frypan with butter and salt
for
minutes until tender.
Rub breast with lemon juice and
salt.
Roll
them in butter and vegetable mixture.
Place all in casserole dish and cover with a buttered piece of waxed paper.
Place in a 400° oven for 6 to 12 minutes or until done.
Place on warm platter while making sauce.

title: beef stew mix(serves 4)
directions: Melt butter in 2-quart casserole in oven.
Mix all other ingredients except stew.
Pour mixture over melted butter.
Spoon stew over batter.
Do not stir!!!
Bake in 350° oven for 60 to 65 minutes or until crust is raised and brown.

title: peanut squares
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
This makes a stiff batter. Press on cookie sheet or large cake pan.

title: chinese crunch
directions: Add sugar to beaten eggs and mix well. Add flour and baking powder. Mix well.
Add dates, walnuts and vanilla.
Mix well. Pour into greased 9-inch pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes until brown. Cool and cut in squares.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 10-inch tube baking pan (or three 8 x 4-inch loaf pans) with unsalted shortening and dust lightly with flour.
In a medium-sized bowl sift together flour, baking powder, baking soda, nutmeg, cloves, cinnamon and salt.
In a large mixing bowl place sugar, oil and eggs; stir until well blended.
Stir pumpkin into egg mixture.
Gradually add sifted dry ingredients to egg mixture, stirring well after each addition. Fold raisins and nuts into batter.
Pour batter into prepared pan(s) and bake 1 hour and 15 to 20 minutes for single pan or 1 hour for small loaf pans until a cake tester inserted into center comes out clean.
Remove bread from oven and cool on a wire cake rack for 10 minutes before removing from pan.
Then cool completely on a rack.

title: casserole sauce mix
directions: Combine ingredients; mix well.
Store in airtight container. When ready to use, combine 1/3 cup of mix with 1 1/2 cups of water in a saucepan.
Cook and stir until thickened.

title: no peek stew
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Place meat in a 13 x 9-inch pan (lightly greased).
In a bowl, combine mushroom soup, soup mix, ginger ale, mushrooms, Worcestershire sauce and ginger.
Mix well.
Pour over meat.
Cover pan with foil.
Bake in preheated oven for 3 hours. No peeking.
Place pan on burner.
Uncover.
Stir cornstarch in water.
Heat and stir to thicken pieces.
Stir in sour cream. Serve with noodles or mashed potatoes.

title: grilled salmon with soy ginger
directions: For marinade, put soy sauce, sesame oil, ginger, sherry, vinegar, chili powder, cayenne pepper and garlic in a small bowl and mix.

title: blackberry pie
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients; beat 5 minutes at medium speed or until smooth.
Fold in blackberries.
Pour filling into pastry shell; bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: zagreb pork chops
directions: Mix dressing, onion soup mix, chopped up garlic and apricot preserves. Pour mixture over salted and peppered pork chops. Use a greased 9-inch Corning Ware dish. Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour at 375°. Serve over rice or egg noodles.

title: cheesy-bacon potatoes
directions: Wash and dry potatoes.
Pierce with a fork and bake at 425° for 50 to 60 minutes or until tender.
Meanwhile, saute bacon in a skillet.
Cool and crumble.
In 2 tablespoons of bacon drippings, saute onion and green pepper, adding mushrooms, until cooked.
Set aside.

title: strawberry limeade
directions: Put all ingredients except ice in blender.
Cover and blend until smooth.
While blender is running, add 1 ice cube at a time through center opening in cover.

title: kahlua dip
directions: Add pudding mix and milk to make a paste.
Fold in a medium-size Cool Whip a little at a time.
Then fold in Kahlua. Dip with fresh pineapple, bananas, tart apples, fresh strawberries or any other fruit you choose.

title: easy banana pie
directions: Slice bananas onto crust.
Gradually add 1/2 cup milk to softened cream cheese.
Mix well.
Add pudding; mix and add remaining milk.
Beat slowly one minute.
Pour into crust.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cut up squash.
Chop onion.
Cook until tender.
Mash mixture. Add remaining ingredients.
Top with additional grated cheese and bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: potato ham casserole
directions: In a large bowl, combine first 5 ingredients and mix well. Stir in ham and thawed potatoes.
Spread into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish.
Combine the last two ingredients (margarine and corn flakes) and sprinkle on top.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour or until potatoes are tender.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: whiskey sour slush
directions: Bring the water and sugar to a boil; let simmer 15 minutes. Add remaining ingredients to sugar and water.
Put in plastic pretzel container and let freeze at least 24 hours.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix softened cheese and sour cream with electric mixer on medium.
Mix in taco seasoning.
Spread in bottom of pie plate. Put cut-up tomato, olives and lettuce.
Top off with Cheddar cheese.
Refrigerate.
Dip with nacho chips.

title: granny's tea cakes
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a large bowl.
Beat for 3 minutes.
Mix flour, soda and salt in separate bowl.
Gradually add to mixture in large bowl alternately with milk.
Mix well. Drop by tablespoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Cook at 350° for approximately 10 minutes or until lightly golden brown around edges.

title: fruit cups
directions: Chop fruit and nuts.
Mix all ingredients.
Line small muffin tins.
Pour mixture into muffin tins and bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: fish slaw or barbecue
directions: Mix and store in refrigerator.
Will keep well for at least 4 weeks.

title: scotch short bread
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Sift flour, cornstarch and salt into medium-size bowl; set aside.
In large bowl, cream butter and superfine sugar until light and fluffy.
With wooden spoon, gradually work in dry ingredients until thoroughly mixed.
Press dough into an ungreased 11 x 7-inch or 9-inch square baking pan. Prick deeply all over with a fork.
Score surface for serving size. Bake about 40 minutes or until light brown.
Sprinkle with granulated sugar.
Cool and cut.
Yields 20 (1 1/2 x 2-inches).

title: apple roll
directions: Roll crust 1/2 inch thick. spread with finely diced apples. Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Roll up and cut 1 1/2-inches wide.
Place in baking dish and pour over a syrup of 2 Cups Water and 2 Cups Sugar.
Bake at 350 for 1 hour.

title: vidalia onion pie
directions: Saute onions in melted margarine until almost tender.
Pour into pie crust.
Mix eggs, salt, pepper, milk and 1/2 cup cheese. Pour over onions and lightly stir.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes. Remove from oven and top with rest of cheese and paprika.
Return to oven and bake 8 to 10 minutes.

title: corn salad
directions: Put all in a big bowl.

title: marinated cucumbers
directions: Combine all ingredients. Cover lightly. Keeps well in refrigerator for weeks.

title: marble squares
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour batter in pan. Sprinkle 1 cup chocolate chips on top.
Melt one minute, then cut through with knife to make swirls.
Bake 14 minutes at 350°.

title: boiled molasses cookies
directions: Boil molasses over heat for 1 minute.
Remove from stove and in same pan add baking soda, margarine or shortening, sugar, salt, cinnamon, ginger, vanilla, beaten eggs and vinegar.
Stir in flour and mix well.
Roll into balls, place on a greased cookie sheet. Press down with a fork.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: blue cheese dip
directions: Mix well; marinate in refrigerator.
Serve with cucumber slices, bell pepper strips, carrot stick, cauliflower and other fresh vegetable dippers.

title: best smokey beef brisket
directions: Sprinkle the brisket with the liquid smoke, salt and pepper. Wrap in foil and put in refrigerator overnight.
When ready to cook, add the celery salt, garlic powder, onion salt, paprika, nutmeg and brown sugar.
Rewrap and bake 1 hour at 300°.
Loosen foil and cook 5 to 6 hours at 200°.
Cool and slice across the grain.
Mix 1 cup of the brisket juice and barbecue sauce.
Pour over slices and put back in oven to reheat, with foil covering the meat.

title: spoon burgers
directions: Brown beef, onion and peppers.
Add the remaining ingredients and simmer 10 minutes.
Serve on fresh hamburger buns.

title: pat's mexican wedding cake
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients together.
Pour into ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes, until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool completely before frosting.

title: easy double peanut clusters
directions: Melt chips and
shortening in double boiler in hot, not boiling water.
Stir in peanuts.
Drop by tablespoons onto wax paper.
Cook until set.

title: fruit pie
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs well beaten.
Add raisins, pecans and coconut, mixing well.
Add vanilla and vinegar.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 325° for about 45 minutes.

title: mexican turkey
directions: Put all ingredients in crock-pot and cook 10 to 12 hours. Shred and use in tacos.

title: gelato - italian ice cream
directions: Mix together water, sugar and salt in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil and cook over medium heat for 5 minutes.
Add the lemon juice and rind to sugar mixture; let cool.
Beat the egg whites until stiff and fold into the cooled lemon mixture.
Pour into freezer trays, cover with plastic wrap and freeze until firm.
Stir occasionally.

title: mayonnaise devil's food cake
directions: Blend mayonnaise and sugar together.
Add flour, soda, cocoa and water to blended mixture.
Stir into batter.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Makes 1 cake.

title: chicken delight
directions: Brown chicken in large pot.
Put tomato sauce, Ranch Style beans, crushed chips and spices in pot.
Be sure chicken is cooked before putting ingredients in.
When chips are moistened, sprinkle cheese and mix in with chicken mixture.
When cheese is melted, remove from stove.
Serve with Spanish rice and green salad.

title: meat dressing
directions: Add water to broth of ham.
Add onion.
Cook with broth until onion is tender.
Add cornmeal a little at a time until thickened. Stop adding meal before too dry.
If thick enough after it is chilled, can be sliced and fried until brown.

title: rice custard
directions: Stir eggs, sugar, salt and spice together.
Add milk, vanilla and rice; mix thoroughly.
Pour into casserole dish; bake for 45 minutes at 325°.

title: quick mexican pizza
directions: Cook meat; drain.
Stir in seasonings.
Spread 1/4 cup salsa and 1/2 cup meat mixture on each tortilla.
Top each with 1/2 cup cheese and desired toppings.
Bake in preheated 400° oven for 8 to 10 minutes or until crisp and lightly browned.
Makes 4 servings.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: Brown ground beef in microwave.
Combine with spaghetti sauce, tomato sauce and chopped onion.
Simmer for several hours.
Drain cooked noodles and mix thoroughly with sauce.
Place in large Pyrex dish and cover with grated cheese.
Bake at 325° until cheese melts.
Turn oven off and let stand for 15 minutes until spaghetti sets.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Pour onion soup and 1 can of water in casserole.
Pour rice in and spread evenly.
Top with cream of mushroom soup mixed with 1/2 cup water.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Cover with aluminum foil and bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Uncover last 15 minutes to brown.

title: brownies
directions: Cream oleo and sugar together.
Add eggs one at a time.
Mix in remaining ingredients and bake in sheet cake pan, greased, at 350° for 30 minutes or until center is firm.
Cut in squares.

title: tater tot hot dish
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a long 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Brown meat and drain. Spread Tater Tots all over.
Mix soup and seasonings to taste. Pour over Tater Tots and meat. Sprinkle peas and carrots and cheese on top. Bake 1 hour.

title: chicken and spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti until tender; drain.
Add all other ingredients except 1/4 cup cheese.
Mix well.
Pour into greased baking dish. Cook at 325° for 1 hour.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese and bake 5 minutes more.

title: squash casserole
directions: Place all of this in greased casserole dish after you mix it well.
Put dish in pan of hot water; bake until firm at 350°, approximately 1 1/2 hours.
This can be frozen and baked later. Add extra cooking time if frozen.

title: artichoke spread
directions: Mix well and put into a 1-quart baking dish.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Serve with crackers.

title: pizza salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine macaroni, tomatoes, Cheddar cheese, green onions and pepperoni.
In a small bowl, combine oil, Parmesan cheese, vinegar and seasonings; pour over macaroni mixture.
Cover and refrigerate for several hours.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients.
Sift and stir next 4 ingredients.
Add last ingredient (milk).
Roll into balls the size of small walnuts.
Roll in mixture of 2 tablespoons sugar and 2 teaspoons cinnamon.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 10 minutes at 400°.
(These cookies puff up at first, then flatten out.)

title: marinated corn salad
directions: Drain corn.
Mix corn, pepper, onion, celery and pimento.
In separate bowl, mix oil, vinegar and sugar.
Pour over corn mixture and marinate 24 hours.
Serve chilled.

title: orange roughy italiano
directions: Heat oil in a large skillet.
Add onion, zucchini and spices and saute over medium-high heat, stirring often, 4 minutes.
Put tomato and fish over vegetables.
Sprinkle fish with salt and pepper.
Cover skillet, reduce heat and simmer until fish is opaque and flakes easily with a fork.
Uncover skillet and sprinkle fish with cheese.
Cover skillet until cheese melts.
Serve immediately.

title: methodist tea cookies
directions: Cream butter; add sugar, then flour and cornstarch.
Add nuts. Chill at least 1 hour.
Form into 1-inch balls.
Press thumb into center.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheets for 12 to 14 minutes at 350°.

title: seasoned rice
directions: Add all to pot of boiling water (2 cups). Cover and simmer about 16 minutes. Fluff with a fork.

title: sugar and spice cookies
directions: Mix together the following: butter, sugar, egg and molasses. Sift remaining ingredients together in a separate bowl.
Mix every together thoroughly.
Refrigerate 1 to 2 hours, or overnight. Form into balls the size of small walnuts.
Place 2 inches apart on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Roll in confectioners sugar while still warm.

title: apple jack
directions: Mix together with fork the first 5 ingredients until crumbly. Sprinkle over sliced apples in pie plate (9-inch size).
Melt 1/3 cup oleo.
Pour over top; also sprinkle on 1/2 to 1 teaspoon cinnamon.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes in 350° oven or until apples are tender.

title: chocolate pies
directions: Mix sugar, flour, cocoa and salt together.
Add margarine, egg yolks, milk and vanilla.
Cook over medium heat until thick.
Stir constantly with wooden spoon.
Pour into baked pie crust.
Chill and top with Cool Whip.
Makes 2 regular pies or 1 deep dish.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Combine flour and baking powder.
Combine milk, vanilla, almond and sherry.
Alternate, adding flour and milk mixture.
Pour into tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: play dough
directions: Combine and cook over medium heat until mixture pulls away from sides of pan and becomes like play dough in consistency. Knead until cool.
Keeps 3 months unrefrigerated.

title: clam dip
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Add clam juice until desired consistency is reached.

title: monster cookies
directions: Mix in large bowl or dish pan. Bake on ungreased cookie sheets 10 minutes at 350° or until brown. Makes about 17 dozen.

title: potato casserole
directions: Defrost potatoes and combine with melted margarine.
Add remaining ingredients, except the cornflakes.
Blend thoroughly; pour into greased 8 x 12-inch casserole dish.
Cover with buttered cornflakes mix.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
You can make ahead of time, but add topping when ready to bake.

title: hush puppies
directions: In a medium bowl, combine cornmeal, flour, baking powder and salt; mix well.
Add the egg, milk and onion; stir just until mixed.
In a deep-fat fryer or electric skillet, heat oil to 365°. Drop batter by teaspoonfuls into oil.
Fry 2 to 2 1/2 minutes or until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels.
Serve warm.

title: sugarless fruit jam
directions: Combine all of the ingredients in a saucepan. Cover and cook over a low heat until the water is fully absorbed. Remove from the heat and allow to cool. Place the mixture into a food processor in batches and process until thoroughly blended. Pack into containers with tight-fitting lids and store in the refrigerator.

title: pineapple nut cakes
directions: Combine all ingredients together as listed.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: hardee's biscuits
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Cut or mix in Crisco.
Add buttermilk and egg together.
Add to flour mixture.
Work fast and knead lightly.
Roll out and cut into biscuits.
(I like to drop mine in melted butter and place in pan.) Bake for 10 minutes at 400° or longer if you like them brown.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook and drain macaroni.
Mix all ingredients.
Place in refrigerator for 1 hour.
Mix again.
Add more more if a creamier salad is desired.

title: banana caramel pie
directions: Boil can of Eagle Brand milk for 5 hours.
Keep can covered with water.
Remove can and put in refrigerator overnight.
Place sliced bananas in pie shell.
Open both ends of canned milk; slide out onto plate.
Slice and spread over bananas.
Top with Cool Whip.
Keep refrigerated.

title: squash pie
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add flour, sugar, salt, vanilla and spices. Scald milk.
Add butter and squash.
Pour into egg mixture.
Mix well.
Pour into 9-inch pastry shell.
Bake 10 minutes at 375°. Reduce to 350° and bake for 30 more minutes.

title: macaroni casserole
directions: Mix together and put in greased casserole.
Let sit overnight. Before cooking, sprinkle with cracker crumbs and dabs of margarine.
Bake 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: hermits
directions: Mix margarine, add sugar, egg and molasses.
Beat together well.
