Add flour (sift before measuring) and dry ingredients.
Add raisins.
Dough will be stiff, so knead with hands.
Spread on ungreased pan, leaving 1-inch edge from edge of pan.
Bake at 375°. Cool for 20 minutes before cutting.

title: hungarian goulash
directions: Saute onions and green pepper in oil until golden brown.
Add tomatoes and simmer until soft and thickened.
Add the cubed meat which has been seasoned with salt and paprika.
Cook covered until almost done, about 1 1/2 hours.
Add ketchup, vegetables and enough water to cover ingredients.
Cook slowly until done. Serves 8.

title: easter "hrutka"(egg cheese for easter)
directions: Cook in a double boiler until thick and curdly-like.
Pour into cheesecloth; tie and form a ball.
Tie tightly.
Let all liquid drip.
You can hang it outside or over pan in kitchen.

title: cobbler
directions: Melt 1/2 stick butter in Pyrex dish.
Make batter of 1 cup flour, 1/2 cup sugar, baking powder and milk; pour over butter in dish, then pour hot, sweetened fruit on batter and bake at 350° until golden brown.
You can sprinkle sugar on top and cinnamon, if desired.

title: sesame seed cookies
directions: If using corn flakes, crush into fine crumbs.
Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Blend butter and sugar.
Add egg and vanilla; beat well.
Stir in sifted dry ingredients together with 1/2 cup of the corn flake crumbs.
Mix well.
Shape dough into balls into about 1 inch in diameter.
Combine remaining corn flake crumbs and sesame seed.

title: hamburgers
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Fry over the grill until browned on	both
sides.
(May also be fried in a frying pan.) For cheeseburgers,
place a slice of cheese on top of hamburgers during last few minutes of frying.

title: coconut pineapple pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar, then add other ingredients.
Bake in uncooked pie shell about 30 minutes at 350°.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except chop mein noodles.
Place in a greased baking dish.
Top with noodles.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Makes 12 servings.

title: cream cheese glaze
directions: In food processor (with blade in) combine lemon juice and soft butter or margarine.
Drop through chute the cream cheese, with motor running.
Add powdered sugar and process until smooth. Makes 1 cup.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Beat margarine and sugar until smooth.
Add other ingredients and mix well.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes in preheated 350° oven.

title: buckhall's baked beans
directions: Strain beans.
Cut bacon into 1-inch strips.
Mix all ingredients.
Bake 2 hours at 400°.
Serves 100 people.

title: confetti salad
directions: Cook peas according to package directions or until just tender.
Remove from heat; drain and cool.
In large bowl, gently toss together peas, eggs, celery, carrot, pickle relish and onion. Combine mayonnaise, cheese, salad seasoning and mustard; toss with vegetable mixture.
Cover and chill.
Makes 4 servings.

title: coffee bars
directions: Dissolve
soda in
coffee.
Mix
together.
Pour
on
a greased cookie sheet or large pan.	Spread chocolate chips and nuts on top.
Bake in a
350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.
When cool, cut into squares.

title: super quick sticky rolls
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In small bowl, combine margarine, brown sugar and corn syrup; blend well.
Spread evenly in bottom of ungreased 8 or 9 inch round pan.
Sprinkle with pecans.
Remove dough from can.
Separate into 8 coils.
Do not unroll breadsticks.
In shallow dish, combine sugar and cinnamon; dip one cut side of each coil in sugar-cinnamon mixture.
Arrange coils, sugared side down, over pecans in pan.
Sprinkle with any remaining sugar mixture.
Bake at 375° for 19 to 24 minutes or until deep golden brown.
Cool 1 minute.
Invert onto serving plate.
Serve warm.
Makes 8 rolls.

title: chili parlor chili
directions: Boil meat in water until red is gone.
Add all other ingredients.
Bring to a boil and simmer for 3 hours.
Remove bay leaves.
Let sit for 1 day so spices blend.
Great for 3-ways and Cheese Coneys!

title: pork chops for microwave
directions: Mix soup, milk or water together.
Place in a baking dish over chops.
Bake at 50% power for 15 minutes per pound.

title: banana muffins
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt in a mixing bowl.
In separate bowl, thoroughly beat together egg, sugar, butter and mashed bananas.
Add to dry ingredients and stir until moistened.
Fill greased muffin cups 3/4 full.
Bake in preheated oven at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes or until top springs back when lightly touched.

title: no-cook broccoli casserole
directions: Mix first four ingredients together.
Blend mayo, vinegar and sugar and add to other ingredients.
Store in refrigerator overnight for better flavor.

title: *sweet potato souffle
directions: Mix until light.
Fold in pan and bake in a moderate 350° oven until golden.
Sprinkle walnuts on top.

title: apple salad
directions: Combine pineapple and sugar.
Put in saucepan.
Boil 3 minutes. Add jello; stir until dissolved.
Add cream cheese; mix well.
Let cool.
Fold in apples, celery, Cool Whip and nuts.
Chill.
Cut in squares; serve plain or on lettuce leaves.
Can use any flavor jello.

title: lemon cheesecake
directions: Combine crumbs, sugar and butter; mix well.
Press mixture firmly on the bottom and up sides (to within 1-inch of top) of a 9 or 10-inch spring-form pan (or use 9-inch square pan; press mixture on the bottom).
Bake at 250° for about 8 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool.

title: prune cake
directions: Mix sugar and oil.
Stir in eggs.
Sift flour, spices and soda together.
Add flour mixture, alternating with milk, ending with flour.
Add prunes and nuts; mix well.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Put in blender or food grinder onions, garlic and green peppers; set aside.
Cut up tomatoes and cook until thick.
Add all ingredients together and heat and pack in hot jars.

title: lamb and spinach burgers
directions: Heat broiler or prepare outdoor grill.
Remove any tough stems from spinach.
Wash leaves and dry well. Set aside about 1/3 of the nicest leaves for garnish.
Chop the rest and reserve. Meanwhile, in a medium frying pan over medium high heat, cook the bacon until crisp, 5 to 7 minutes.
Drain on paper towels, crumble and set aside.
Discard all but 1 tablespoon rendered fat.
Place pan with the reserved bacon fat over medium heat.
Add red pepper and onion; cook, stirring occasionally, until soft, about 5 minutes.
Add reserved chopped spinach and cook just until it wilts, 2 to 3 minutes.
In a large bowl, combine the crumbled bacon and the spinach mixture with lamb and bread crumbs.
Mix until well blended, then divide mixture in fourths, shaping each portion into a 1 1/4-inch thick patty.
Place patties on grill, broiler pan or a foil-lined cookie sheet and cook, turning once, until done (6 to 7 minutes per side for medium rare longer for well done).
Line rolls with reserved spinach leaves.
Add burgers and top with crumbled Feta cheese.
Serves 4.

title: sauted zucchini
directions: In a

nonstick skillet, heat oil over medium-high heat. Add zucchini and saut until just tender and lightly browned, 5 to 8 minutes. Combine remaining ingredients and add to zucchini. Remove from heat. Toss gently and serve immediately.

title: party potatoes(club member: amanda speed)
directions: Prepare potatoes according to package directions. Add onions, sour cream and cream cheese. Mix well and place in baking dish. Brush well with melted butter and sprinkle with paprika. Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: salmon cheese balls
directions: Mix the first 8 ingredients well.
Shape mixture into little balls the size of a walnut.
Push cube of cheese into the center and reshape ball.
Roll in bread crumbs and fry in bacon grease on all sides.

title: green tomato pickles
directions: Soak tomatoes in lime water 24 hours; drain and wash carefully through 3 or 4 waters.
Soak in ice water 4 hours. Drain well.
Combine vinegar, spices and sugar.
Heat and pour over tomatoes and let set for 3 or 4 hours.
Add tomatoes and simmer for 35 minutes.
Put in clean, hot jars and seal.

title: easy cheese bread
directions: Sift together the flour, baking powder and salt.
Cut in butter.
In small bowl, beat eggs until foamy, then add sugar and milk.
Pour egg mixture into flour mixture; stir only until moistened.
Grease 1 large loaf pan or 2 small ones.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
May not take as long for small pans.

title: genoese pesto
directions: Put all ingredients in blender.
Should be a paste.
Tastes best over linguine.
Cook linguini.
Add 2 tablespoons out of cooking water to the pasta.
Put in the paste.
Pour pesto over pasta.
Toss and eat.
Serves 4.

title: buttermilk cake
directions: Cream together sugar and shortening.
Beat eggs in one at a time.
Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and soda.
Blend into creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk (flour in 4 parts, milk 3) and vanilla and lemon extract.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan at 350° for 1 hour.
This cake is much better, more moist and lasts indefinitely if you keep it covered.
When you remove from pan, put on cake plate, wrap immediately in foil while hot.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Cook macaroni and cheese according to package directions. Brown hamburger meat
and add onion.
Drain.
Mix macaroni and cheese and browned hamburger meat.
Place in an ungreased casserole dish.
Spread cheese over top and bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Good with cornbread and green salad.

title: black forest cake easy
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in greased and floured pan, 9 x 13-inch.
Cool and frost.

title: no-crust cheesecake(passover)
directions: Beat cheese in electric mixer until softened.
Add eggs, 1 cup sugar, salt and almond extract.
Beat until smooth, thick and lemon colored.
Pour into a buttered 9-inch spring-form pan.
Bake in a preheated 325° oven for 45 to 50 minutes or until set.
Cool on cake rack 20 minutes.
Mix 2 tablespoons sugar, sour cream and vanilla.
Pour over cake (or spread on top of cake).
Return to oven and bake 10 minutes.
Chill and decorate with shaved chocolate.

title: bread pudding
directions: In large bowl, toss bread, cinnamon and nutmeg.
In medium pan, combine milk, sugar, butter and salt; bring to boil.
Stir in eggs.
Pour over bread; mix well.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Boil sweet potatoes; let cool and take skin off.
Cut in half and arrange in casserole dish.
Combine remaining ingredients and bring to a boil, stirring occasionally.
Pour over sweet potatoes and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: holly wreaths
directions: Combine butter and marshmallows in medium saucepan; cook over low heat until melted, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; add vanilla and food coloring.
Mix in corn flakes.
Drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper.
Form wreaths.
Decorate with cinnamon candies.

title: angel hair slaw
directions: Mix oil, vinegar, pepper, salt and sugar.
Mix until sugar and salt are dissolved.
Then mix all ingredients and serve.
Will not be good the next day.
Preparation time:
10 to 15 minutes.

title: quick and easy rice casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients together in a 2 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Bake for 1 hour in a 350° oven.

title: diet egg custard(diabetic)
directions: Stir together.
Pour mixture in individual custard cups and sprinkle with nutmeg.
Put hot water in flat baking dish; set cups in the water and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Delicious.
Use for lunch only, one cup daily.
Don't ever indulge.
Makes 6 custard cups.

title: baking powder biscuits
directions: Sift together into bowl the dry ingredients.
Cut into dry ingredients with a pastry blender the vegetable shortening until mixture resembles coarse cornmeal.
Make a well in center of mixture and add all at one time the milk.
Stir with fork until dough follows fork.
Gently form dough into a ball and put on a lightly floured surface.
Knead dough by folding opposite side over toward you.
Using fingertips, gently push dough away.
Give it a quarter turn.
Repeat process rhythmically 10 to 15 times, until dough is just smooth.
Always turn dough in same direction, using as little additional flour as possible.

title: glazed carrots
directions: In a one-quart casserole, combine all ingredients except salt.
Cook in microwave, covered, 7 to 8 minutes or until carrots are just about tender.
Sprinkle with salt.
Yield: 5 to 6 servings.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients well;
refrigerate.
Will keep well for 3 weeks.
Especially
good
with carrot and celery sticks, cauliflower and green pepper.
Can also be used with chips.

title: ice cream pie
directions: To make chocolate sauce: Bring to boil the sugar, evaporated milk, vanilla, chocolate and butter.
Boil for one minute, then cool.
Soften ice cream and spread in the two pie crusts.
Freeze. Pour cooled chocolate sauce over ice cream and refreeze.
Mix Cool Whip with nuts and spread over chocolate.
Keep frozen until ready to serve.

title: no bake peanut butter bars
directions: Crush graham crackers very fine.
Add melted butter (or margarine), peanut butter and powdered sugar.
After mixing together, put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pat firmly.
Melt chips; spread on top.
Put in refrigerator about 15 minutes or until chocolate starts to get firm.
Cut into 1-inch squares.

title: summer egg salad
directions: Thoroughly blend cream cheese, mayonnaise and seasonings. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Spoon 1/2 cup mixture into each pocket bread half.
Store in cooler on ice.
Makes 6 halves.

title: old fashion cooked cheese
directions: Put
all
ingredients
into double boiler.
Add caraway seed. Cook
over
medium heat until all is melted and creamy. Keep
on stirring so it will not stick, then pour into a bowl. When cold, this cheese spreads nice and easy on bread.

title: hot apple cake with caramel pecan sauce
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease cake pan and set aside.

title: mephistol cake
directions: Cream shortening, cocoa and sugar.
Add egg.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Add vanilla and pecans.
Bake in layers at 350°.

title: oven caramel corn
directions: Have popped popcorn ready.
In saucepan, melt brown sugar, syrup, salt and butter together.
Bring to boil and boil for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add soda and vanilla; stir well and pour over popcorn (that's in a large sheet pan).
Cook in 200° oven for 1 hour, mixing every 15 minutes.

title: turkey custard cups
directions: About 30 minutes before serving, cook green onion in a 1 quart saucepan over medium heat in hot butter or margarine until tender, stirring occasionally.
Meanwhile, cut bread into 1/4-inch cubes; place bread into 6 (6 ounce) custard cups.
Sprinkle with the diced turkey and shredded cheese.
In medium bowl with wire whisk or fork, beat eggs, milk, salt and green onion.
Pour mixture into custard cups.
Place custard cups in a 12-inch skillet.
Pour water in skillet to come halfway up side of custard cups.
Over medium-low heat, heat water to boiling.
Cover skillet and remove from heat.
Let custard stand in covered skillet 15 minutes or until set.
Makes 6 main dish servings.

title: oriental rice
directions: Cook pork bits in 2 tablespoons bacon grease until well done. Add to cooked rice.
While pork is cooking, saute green onions, green beans and carrots in 2 to 3 tablespoons of bacon grease for 8 to 12 minutes.
When
done,
add to rice and stir well.
Beat eggs and cook
in 1 to 2 tablespoons bacon grease, then add to rice mixture
and
stir
well.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Serve with soy sauce as a condiment.

title: fruit punch
directions: Mix all liquids together.
Chill.
Just before serving, top with orange slices and cherries.
Add ice cubes.

title: date nut bars
directions: Put dates and 1 cup brown sugar in a saucepan. Add enough water to cover dates. Over medium heat, bring to a boil. Boil about 10 minutes. Set aside.

title: seafood cocktail sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in a small bowl, stirring to mix well. Cover and refrigerate until chilled. Serve with shrimp, crab or lobster cocktail.

title: snack meatballs
directions: Combine milk, 2 teaspoons Worcestershire sauce and soup mix; blend well.
Let stand for about 5 minutes.
Add beef; mix well. Mixture will be moist.
Shape into balls, using one tablespoon for each.
Place on rack in broiler pan.
Broil 5 to 6 inches from heat for 10 to 12 minutes; do not turn.
Combine remaining Worcestershire sauce and remaining ingredients in saucepan; cook, stirring until heated through.
Add meatballs; serve.
May be frozen and reheated.

title: biscuit pudding
directions: Crumble biscuits into 1 1/2-quart Pyrex baking dish.
Mix remaining ingredients and press over biscuits.
Stir to mix.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: zesty pork chops
directions: Brown chops in oil.
Combine sauce ingredients, reserving 1/2 cup
mixture.
Pour
over chops.
Simmer over low heat for 25 minutes.
Place apple slices over chops and add remaining sauce. Cover
and	simmer 25 minutes longer.
Blend cornstarch with sauce and cook until thick.

title: sharp cheddar and walnut spread
directions: Combine cheese, butter, sour cream, Cayenne, mace and cooking wine in the container of a food processor, and whirl until mixture is smooth and creamy.
Scrape into a bowl. Stir in the nuts. Taste, and correct seasoning.
Pack the spread into two 1 1/2 to 2 cup glazed crocks (onion soup bowls are nice for this). Cover tightly and refrigerate for two days or more before serving.
To serve, let the spread soften slightly at room temperature.
Yield: 3 cups.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a greased casserole dish.
Top with grated Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: lemonade watermelon punch
directions: Cut a slice of watermelon from the bottom in order to sit flat. Cut 1/3 off the top of melon.
Remove pulp and separate from seeds; puree in blender.
Replace pureed melon (about 12 cups); stir in lemonade, water and grenadine.
Add lemon-lime beverage just before serving.

title: mother anderson's gingerbread
directions: Bake at 350° for 35 minutes
in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.

title: oatmeal candy
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa together.
Add milk.
Bring to a boil and boil for 1 1/2 minutes.
Remove from heat and add oatmeal.
Drop on wax paper with a teaspoon and allow to cool.

title: green rice
directions: Mix in casserole dish.
Bake in oven at 350° until thoroughly heated.

title: cheeses vegetable medley
directions: Cook vegetables in salted water until crisp tender (drain). Mix milk, cheese and butter in a bowl. Cook in microwave until cheese melts. Put vegetables in a casserole dish, pour cheese mixture over vegetables (sprinkle more cheese on top if you like) and microwave for 5 minutes.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Pour into top of double boiler and heat. Cook until thick and spoon some of this hot mixture over beaten egg yolks; return to pan. Cook 2 minutes longer.
Add vanilla, margarine and coconut.
Pour into baked pie shell. Top with meringue.

title: chocolate shake
directions: In a heavy medium-sized saucepan, stir sugar and water over low heat until sugar dissolves. Increase heat and bring to a boil. Whisk sugar syrup into a small bowl with the cocoa. Return to saucepan and boil 1 minute, whisking constantly. Pour into bowl. Mix in vanilla and cool completely. Cover and chill until cold, at least 1 hour. Pour chocolate syrup and milk into blender and mix. Gradually add ice cream, blending each time until smooth. Makes 2 glasses.

title: pumpkin pies
directions: Bake in 425° oven for 15 minutes, then reduce heat to 350°. Bake for 45 minutes.

title: pasta salad
directions: Chop all vegetables except tomatoes and mushrooms and put in a microwavable bowl.
Add 1 bottle of Italian dressing.
Microwave on High 4 to 6 minutes until vegetables are tender-crisp.
Boil pasta 8 to 10 minutes.
Drain and rinse with cold water.
Stir into vegetables.
Add tomatoes, mushrooms and olives.
Refrigerate until chilled.
Salad can be eaten immediately, but it tastes even better the second day.
This low calorie salad makes a cool summer meal! Serves 16.

title: fruited bulgur
directions: Place bulgur in a colander and rinse under cold running water. Drain and place in a container with a tight fitting cover.
Add water, apricot nectar, fruit bits, oat bran and honey.
Add onion powder.
Stir well.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: guatemalan pickled vegetables(verduras en escabeche de guatemala)
directions: Fry the jalapeno peppers in oil for 2 minutes to soften the skins. Remove the jalapenos, slice them open and remove the seeds and fibers. Set aside. Blanch the carrots, cauliflower, onion and garlic separately in boiling water for 2 minutes. Drain well and mix them all together. Place in glass jar or stone crock. Mix thyme, oregano, bay leaves, salt and sugar in the cider/vinegar. Pour over the vegetables and mix well. Allow the escabeche to marinate 1 day before using. The pickled vegetables can be refrigerated or stored at room temperature in a cool place. Without the seeds and fibers, the jalapenos just add flavor and not the heat. This is excellent and very easy to make.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt chocolate chips, peanut butter and oleo together.
Mix with Wheat Chex.
Put powdered sugar in bag and put in Chex mix. Shake well.
Pour into a dish.

title: pasta salad
directions: Combine all ingredients except mayonnaise. Add salt and pepper to taste. Add 2 tablespoons
mayonnaise, more if desired.
Chill.

title: summer chicken salad
directions: I add shredded Cheddar cheese.

title: chicken zucchini casserole
directions: Set chicken aside.
Dice zucchini in 1-inch chunks; cook until tender and set aside.
Simmer onion and carrots in oleo until tender.
Mix all together with cream of chicken soup; add 2 1/2 cups herb Croquette dressing.
Pour in casserole dish; add the other half cup dressing mix on top of casserole and bake at 350° for 30 or 40 minutes.
Makes a whole meal.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Mix and bake in layers at 325° for about 30 minutes.

title: mirza gasemi(eggplant, tomato and garlic)
directions: Roast whole eggplants over charcoal, or bake in a 400° oven until tender, about 15 to 20 minutes.
Allow eggplants to cool, then peel and chop fine.
Saute onions and garlic until soft. Stir in turmeric and eggplants; saute for a few more minutes.
Add tomatoes; cook for 5 minutes, until all water is absorbed.
Stir seasoning and eggs into eggplant mixture; continue cooking for several minutes until eggs are cooked.

title: sweet n' sour chicken
directions: Brown chicken in large skillet. Drain. Stir in sauce. Cover and simmer for 1 minute. Add pepper stir-fry. Cover and simmer for 5 minutes or until peppers are tender. Serve over white rice. Makes 4 servings.

title: pecan pie
directions: Combine and bring to a boil all ingredients except eggs and pecans.
Remove mixture from heat and cool thoroughly before adding eggs, stirring all the time you are adding.
Add pecans and pour into prepared pie shell; bake at 400° for 10 minutes and 325° for 45 minutes.

title: jello salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large bowl.
Refrigerate 1 hour and serve.

title: aunt virginia's pumpkin pie
directions: Thicken 1 cup boiling milk with flour; cook until smooth.
Then add the following mixture:
sugar, pumpkin, egg yolks, salt and spices.
At the last stir in the whipped egg whites.
Put in pastry shell and bake until it puffs and is brown at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: lemon squares
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients well and pat into an 8 1/2 x 11-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: microwave turkey meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl until blended.
Place a 4-ounce glass custard cup, right side up, in the center of a 9-inch deep-dish microwave-safe pie plate.
Pack turkey mixture in a ring around custard cup.
Loosely cover turkey mixture with waxed paper.

title: fish batter
directions: Mix all ingredients well.

title: healthy chinese noodles
directions: Cook the spaghetti while you are preparing the other ingredients so that it remains hot.
Timed properly, you should drain the spaghetti right before it is stirred in with the other ingredients.

title: mid-carolina middle school oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream sugar, brown sugar and butter together.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add rolled oats and coconut.
Mix flour, baking soda, salt and baking powder together.
Add the dry mixture to the sugar mixture.
Add vanilla.
Blend until all ingredients are moistened.

title: spinach squares
directions: Mix flour, milk, salt, baking powder and eggs until smooth. Add spinach.
Fold in grated cheese.
Melt oleo in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Add spinach mixture to pan; pat down.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let cool before cutting.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Combine flour, sugar (1 1/2 cups), egg and fruit.
Pour in greased oblong pan.
Mix brown sugar and pecans and spread on top of mixture and bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Combine oleo, milk and sugar (3/4); cook for 5 minutes.
Add coconut, if desired, and spread on hot cake.

title: hamburg crock-pot meal
directions: Brown the ground beef.
Mix the soup and water.
Combine all ingredients and cook in crock-pot on high 2 to 4 hours or low 6 to 8 hours.

title: mexicana crema (sour cream)
directions: Whisk heavy cream with sour cream in a small saucepan.
Heat to 90° over low heat.
(Do not allow mixture to become hotter or the culture will be inhibited and the cream will not thicken.) Pour into a warm sterilized glass jar; cover lightly.
Store in a dark place 8-12 hours or until cream ripens and becomes thick. Refrigerate 24 hours.
Cream will continue to thicken.
This is a luxurious, thick, rich cream which resists curdling.
Use for special Mexican dishes in place of regular sour cream.
Yields: 1-1/2 cup.

title: death by chocolate cake
directions: Prepare cake per instructions on box.
Pour chips over top before baking (chips will sink to bottom).
Remove cake from oven. With a wooden fork, poke holes in cake.
Pour hot fudge over holes (cake is still hot).
Cool and ice with Cool Whip. Refrigerate.

title: dill vegetable dip
directions: Mix well and chill.

title: skillet cake
directions: In a skillet, melt together brown sugar and 1 1/2 tablespoons butter, then add moist fruit (dried fruit may be used if cooked until tender).
Make a batter as follows.
Cream together sugar and 3 tablespoons butter; add egg, milk and pastry flour.
Pour this into the skillet over the melted butter and brown sugar. Bake in moderate oven.
When done, turn out on a large plate, bottom side up and your cake is already iced.
Serve hot or cold with whipped cream or plain.

title: grandma's apple dump cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients into a thick batter.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: grilled chicken
directions: Place chicken in a dish or heavy duty zip top plastic bag. Combine vinegar and remaining ingredients; pour marinade over chicken.
Cover and refrigerate 8 hours, turning occasionally. Remove from marinade, discarding marinade.
Grill covered, over hot coals 30 to 40 minutes or until done, turning frequently.

title: party punch
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Then add slices of lemon or strawberries on top.

title: peach pickle 1
directions: Pour boiling water over peaches.
Let stand until skins slip off easily when dipped into cold water.
Peel.
Stick a whole clove into each peach.
Pour on 2 quarts water with the 2 tablespoons of vinegar added.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Mix and bake at 300° until done.

title: chocolate filled angel food cake
directions: Cut the cake 1-inch from top and take it off.
Spoon out cake 1-inch wall and 1-inch base.
Keep crumbs.
Combine pudding, 1 envelope Dream Whip and milk.
Beat until thick, 2 or 3 minutes. Fold cake pieces into mixture and fill the cake.
Ice with remaining 2 envelopes of Dream Whip

title: dirty rice
directions: Cook sausage, pepper, onion and celery.
Mix with rice. Put in	greased
baking
dish.	Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Uncover and cook for 15 to 20 minutes longer.

title: broiled shrimp with garlic and hot pepper
directions: Peel and clean shrimp.
Combine remaining ingredients to make the marinade.
Add shrimp and marinate at least 15 minutes but not more than 1 hour.
Next, remove shrimp from marinade and place on a broiler pan.
Broil for 3 to 5 minutes.
Serve immediately, or chill in a covered container.

title: almond roca bars
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and pat evenly onto cookie sheet (at least 10 x 15-inch size).
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes or until light brown.
While still hot, top with chocolate chips.
When warmed, spread over hot dough.
Sprinkle with fine slivered almonds.
Cut carefully into squares while still warm.

title: rumaki(microwave)
directions: Cut bacon slices in thirds and chicken livers in 1-inch pieces. Mix garlic powder in soy sauce.
Dip chicken livers in soy sauce. Place one slice water chestnut on one piece of liver and wrap in one slice of bacon.
Roll, secure and fasten with wooden toothpick. Place 12 at a time in a circle on paper towel-lined microproof plate.
Cover with paper towel.
Cook on High 3 minutes or until bacon is cooked.
Let stand 1 minute before serving.
Yields 36 appetizers.

title: easy punch
directions: Any flavor of sherbet is wonderful.
Lime and raspberry are my favorite.

title: banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift the flour, baking soda, salt and cinnamon.
Cream butter and add sugar.
Beat well.
To the butter and sugar, add the eggs and bananas and mix well.
Combine the milk and lemon juice and add to the liquid ingredients.
Fold dry ingredients by the 1/2 cup into liquid ingredients.
Fold well after each 1/2 cup of dry ingredients.
Pour batter into buttered 9 x 5 x 3-inch pan and bake for 1 hour.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: pretty salad
directions: Peel cucumber; then run the prongs of a fork down the sides of it, making thin lines all around the cucumber.
Cut it in thin slices; cover each salad plate with shredded lettuce leaves. Place 1 slice of cucumber near the top of the plate.
On the cucumber, put a thin slice of raw carrot.
On the carrot, put a thin slice of ripe olive.
For the stem, use a thin piece of celery and for leaves, parsley.
If you like, add your favorite salad dressing.

title: sugarless banana nut bread
directions: Sprinkle sweetener over mashed bananas and stir until dissolved.
Beat eggs well and beat into bananas.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add nuts and blend thoroughly into banana mixture until just mixed.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook noodles night before and soak in Italian dressing with oregano sprinkled on.
Mix well.
Let set overnight.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Add remaining ingredients. Place in greased bread pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken escabeche
directions: Sprinkle chicken with salt and pepper.
Place half the onions in baking dish.
Place chicken on onions and top with remaining onions.
Combine lime juice, bouillon, paprika and chili powder; pour over chicken and onions.
Cover and refrigerate 2 hours. Remove from refrigerator 30 minutes before cooking.
Place pimentos over onions and chicken.
Bake, covered, at 325° for 30 minutes. Remove cover.
Bake 30 minutes longer or until chicken is tender. Serves 4.

title: potato supreme
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pat mixture evenly in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with crushed potato chips.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until tender, uncovered.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Mix all together and cook in a large baking pan or 2 round layer pans. Bake at 350° about 30 minutes.
When cool frost with Fluffy White Icing.

title: puffed wheat squares
directions: Stir first five ingredients together.
Boil for 3 min.
Add to wheat and place in glass pan.
Press down.

title: hanky panky's
directions: Cook and drain meat.
Stir in cheese; melt.
Add other ingredients; mix well.
Spread on slices of approximately 1 loaf of party rye or pumpernickel bread.
Put on cookie sheet and freeze, then put in plastic Ziploc bag.
Store bag in freezer until ready to use.
Broil (watch carefully) for about 2 minutes. Serve from warming tray, if possible.

title: greek salad dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients well.

title: zucchini puffs
directions: In a large bowl, combine zucchini, eggs, onion and garlic. Blend in baking mix, salt and pepper.
Heat 1/2-inch of oil in deep-fryer to 375°F (190°C).
Drop batter by spoonfuls into hot oil and fry until evenly brown and fluffy.
Drain on paper towels. Sprinkle with salt before serving.
Serves 6.

title: cavatini
directions: Cook macaroni first, add browned hamburger.
Mix macaroni, spaghetti sauce, basil, mushrooms, onion, green pepper, tomato sauce, Italian seasoning, salt and pepper to taste.
Pour into a large 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Put sliced pepperoni all over top and sprinkle Mozzarella cheese on top of that and then sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until thoroughly cooked.

title: big red homemade ice cream
directions: Mix ingredients thoroughly.
Pour into ice cream maker; begin to make a delicious and simple ice cream.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Brown pork chops.
In large casserole dish, mix rice, butter, mushrooms and beef broth.
Place pork chops on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: goulash
directions: Cut stew meat into 1-inch cubes and brown in a bit of oil in a 4-quart pot for 10 to 15 minutes.
Add sliced onions, salt, pepper, paprika and water.
Lower heat to simmer.
Cover and let slowly cook until onions are all but dissolved, 1 1/2 to 2 hours. Serve over hot egg noodles and top with sour cream.

title: pat's fried puffs
directions: Mix all together.
Put in warm place for 15 to 30 minutes. Knead and roll out.
Cut into pieces and fry in hot oil or Crisco.

title: sunday morning sausage ring
directions: Heat oven to 350° (moderate).
Lightly butter a 9-inch ring mold.
Mix ingredients well and pack into mold.
Bake 20 minutes. Take from oven and pour off excess fat.
Bake 20 minutes more. Turn onto heated platter and fill with scrambled eggs (8 to 12 eggs) or sausage gravy.
Yields 8 servings.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream sugar, butter and cream cheese.
Beat until smooth. Alternately add eggs and flour.
Blend in flavors.
Bake for 90 minutes at 325°.
Makes 1 large Bundt cake.

title: grandma's cowboy cookies
directions: Sift together and set aside dry ingredients.
Blend shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and beat until light and fluffy.
Add flour mixture and mix well.
Add oats, vanilla and chocolate chips. Dough is crumbly.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet and bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: cherry cake
directions: Pour cherries (juice and all) in oblong pan.
Sprinkle sugar over this.
Sprinkle pineapple over this.
Spread dry cake mix over all.
Dot with butter.
Sprinkle nuts and coconut over all. Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours with foil on top.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, milk and lemon juice to mashed bananas; combine with butter and sugar.
Add sifted flour and pecans.
Stir only enough to blend.
Bake in greased pan at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Add remaining ingredients. Drop on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: olive dip
directions: Mix together, blending well.
Refrigerate before serving with your favorite crackers.

title: italian chicken and artichokes
directions: Melt butter in a skillet.
Add garlic and saute for 15 seconds.
Add chicken breasts, cooking for 2 to 3 minutes on each side.
Mix together soup, sour cream, mozzarella cheese, wine, and parmesan cheese and spoon over chicken.
Reduce heat and simmer 5 to 7 minutes.
Add artichoke hearts and continue cooking for 1 to 2 minutes.
Place chicken breasts on top of fettucine.
Cover with sauce and garnish with fresh parsley.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix cornbread, herb mix, onion and melted butter together in bowl.
Mix soups and chicken broth together in separate bowl. Stir well.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put in a layer of chicken, a layer of soup and a layer of crumbs.
End with a layer of crumbs.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: mom's pound cake
directions: Cream the butter.
Add half the sugar, half the flour, vanilla and lemon. Add 2 to 3 eggs; mix until well blended.
Add remaining dry ingredients and remaining eggs.
Mix until all blended.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 1 1/2 hours in tube pan or loaf pan until desired brownness.
Insert toothpick in center of cake to make sure it is done.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Put all in a blender until smooth and creamy.
Delicious with all vegetables.

title: cheese ball with pineapple
directions: Stir until mixed well.
Shape with hands into 1 large or 2 small balls.
Pat finely chopped nuts all over outside.

title: zucchini pickles
directions: Put sliced zucchini and onions in the mixture of water and salt.
Let stand for 1 hour.
Remove, rinse well and drain. Combine vinegar, sugar and spices.
Bring to boil and add zucchini, onion and green peppers.
Cook for 3 to 5 minutes or until vegetables turn color.
Pack in hot sterilized jars.
Cover with vinegar and seal.
Cool.
Refrigerate for at least 24 hours before serving.
Makes about 1 1/2 pints.

title: texas potatoes
directions: Mix thoroughly all ingredients but the last 2.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish; top with crushed corn flakes and dot with butter.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: nutty date snowballs
directions: Mix all ingredients; roll into balls.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Do not overcook.
When cookies are cold, roll in powdered sugar.

title: creamy turnip
directions: Cook turnip with dash of salt until tender.
Mash cooked turnip.
Add cream cheese, chives, garlic, pepper and butter; mix well.
Stir in heavy cream.
Pour into 8-inch square pan.
Dot with 1 tablespoon of butter.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: chocolate sauce for ice cream
directions: Melt the chocolate and butter together, then add the powdered sugar and Carnation milk.
Let boil for 10 minutes.
Serve over ice cream.

title: linda's sausage and egg casserole
directions: Remove crusts from bread and spread with margarine.
Place in greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch dish.
Cook sausage (crumbled), drain and pour over the bread.
Sprinkle the cheese over the sausage.
Mix the beaten eggs with salt and half and half.
Add to dish.
Cover dish and refrigerate overnight.
Remove from refrigerator 15 minutes before baking.
Cook uncovered at 350° at least 45 minutes.

title: steak giorgio
directions: Grill steak in oil to desired doneness.
Remove; add mushrooms to meat juices and saute.
Put steak on broiler rack.
Put mushrooms, then Mozzarella on top of steak.
Broil until cheese is melted.
Serve hot.

title: party potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until browned and bubbling.

title: short-cut lasagna
directions: Brown meat; spoon off excess fat.
Add tomatoes, tomato sauce, spaghetti sauce mix and garlic.
Cover; simmer for 40 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Season.
Cook noodles in boiling salted water until tender; drain and rinse in cold water.
Place half the noodles in an 11 1/2 x 7 1/2 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish.
Cover with 1/3 the sauce.
Top with half the Mozzarella.
Repeat layers, ending with sauce; top with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Let stand for 15 minutes; cut into squares.

title: manicotti
directions: Take the first 6 ingredients plus salt and pepper to taste and mix well.
Stuff noodles and place in pan.
Take leftover meat and put in skillet.
Brown, then add tomato sauce.
Pour over noodles and bake at 375°, covered, for 1 hour.
Great with salad and garlic bread.

title: cranberry chicken
directions: Mix dressing, onion soup mix and cranberry sauce together. Place chicken in ovenproof pan and pour mixture over chicken. Bake for 30 minutes or until chicken is tender.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into 9-inch pie crust.
Makes two pies.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes, then at 350° until done.

title: fruit gelatin salad
directions: Combine oranges, pineapple, cottage cheese, Cool Whip and vanilla.
Sprinkle gelatin over mixture and stir well.
Spoon mixture into 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish.
Combine pecans and coconut, sprinkle over salad.
Chill 6 hours to overnight.

title: sausage pinwheels
directions: Mix Bisquick, margarine and milk to make dough.
Chill for at least 30 minutes.
Mix chopped chiles and sausage.
After dough is chilled, divide in 2 or 3 parts.
Make into long, narrow rectangle and spread with chile-sausage mixture.
Roll up like a jelly-roll. Refrigerate or lightly freeze rolls.
Slice 1/3 to 1/2-inch thick.
Bake at 400° approximately 10 minutes.

title: applesauce biscuits
directions: In a small bowl, mix flour, baking powder, salt, shortening, cinnamon and nutmeg.
In a large bowl, combine cereal and apples. Stir in applesauce.
Gradually add flour mixture.
Mix well.
Drop by tablespoonfuls onto a greased baking sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 375°.
Serves 6.

title: golden glow salad
directions: Heat pineapple juice and water to boiling point.
Dissolve lemon gelatin in mixture and let cool.
Before it hardens, add evaporated milk and mixture of cream cheese, carrots, pineapple and vinegar or lemon juice.
Stir until all ingredients are blended.
Pour into mold and chill.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Combine sugar, oil, eggs and pumpkin.
Sift together flour, cinnamon, allspice, nutmeg, soda and salt.
Add to pumpkin mixture.
Stir in nuts and raisins.
Grease and flour 4 (1 pound) coffee cans and fill 1/2 full of mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Let cool and you can store in cans with lids.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Put all ingredients in large mixing bowl and beat 2 minutes on medium speed.
Do not overmix.
Line bottoms of 2 loaf pans with waxed paper.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Let cool slightly before pulling paper off loaf.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion with enough water to cover and boil 20 minutes; drain well, pressing between paper towels.
Stir together squash mixture, sour cream, salt and pepper.
Spoon into lightly greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Top with cheese.
Add crushed crackers on top.
Drizzle with melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: steak supper in a foil package
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Place 24 x 18-inch piece of heavy-duty aluminum foil in baking pan.
Place meat on foil.
Stir together mushroom soup and onion soup; spread over meat.
Top with vegetables; sprinkle with water.
Fold foil over and seal securely. Cook 1 1/2 hours or until tender.

title: quick and easy chili
directions: Brown ground beef with celery and onion.
Add beans and sauce and chili powder to taste.
Simmer 20 minutes.

title: pizza dough
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Slowly add 2 cups flour; work a little.
Let rise at least 3 to 4 hours.
Knead and add a little flour, working in to get rid of stickiness, so it's easy to work with.
Roll out to about a 13-inch pie.
Spread 3 tablespoons olive oil on crust, leaving 1/2-inch from edge bare.
Add sauce and cheese of your choice, leaving 1/2-inch from edge bare.
Bake at 425° until cheese melts and crust is puffed up and brown.

title: columbia river eel(modern)
directions: Slice tomatoes into thick portions; chop mushrooms and onion. Cover bottom of baking pan or dish with half the mixture of tomatoes, onions and mushrooms.
Put eel over this bed of vegetables and cover with remaining mixture.
Add a few tablespoons of lard and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: veggie bars
directions: Lay the crescent rolls in 9 x 13 pan. Bake as directed. Mix the cream cheese, mayo, dill weed, Hidden Valley and spread over top. Spread the vegetables over the mixture. Top with the cheese.

title: easy peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large mixer bowl, beat milk, peanut butter, egg and vanilla until smooth.
Add biscuit mix; mix well. Chill at least 1 hour.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Roll in sugar. Place 2 inches apart on an ungreased baking sheet.
Flatten with a fork.
Bake 6 to 8 minutes or until lightly browned.
Do not overbake.

title: chicken veg-all pie
directions: Layer chicken, onion and eggs in the bottom of a 4-quart casserole dish. Mix soup, vegetables and broth together.
Pour over layers.

title: cabbage soup
directions: Simmer for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: easy broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until tender; drain. Put in greased casserole dish. Cover broccoli with slices of Velveeta cheese. Melt margarine. Add 1 package crushed Ritz crackers to melted margarine. Put on top and bake at 350° to 375° until brown.

title: cabbage bake
directions: Put cabbage and rice in a baking dish.
Lightly saute hamburger and onion.
Add to cabbage.
Add tomato soup and bake. Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: gortons
directions: Place ground meat in large saucepan with water to cover.
Add seasonings and stir occasionally until meat is cooked well.
Add a little bread crumbs, enough to hold meat together.
Pour into several small molds.
Cool, then chill in refrigerator.
Can be frozen.

title: bangus en tocho(fish in black beans sauce)
directions: Cut fish to 4 to 6 slices; sprinkle with salt and let stand for about 20 minutes, then fry in hot oil until golden brown on both sides.
Transfer to a serving dish.

title: veggie dip
directions: Mix well and refrigerate.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix sugar, eggs and oil together well.
Sift flour, soda, cinnamon and salt.
Add to oil mixture and mix well.
Add apples and pecans.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 20 minutes in a tube pan.

title: green tomato chow-chow
directions: Bring vinegar and sugar to a boil. Combine other ingredients and add together.
Simmer 20 minutes. Stir often.
Pour into sterilized jars and seal.

title: chocolate chip bars
directions: Melt margarine and mix in sugar; cool.
Add eggs and beat; add flour and rest of ingredients.
Bake in square pan at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes until done.

title: my favorite crunchy cookie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
You can add raisins to flour so they will not clump together.
Beat well on low.
Drop by teaspoons about 2 inches apart on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes until golden brown.
Yields about 5 1/2 dozen.

title: blackberry buckle
directions: Sift together 1 cup flour, baking powder and salt; set aside. In mixer bowl beat together 1/2 cup butter and 1/2 cup sugar until fluffy.
Add egg and beat until smooth.
Combine milk and vanilla in separate container.
Add dry ingredients and milk alternately to the beaten mixture.
Pour into a greased and floured 1 1/2-quart oval baking dish.
Spoon berries evenly over batter. Combine 1/4 cup sugar, 1/4 cup flour and 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon. Cut in 3 tablespoons butter until crumbly.
Sprinkle over berries. Bake in 375° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.
You may substitute other berries or fruit.

title: butt and green beans
directions: Remove the wrapping from pork butt and in large pot, cover it with cold water.
Bring to boiling and lower heat.
Let pork simmer for about 1 hour and 40 minutes.
Add carrots and simmer another 20 minutes.
Add green beans.
Simmer 20 minutes and add potatoes.
Simmer until potatoes are cooked.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown beef and sausage lightly in oil with garlic and onion. Add tomatoes, tomato paste, water, basil, oregano, 1 1/2 teaspoons salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil and simmer, covered, 2 to 3 hours.

title: sugarless chocolate cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl and beat just until blended.
Pour into well-greased and floured 13 x 9-inch (33 x 23 cm) cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes, or until done.

title: reese's peanut butter cake
directions: Cream the peanut butter and oil.
Mix well and spread on cooled cake.
Mix cocoa, butter, buttermilk and vanilla.
Bring to a boil and pour over the xx sugar.
Beat until smooth and spread over cake.

title: smith and vaughn goulash
directions: Cook ground beef overnight in crock-pot at low setting.
Add all the can food next morning and heat until noon.
Can be eaten with crackers or cornbread.
Makes a big pot full, enough for a good size crowd.
Very good and flavorful.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar well.
Add eggs, one at a time. Add dry ingredients alternating with milk.
Blend in vanilla. (Sift flour, cocoa and baking powder together before adding to mixture.)
Bake in greased tube pan dusted with flour at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: salisbury steak
directions: Combine all ingredients, except soup and water; mix well. Shape into 6 patties.
Dip into flour and brown in hot fat. Place in baking pan.
Add soup and water.
Bake for 45 minutes at 300°.

title: taco pie
directions: Brown beef and onions.
Drain.
Stir in taco mix, water and green pepper and simmer 5 minutes.
Separate dough into 8 pieces. Spread on 9-inch pie plate.
Sprinkle 1 cup of chips over chips over crust.
Spoon meat over crust.
Spread sour cream over meat mixture.
Cover with cheese and chips.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes until brown.
Check sometimes it doesn't take that long, depends on your oven.
Serving Size:

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Fold in blueberries, (1 cup fresh ones or frozen ones may be used).
Bake at 350°.
This mixture will keep in refrigerator 2 to 3 weeks.
Also freezes well.
Makes about 48 muffins.

title: jiffy dump cake
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch baking pan, spread pie filling evenly over bottom; sprinkle vanilla over pie filling.
Sprinkle dry cake mix on top of filling.
Spread evenly, breaking up large pieces. Sprinkle nuts on top of cake mix.
Slice butter into thin pieces; place evenly over top of mixture.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: easy gazpacho
directions: Combine all ingredients except chopped vegetables.
Simmer for 20 minutes.
Just before serving add vegetables.
Plain or garlic croutons may be sprinkled on top when served.
Serve icy cold in hot weather - or hot in cool weather!

title: lemon zucchini bread
directions: Mix all dry ingredients in large bowl.
Mix eggs, milk and oil together.
Add to dry ingredients.
Fold in shredded zucchini. Bake at 375° in greased pan for 30 to 40 minutes.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: coconut balls
directions: In saucepan, stir butter, juice and flavoring.
In separate bowl, add sugar, dry milk and wheat germ.
Gradually stir in butter mixture; mix well.
Blend in coconut; roll in balls.
Place on waxed paper; let set.

title: dried beef cheese ball
directions: Mix ingredients and form into ball or 2 smaller balls.
Wrap in Saran Wrap; chill.
Will freeze.

title: pretzel salad 3
directions: Mix pretzels, sugar and butter in a bowl.
Press into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 400° for 6 minutes.
Cool to room temperature.

title: candy cake
directions: Make your favorite yellow cake mix according to directions. Bake in 8 or 9 inch layers.
Allow to cool and make seven minute frosting.
Put all ingredients in top of double boiler and beat with mixer for 7 minutes.
Spread on cake.
Take 1 large peppermint stick and crush.
(Works well in food processor.) Sprinkle between layers, on top, and sides of cake.

title: date balls
directions: Boil dates, butter, sugar and eggs together for 8 to 10 minutes, stirring until thickened.
Add to Rice Krispies, walnuts and coconut.
Mix well.
Cool for 30 minutes.
Roll into balls.
Then roll in confectioners sugar.

title: chicken and dressing
directions: Prepare dressing.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Put chicken on top.
Pour soup over this.
Cover; bake for 45 minutes at 350°. Uncover; bake another 45 minutes.

title: sweet potato muffins
directions: Mix dry ingredients first.
Stir in wet ingredients until batter is moist.
Batter will be lumpy.
Fill muffin pan 3/4 full, each cup.
Sprinkle top of each muffin with 1/4 teaspoon sugar. Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Yield:
12 muffins.

title: goody cake
directions: 1st layer:
Mix well the first 4 ingredients.
Batter will be stiff.
Pat in the bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish which has been lightly greased.

title: salmon log
directions: Drain and flake salmon.
Remove skin and bone (if any). Combine salmon with next 6 ingredients; mix thoroughly.
Chill 2 to	4
hours
in icebox.
Combine parsley and pecans.
After mixture has
chilled
enough to handle, shape into a log roll. Roll in parsley and pecans.
Chill and serve with crackers.

title: orange date cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar gradually.
Add eggs; mix well, then add milk and flour alternately, beating after each addition.
Add nuts, dates and orange rind.
Bake for 1 hour at 300°.
Drizzle with 1/2 cup orange juice and 1 cup of sugar mixed.

title: creamed corn casserole
directions: Melt margarine in casserole dish.
Mix remaining ingredients together.
Pour into dish on top of melted margarine and sprinkle paprika on top.
Bake for 30 minutes at 325°.

title: quick coconut pie
directions: Mix the ingredients in blender for 3 minutes.
Pour into greased deep dish pie pan.
Top with additional coconut to taste. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: veggie casserole
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients.
Place in 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Cover with buttered crumbs.
Bake, uncovered, in 350° oven for 30 minutes or until starts to brown.

title: carrot cake
directions: In a bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda and cinnamon. Add carrots, oil and eggs. Beat with electric mixer until combined. Add pineapple, coconut, raisins and nuts.
Mix by hand. Pour into a 9 x 13-inch dish and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
When cooled, frost with cream cheese frosting.

title: braised turkey breast
directions: Rub turkey breast in oil or oleo.
Combine salt, sage and paprika in a cup; sprinkle on turkey.
Place sliced onion in bottom of Dutch oven or large roaster pan.
Sprinkle garlic over onion and place turkey breast on top.
Sprinkle with additional paprika. Roast in a moderate oven at 350°, uncovered, for about 30 minutes. This will slightly brown the breast.
Pour water with bouillon cube in pan around turkey.
Cover with top of roaster pan, decrease oven temperature to 300° or 325°, continue roasting until done.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Steam broccoli.
After that is done, crunch up a sleeve of crackers.
Layer the bottom of casserole dish with crackers.
Put broccoli on top.
Melt butter and pour half over top of broccoli. Cut cheese into slices and lay them all on top of broccoli and sprinkle crackers and rest of butter on top of that.
Bake for about 1 hour uncovered at 350° and then it's done.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Heat 1 cup water; add cherry jello and gelatin and dissolve. Add sugar and stir.
Add lemon juice and pineapple juice.
Place in refrigerator and cool.
Then add crushed pineapple, ground cranberries, ground orange, celery and pecans.
Mix all together; place in refrigerator until jelled.

title: sweet and sour chicken(serves 4 to 5)
directions: Wash and dry chicken pieces and place in large ovenproof baking dish.
Mix preserves, dressing and onion soup together and pour evenly over chicken.
Cover and bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour or until chicken tests done.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Chill and serve with fruit wedges.

title: scalloped spinach
directions: Combine all ingredients, except crumbs.
Season with salt and pepper.
Turn into loaf pan.
Top with crumbs.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes or until knife inserted halfway comes out clean. Broccoli may be used instead of spinach.

title: porcupine meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients except tomato sauce.
Form into balls. Brown slightly.
Pour off fat and into skillet add rest of tomato soup and sauce.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves a family of 4.

title: umm!  good chicken salad
directions: Blend mayonnaise, sour cream and salt. Set aside. Dice chicken, cut grapes, thinly slice the celery, cut apples into bite size pieces and chop pecans. Combine chicken, grapes, apples, celery and pecans. Add mayonnaise mixture. Mix lightly. Refrigerate at least 1 hour or overnight. Serve on lettuce.

title: dill pickles
directions: Bring all ingredients to a boil for 15 minutes.
Pack cucumbers in jars.
Add the following to each jar:
1 dill leaf, 1 dill head, 3 cloves garlic, 1 teaspoon dill seed, 1 pod hot pepper and 1/4 teaspoon alum.
Then pour hot mixture over cucumbers.
Seal and turn jars upside-down overnight.

title: cereal kisses
directions: Add salt to egg whites and beat until foamy throughout.
Add sugar, two tablespoons at a time, beating after each addition until sugar is blended.
Continue beating until mixture will stand in stiff, shiny peaks.
Add vanilla; fold in cereal.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until firm.
Makes 3 dozen cookies.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Five minutes before cake is done, melt and bring to a boil the oleo, cocoa and milk.
Remove from heat and add powdered sugar, vanilla and chopped nuts.
Spread over cake while it is still warm.

title: salmon patties
directions: Combine all ingredients, except oil.
Shape into about 8 patties.

title: texas hash
directions: Cook onions and green peppers slowly in fat until onions are yellow.
Add meat and saute until the mixture falls apart. Drain.
Add tomatoes, rice and seasoning.
Arrange in casserole, cover and bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until done.
Serves 8.

title: kosher style dill pickles
directions: Bring syrup to a boil and pour over rinsed pickles.
Seventh, eighth and ninth day, add 1 cup sugar daily; heat daily and pour over pickles.
On tenth day, pack jars and pour syrup over pickles.
Process for 5 minutes.

title: old fashioned bread pudding
directions: Slice biscuits and lightly butter each side.
Arrange in layers in a shallow baking dish (6 x 9-inch).
Sprinkle each layer with cinnamon, cloves and raisins.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Spray bottom of casserole dish with Pam.
Line bottom of dish with sliced bread.
Beat eggs until foamy.
Cook sausage (or bacon), let cool and gently stir into egg mixture.
Pour egg mixture over bread.
Grate cheese and sprinkle over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes (until egg is done).

title: old-fashion potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes until tender.
Let cool; cut up into little squares.
Cut up green pepper in small squares, then add onion, mayonnaise, sweet pickles, salt and pepper.
Then mix together. Refrigerate, then serve it cold.

title: rice soup
directions: Boil soup bone with salt and pepper in enough water to cover until tender.
Remove meat from bone and set aside.
Measure broth and add water if needed to equal 2 quarts.
Add rice to broth and cook 15 to 20 minutes until rice is tender.
Add rivels to soup; add meat.
Boil slowly for about 7 minutes.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large pot. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat. Simmer for 30 minutes. Pack in hot sterilized jars and seal.

title: buttercream cake icing
directions: Cream together first 5 ingredients.
Add powdered sugar a little at a time.
Blend well until smooth.
Use immediately.
If refrigerated, icing gets hard because of butter.

title: sweet pickles
directions: Make paste of lime and water.
Mix well.
Add water (enough to cover cucumbers).
Let soak overnight.
Drain and wash thoroughly in clear water (will take about 4 washings).
After 5th washing, soak 4 hours and wash well.
Dissolve sugar in red vinegar.
Add cucumbers and let soak 3 to 4 hours.
Add pickling spice and boil for 1 hour.
Pack in jars and seal.

title: butternut chewies
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat eggs; add sugar, vanilla and butter until creamy.
Add flour.
Stir in nuts (mixture will be thick).
Spread in pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: raisin molasses cookies
directions: Beat shortening and 1 cup sugar until light and fluffy.
Add molasses and egg; beat well.
Combine flour, soda, cinnamon, cloves, ginger and salt.
Add to molasses mixture; mix well. Stir in raisins.
Cover.
Refrigerate until chilled.

title: pear relish
directions: Chop and grind first four ingredients and soak in 2 cups plain salt water for 2 hours.
Rinse with water and drain 3 times.
Mix together next 5 ingredients, vinegar, sugar, mustard seed and celery seed and Turmeric.
Mix this mixture with the pear mixture and cook about 30 minutes.
Cool and put in jars and seal.

title: cheese-its
directions: Blend oleo and cheese.
Add flour, pepper and salt.
Stir in Rice Krispies.
Bake at 350°.

title: german chocolate caramel squares
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine caramels and 1/3 cup milk in microwave dish.
Cook on Low until caramels are melted.
Combine cake mix, butter, nuts and remaining milk in bowl, mixing well. Press 1/2 of the cake mixture into well-greased 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake 6 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips. Spread caramel mix evenly over chips.
Crumble remaining dough over top.
Return to oven and bake for 15 to 18 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: easy beef casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In an 8 x 12-inch pan, combine potatoes, oil and pepper.
Spread evenly in pan.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes until slightly browned.

title: apple oatmeal bars
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Cream margarine, egg, vanilla and apple juice concentrate.
Stir in dry ingredients.
Add apples, nuts and raisins.
Spray a 13 x 9-inch pan with Pam.
Spread batter evenly in pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: herb roasted chicken(serving size:  4)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In 13 x 9-inch baking pan, arrange chicken.
In small bowl, combine remaining ingredients; brush on chicken.
Bake 45 minutes or until chicken is done.

title: cracker salad
directions: Mix all ingredients, add enough mayo to make it creamy, but don't add too much, as it will make everything soggy.
Make salad right before serving so crackers will still be crunchy.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix sugar and shortening until well mixed.
Add eggs, milk and vanilla.
Sift flour, salt, soda, baking powder and some of the flour.
Mix well.
Add rest of flour to make stiff dough.
Grease lightly a cookie sheet.
Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet 2 inches apart.
Bake in a 400° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.
Remove right away and let cool.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Mix well and place in greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: oven fried green tomatoes
directions: Grease pan.
Combine cornmeal, salt and pepper; set aside. Combine eggs and water and beat well.
Dip the tomatoes in egg mixture and dredge in cornmeal mixture.
Place tomatoes in a single layer in a pan.
Bake at 450° for 30 to 40 minutes or until golden brown, turning once.
Serves 6.

title: scalloped chicken
directions: Soak bread good in broth.
Add chicken to it (may want to heat if broth is frozen).
Add eggs.
Stir up.
Take out part of mixture.
Cover that in pan with soup.
Put remainder of bread mixture on top.
May cover with browned bread or cracker crumbs. Bake at 350° approximately 1 hour.

title: dorothy ramsaur's appetizers
directions: Mix it up; spread on bread of odd size and shapes.
Put in freezer.
Then broil until bubbles brown.

title: sunshine angel cake
directions: Beat cream of tartar, salt, vanilla and lemon or orange with egg whites until stiff.
Slowly beat in 1 cup of sugar.
Set aside. Beat egg yolks until quite light in color.
Slowly beat in remaining sugar.
Blend flour alternately with water.
Fold into beaten egg white mixture with large spoon.
Pour into ungreased tube pan and bake in center of oven for 60 minutes at 325°, then turn oven to 350° for 20 minutes.
Remove from oven and invert on cake rack to cool in pan.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Brown bacon and remove.
Saute onion and celery in bacon drippings.
Add this to crumbled cornbread.
Dilute soup with one can of water.
Add melted margarine, poultry seasoning and pepper to soup.
Bring just to boil, stirring to blend.
Pour soup over cornbread mixture.
Add eggs.
Stir until all is mixed thoroughly. Butter an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Place cornbread dressing into pan. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: apple crisp
directions: Line 8 x 8 in. baking dish with apples. Mix other ingredients, crumble over apples. Bake at 350° approximately 1 hour.

title: mexican casserole
directions: In skillet, cook ground beef, salt and onion until done; drain well.
Add enchilada sauce and simmer 10 minutes.
Combine cream of mushroom soup, green chilies and Velveeta cheese.
Cook until cheese is melted over low heat or microwave.
Starting with soup mixture, layer quartered tortillas, then the meat mixture.
Make several layers always starting with soup mixture and ending with soup mixture.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese on top.
Bake 1 hour at 300°.

title: pistachio salad
directions: In a large bowl, mix all ingredients together well; refrigerate.
Serve when ready.

title: taco casserole
directions: Saute ground beef and onion.
Pour off fat.
Add taco mix and drained tomatoes.
Cook 5 minutes.

title: peanut butter trail mix bars
directions: Mix and pat into a 9
x
13-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 12 minutes, just until
edges	are brown.
The middle will not be set but the bars will
firm
up as they cool.
Do not overcook.
Cut the bars while warm; let cool in the pan.

title: beer bread
directions: Grease bread pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour

title: antipasto(makes 33 pints)
directions: Boil cauliflower 3 minutes.
Cut all veggies except mushrooms and peppers.
In large kettle saute mushrooms in oil; add ketchup and peppers.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Add vinegar; cool 10 minutes. Add balance and simmer 15 minutes.
Pack in sterilized jars.
Cook in water bath (boil) 15 minutes for pints, 20 minutes for quarts.

title: buttercream icing
directions: In large mixing bowl, cream shortening and margarine or butter with electric mixer.
Add vanilla.
With mixer on medium speed, gradually add sugar.
When all sugar has been mixed in, icing will appear dry.
Add milk and beat at high speed until light and fluffy (usually takes additional milk).

title: aunt bessie's pound cake
directions: Combine butter, shortening and sugar.
Add beaten eggs. Alternate adding flour and milk and extracts.
(Mix by hand, not with electric mixer.)
Put in greased and floured tube pan or 2 loaf pans.
Bake at 315° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: hamburger quiche
directions: Saute hamburger and drain excess fat. Blend mayonnaise, milk, eggs and cornstarch until smooth. Add hamburger, cheese, onion and pepper. Mix to distribute. Pour mixture into raw pie shell (approximately 3 cups). Bake on a sheet pan in 400° oven for 10-15 minutes until filling has begun to set. Then reduce oven to 350° and bake for another 25 minutes or until knife comes out clean. Allow quiche to set for a few minutes, then cut and serve hot.

title: quick-baked pasta
directions: Bring 4 quarts of water to a boil.
Heat a large frying pan and add the oil, beef and garlic, saute until the meat is tender and then drain the excess fat.
Add all remaining ingredients except the cheese for topping and the pasta.
Simmer the mixture while the pasta cooks until just barely tender.
Drain pasta and mix it with the sauce.
Pour into a 3 quart glass rectangular baking dish and top with the remaining cheese. Bake uncovered at 350 degrees for 25 minutes or until bubbly hot.

title: fresh peach cream pie
directions: Stir
lemon
juice and peaches gradually into condensed milk and blend until thickened.
Fold into baked pie shell and spread with
whipped
cream, sweetened to taste with powdered sugar or Cool Whip.

title: apple-carrot quick bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350° (375° if over 3500 feet elevation). Blend first 5 ingredients.
Mix dry ingredients except nuts and coconut and add to first.
Beat 3 minutes, gradually add nuts and coconut; blend well.
Pour batter into greased 9 x 5-inch or 8 x 4-inch loaf pans and bake 50 to 60 minutes.
Check with toothpick. Remove from pan to cool.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Drain.
Mix remaining ingredients and add to drained beef and onion.
Cover and simmer 15 to 20 minutes or to desired consistency.
May need to add a small amount of water.
Spoon over hamburger buns.
Serves 6.

title: orsinger scotch cookies
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco/oleo.
Add molasses and mix.
Add 3 eggs and mix.
Sift flour, baking soda, baking powder and cinnamon.
Add to other mixture.
Add more flour, if necessary, as needed.
Roll out 1/4-inch thick and cut into 3-inch diameter circles.
Brush each round with beaten egg.
Bake at 300° for 5 minutes, then turn cookie sheet and bake 5 more minutes.

title: diabetic fudge
directions: Mix well. Drop on wax paper by spoonful. Freeze.
Yields 8 pieces.

title: borsch
directions: Cook beef and first 4 ingredients.
Remove bones when cooked. Add rest of ingredients and cook another 1/2 hour.
Serve with Sour Cream.

title: spare rib pasta
directions: Cut spare ribs into individual ribs. Cut salscicia into small 3 inch chunks. Saute rubs and salscicia in olive oil and drain. Add fresh oil and saute 3 large chopped onions. Add white wine (about 1/2 bottle) and simmer for 1 minute. Add ribs and salscicia, 5 cans chopped tomatoes with garlic, basil and oregano and 1 bunch fresh basil, (destemmed and chopped). Cover and simmer for about 2 - 2 1/2 hours. Cook pasta and drain. Remove meat from sauce. Mix sauce with cooked pasta. Serve meat and pasta separately. Pass Parmesan cheese.

title: old-fashioned tea cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Work enough flour into a lump of dough to be able to roll out with a rolling pin.
Cut into any desired shape.
Bake on a greased cookie sheet in a 400° oven for 6 to 7 minutes.

title: wild rice soup
directions: Saute rice in vegetable oil.
Add water and salt and cook until 3/4 done (about 35 to 40 minutes).
Drain; reserve stock. Saute onions, celery and carrot in butter in soup pot until onion is transparent.
Turn heat down and mix in flour thoroughly.
Cook 5 minutes, stirring often.
Do not brown.

title: hot cheese dollars
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix.
Form into balls; flatten. Bake 20 minutes at 350° on ungreased baking sheet.

title: meow burgers
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Add sour cream, cheese, salt, pepper, chili sauce and onion.
Cut out 2 eyes from 10 bread slices. Butter 1 side and set aside.
Butter the remaining 10 slices. Place buttered side down on cookie sheet.
Spread 1/3 meat mix on bread.
Top with cut out slices, butter side up.
Bake 7 minutes at 400°.
Serves 10.
Cut green peppers for whiskers.

title: swedish limpa bread
directions: Mix all ingredients. Bake in 400° oven 40 to 45 minutes or until done. Makes 2 loaves.

title: hot chicken salad casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except cheese, potato chips and almonds.
Better if allowed to refrigerate overnight.
When ready to bake, put cheese, potato chips and almonds on as topping.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: rice pudding
directions: In the top of a double boiler, cook rice, 4 cups milk and salt for 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Combine additional milk, eggs, sugar and vanilla in a large bowl.
When rice is cooked, blend with egg mixture.
Pour into a greased 7 x 11-inch ovenproof dish. Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Set dish into a baking pan with hot water. Bake 50 to 55 minutes at 350°.

title: curried fruit
directions: Drain fruit thoroughly and arrange in casserole.
Pour syrup over fruit.
Cover casserole and bake no longer than 45 minutes in 350° oven.

title: apricot oatmeal muffins
directions: Mix together. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Makes 15 muffins.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Alternate carrots and onions in layers.
Put dots of butter on top. Cover and cook at 400° for 1 hour. Stir once after butter melts.

title: cheese and sausage balls
directions: Mix Bisquick and sausage.
Add softened cheese and pepper. Blend well. Shape into 3/4-inch balls.
Bake at 375° to 400° for about 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 9 dozen.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Blend oil and brown sugar in mixer bowl.
Blend in eggs, one at a time. Stir in remaining ingredients, one at a time.
Shape into 3 rolls. Wrap in freezer paper. Freeze until firm.
Slice frozen rolls 1/4-inch thick.
Place on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 12 minutes or until light brown. Cool on wire rack. Yields 6 dozen.

title: pecan balls
directions: Melt chocolate and wax in double boiler.
Mix first 3 ingredients; press into balls.
Dip in wax/chocolate mixture. Place on wax paper.

title: beef or chicken gravy
directions: Bring the broth to a boil in a medium saucepan.
Boil until reduced by one third volume or approximately for 10 minutes.
In a small bowl combine cornstarch and water.
Gradually add to the hot broth, stirring constantly.
Cook over low heat, stir constantly for 5 minutes or until thickened.
Add the thyme or pepper.
Stir to mix.

title: spam and corn
directions: Brown meat in canola oil.
Combine eggs, corn and seasons. Cook over low heat until eggs are done.
Serves 6.

title: fancy chicken salad
directions: Mix together yogurt, mayonnaise, salt, curry powder, and milk. Add chicken.
Just before serving add almonds.
Serve on lettuce leaves.

title: blueberry nut crunch
directions: Spread undrained pineapple in 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Spread washed and drained blueberries over pineapple and sprinkle with 3/4 cup sugar.
Dump yellow cake mix on top.
Add chopped nuts sprinkled over cake mix and then sprinkle 1/4 cup sugar.
Drizzle with melted stick butter.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes then, using knife, make several slices through mixture and return to oven for 20 minutes more.

title: meat loaf
directions: Beat eggs; stir in crumbs, seasonings, milk and vegetables. Add ground beef.
Shape into 2 loaves.
Place into 7 x 4 x 2-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: teriyaki beef
directions: Sprinkle tenderizer on all sides of meat and let stand.
Cut into small pieces.
Marinate overnight in refrigerator.
Turn occasionally; drain.
Grill about 10 minutes.

title: seafood chowder
directions: Saute onions, add potatoes and water, cook 10 minutes.
Add fish and cook 10 minutes more.
Whisk clam juice and flour together until smooth.
Add clam juice and flour.
Cook until thickens.
Cook bacon until crisp, crumble and put on top of chowder.

title: chop suey casserole
directions: Brown beef with salt.
Mix all ingredients except noodles in a casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cover with noodles the last 10 minutes.

title: ida's squash supreme
directions: Boil squash until tender.
Drain.
Let cool.
Slice.
Melt butter, saute onions and carrot.
Add dressing and mix thoroughly. Cover bottom of baking dish with half of mixture.
Add squash, salt and pepper.
Pour soup over mixture.
Sprinkle with cheese and top with remaining mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut each biscuit into quarters.
In plastic bag, shake quarters in sugar/cinnamon mix a few at a time.
Layer in buttered Bundt pan.
Bring butter and sugars to a boil and boil a few minutes to thicken.
Pour quickly over biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Let cool slightly.
Flip onto plate.
Pinch off to eat (hence the name monkey).

title: cinnamon toast cobbler
directions: Drain peaches, save juice and bring to boil.
Add lemon juice, butter and peaches.
Pour into greased cake pan.
Put in cinnamon and dry bread, cut lengthwise.
Add cinnamon on top of peaches. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chili-cheese dip
directions: In square 8-inch glass baking dish, place ingredients in order listed.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve with Tostitos. Serves 8.

title: buffalo chips(given to clo fletcher by clara hollingsworth)
directions: Cream oleo, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
In separate bowl, mix together remaining ingredients.
Add to creamed mixture.
Mix well.
Place egg size mounds of dough on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: zucchini parmesan
directions: Grate zucchini or put through food processor.
Put half in olive oil in pan; brown slightly.
Remove onto baking dish and brown remaining zucchini.
To first layer of zucchini, layer 1/2 of Mozzarella, Parmesan and spices.
Repeat with remaining zucchini and cheeses.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes, or until cheese is melted and slightly browned.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Scald milk.
Add sugar, salt and shortening or oil.
Stir until dissolved.
Cool to lukewarm.
Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water; add to milk mixture.
Add eggs.
Gradually add flour; mix to a smooth, soft dough.
Knead on a lightly floured board until smooth and satiny.
Shape into a ball and place in a greased bowl. Cover with a cloth.
Let rise in a warm place until doubled in bulk.

title: old settlers baked beans
directions: Brown beef, bacon and onion in skillet.
Drain off grease, then place in crock-pot on low setting.
Add the rest of the ingredients; stir, then cook for 2 to 3 hours.

title: elegant eggnog
directions: Soften ice cream; put in serving container.
Pour eggnog over. Pour 7-Up in against the side of the bowl.
Have a shaker of nutmeg ready.

title: no cook icebox pickles
directions: Slice 12 small cucumbers very thin and put in gallon jar.
Mix remainder of ingredients, but do not heat.
Pour over sliced pickles and stir well.
Put in refrigerator.
After 5 days you may use them.
Store in refrigerator until all used.

title: caramel apple pecan squares
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In large bowl combine flour, oatmeal, sugar, soda and salt.
Cut in margarine until crumbly.
Reserve 1/2 cup crumb mix.
Press remainder in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes.
Add pecans to remaining crumb mix.
Spoon apple filling over baked crust.
Mix caramel and milk together.
Pour over apple pie filling then top with the crumb mixture.
Bake approximately 20 minutes until set.

title: pace sunset dip
directions: Spread cream cheese into a 9-inch microwave safe dish or pie pan.
Top with Cheddar cheese soup and salsa or picante.
Microwave on High for 2 to 3 minutes.
Serve with tortilla chips.
Enjoy!

title: pineapple cream cheese cake
directions: Mix cake mix as box directs, pour into a lightly greased 9 X 13 pan.
Bake, cool completely.
In a mixing bowl beat together vanilla pudding and cold milk until thick.	In a separate bowl whip cream cheese until smooth and stir into the pudding mixture, beat until light and fluffy.
Stir in pineapple, spread over top of the cooled cake.
Then carefully frost with Cool Whip, top with nuts and refrigerate.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Cut up carrots and boil in water until soft.
Combine cooked carrots with all the ingredients and beat until well mixed (will be somewhat lumpy).
Put into a 10-inch pie plate. Sprinkle with cinnamon. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Also can be frozen.

title: 24 hour vegetable salad
