directions: Place torn romaine lettuce in bottom of large bowl.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and sugar.
Top with 1 cup of the cheese, standing some slices on edge around sides of bowl, if desired. Sprinkle with salt.
Next, layer in order half the bacon, the leaf lettuce and peas.
Spread mayonnaise over top, sealing to edge of bowl.
Cover and chill 24 hours or overnight.
Garnish with remaining cheese, remaining bacon and green onion.
Just before serving, toss salad until mixed.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: quick praline candy
directions: Mix pudding mix, both kinds of sugar, milk and butter or oleo in a pot.
Cook and stir over low heat until sugar dissolves and mixture boils.
Cook gently stirring frequently until a small amount tested in cold water forms as soft ball (234° on candy thermometer).
Add nuts and mix well.
Remove from heat and beat until mixture begins to thicken.
No longer!
Drop by tablespoons onto waxed paper and let stand until firm.
Makes about 18 to 20 pieces.

title: out of this world pie
directions: In saucepan, combine first 5 ingredients.
Cook until thick. Remove from heat and add jello.
Allow to cool.
Add bananas and pecans.
Pour into pie shells and top with whipped topping.

title: mom's moist chocolate cake
directions: Sift together dry ingredients in a mixing bowl. Add oil, coffee and milk.
Mix at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Beat 2 more minutes. Batter will be thin. Pour into two greased and floured 8-inch round cake pans. Bake at 325° for about 40 to 60 minutes. Cool cakes for 15 minutes before removing from pans.
Ice cake with any icing you want to use. Freezes well.

title: waffles
directions: Sift flour, salt and baking powder together.
Beat eggs.
Add milk and shortening.
Add flour mixture.
Beat until smooth.
Bake in hot waffle iron.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Boil chicken pieces for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Clean the meat off of the bones.
Discard the bones and skin.
Cut meat to bite-size pieces and put into 9 x 12-inch pan.
Mix sour cream and soup together and add poppy seed to mixture.
Pour over chicken pieces.
Distribute cracker crumbs over top and pour melted margarine over top of this.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: saucy potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling water for 15 to 20 minutes, until tender.
Drain and set aside.
Saute onion and green pepper in butter until tender; add flour, stirring constantly.
Add milk; stir until thick.
Add cheese, salt and pepper.
Stir until cheese melts.
Stir in potatoes and pimento.
Spoon mixture into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: prune cake
directions: Combine oil, sugar and eggs.
Add dry ingredients and mix. Add remaining ingredients and blend thoroughly.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 60 minutes in an angel food cake pan.
Remove from oven and allow to cool 5 minutes.
Remove from pan and place in a deep serving dish.
Spoon on topping.

title: baked bean casserole
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Remove from skillet.
Brown onions. Add all other ingredients except beans.
Cook 15 minutes, uncovered.
Drain the lima and kidney beans.
Mix with the can of New England-style baked beans and crumbled crisp bacon.
Mix onion and bean mixture.
Pour into 3-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 15.

title: goulash
directions: Brown ground beef and cook macaroni.
Pour macaroni and tomato sauce with melted cheese over ground beef.
Mix together.
Serve hot.

title: healthy yogurt quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cover bottom of 9-inch pie plate with sliced mushrooms.
Mix all ingredients together except nutmeg, beating well.
Pour into pie plate over mushrooms.
Sprinkle top of mixture with nutmeg.
Bake 35 minutes or until lightly browned. Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: pork chop and apple stuffing
directions: Brown chops and place in casserole.
Make stuffing; mix chopped apples, raisins, onions, celery and croutons.
Moisten with chicken bouillon.
Salt with poultry seasoning.
Cover chops with stuffing mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Place on top of stuffing unpeeled apple slices.
Sprinkle with brown sugar.

title: cucumber preserves
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Refrigerate 2 to 4 weeks before serving.

title: swiss steak deluxe
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients and flour steak.
Brown steak in salad oil; add onion, tomato soup and water.
Simmer 1 3/4 hours or until tender.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Cook spinach and drain.
Melt (heat) cream cheese and soup mix. Add spinach and onion rings; melt butter and bread crumbs.
Spread on top.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: pizza sauce
directions: Mix and heat together.
Serve on top of crust for pizza.

title: perfect peanut clusters
directions: In a small saucepan, melt chocolate chips over low heat until smooth.
Remove from heat and stir in milk and peanuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto a cookie sheet lined with waxed paper.
Chill thoroughly before serving.

title: lemon drizzle
directions: In a small bowl, combine powdered sugar, corn syrup and lemon rind.
Stir in lemon juice until desired consistency.
Tint with food coloring, if desired.
Makes 2/3 cup.

title: henry's spaghetti sauce
directions: Mix all together and cook 30 minutes on medium heat.

title: pistachio congealed salad
directions: Drain pineapple.
Mix pudding with pineapple juice.
Add whipped topping, nuts, pineapple and marshmallows.
Mix well. Chill until ready to serve.
Top with crushed nuts.

title: creamed lobster, salmon or tuna
directions: Heat lobster, salmon or tuna in white sauce; add lemon and Tabasco sauce.
Serve over toast.

title: turkey loaf
directions: Dissolve bouillon cubes in boiling water.
Combine bouillon, egg and remaining ingredients, mixing well.
Shape mixture into a 6-inch loaf and place on rack of a lightly greased broiler pan. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: chocolate silk pie
directions: Cream butter and 3/4 cup sugar together.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well, then add vanilla and chocolate.
Use mixer to blend until thick.
Pour into cooled pie shell.
Refrigerate 15 minutes before adding whipped cream to which 2 tablespoons sugar has been added.
Chill until serving time.

title: *gambier (sweet and sour) dressing
directions: *If you prefer not to use sugar and want a non-sweetener, I use Twin in the place of sugar (1/2 cup).

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Make 2 rolls and wrap in wax paper. Chill. Slice and bake 8 to 10 minutes at 400°.

title: fried chicken with cream gravy
directions: Rinse chicken.
In plastic bag, combine flour, salt, paprika and pepper.
Add a few chicken breasts at a time to bag; shake to coat.
Remove chicken from bag.
Reserve remaining flour mixture. In 12-inch skillet, heat cooking oil.
Add chicken and cook, uncovered over medium heat for 10 to 15 minutes, turning to brown evenly.
Reduce heat; cover tightly.
Cook 30 minutes.
Uncover and cook 10 to 15 minutes more or until chicken is tender and no longer pink.
Drain chicken on paper towels.
Keep warm.

title: corn pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Combine both corns.
Add seasonings. Beat in eggs.
Stir in milk.
Fold in cracker crumbs.
Add butter. Stir well.
Pour in large 2-quart buttered baking dish.
Bake 45 minutes until fairly firm in center and browned.
Serves 8 to 10 people.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Preheat oven to 275°.
Pour rice in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt margarine or butter and soups together in a pan on top of stove. When melted, pour half of this mixture over the rice.
Take boneless chicken breasts and lay on top of rice mixture.
Pour remaining soup mixture on top.
Bake at 275° for 2 hours.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Cream all ingredients together (except 8 ounces Cool Whip). Spread into a graham cracker pie crust.
Cover with Cool Whip. Chill.
Makes 2 pies.

title: lemon bars
directions: Use mixer and mix dry cake mix and lemon pie filling.
Pour into a floured and greased 9 x 13-inch cake pan or 10 x 15-inch cookie sheet.
Smooth out and make sure batter is even.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.
Frost with a thin glaze, using powdered sugar and lemon extract.

title: strawberry fruit dip
directions: Combine cream cheese and strawberries in a bowl; add lemon peel and lemon juice. Cover and refrigerate at least 1 hour. Serve with assorted fruits.

title: corn dog casserole
directions: In a skillet, saute celery in butter for 5 minutes.
Add onions; saute for 5 minutes.
Place in a large bowl; set aside. Cut hot dogs lengthwise into quarters, then cut into thirds.
In the same skillet, saute the hot dogs for 5 minutes or until lightly browned; add to vegetables.
Set aside 1 cup.
In a large bowl, combine eggs, milk, sage, and pepper.
Add the remaining hot dog mixture.
Stir in corn bread mixes.
Add 1 1/2 C. of cheese. Spread into a shallow 3 quart baking dish.
Top with reserved hot dog mixture and remaining cheese.
Bake uncovered, at 400 degrees for 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Yield 12 servings.

title: coconut pie(makes 1 pie)
directions: Bake your favorite pie crust recipe or frozen pie crust.
Over medium heat on top of stove, add all ingredients and stir constantly until mixture coats the spoon.
(Mixture will be thick and stiffen as it cools in pie crust.)
Pour the mixture into the pie crust.
Top with meringue or Cool Whip.
(See Meringue recipe in this section.)

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix together sugar, zucchini, eggs and oil.
Add flour, salt, soda, cinnamon, baking powder, nuts and vanilla.
Bake in 2 greased and floured loaf pans at 350° for 1 hour.

title: "spanakopita" - spinach pie
directions: Wash spinach well; remove stems.
Sprinkle salt all over spinach (2 to 3 tablespoons salt).
Let set for 15 minutes, then rinse spinach.
Drain and squeeze off all liquid.
In a large bowl beat the eggs; add the cottage cheese and Feta cheese, parsley and onion and fold in the spinach.

title: crisp baked chicken
directions: Place skinned and halved chicken breasts in ice water. Preheat oven to 425°.
Place yogurt into a bowl.
Coat baking sheet with 4 sprays of light vegetable oil.
Toss all breading ingredients in a large plastic bag.
Shake well to mix.
Remove chicken from ice water and roll in yogurt.
Place in plastic bag to coat.
Place all chicken on baking sheet.
Spray once.
Bake 1 hour.
Turn chicken every 20 minutes.

title: no-bake butterscotch cookies
directions: Mix oatmeal, orange peel and walnuts in large bowl.
Combine butter, brown sugar and evaporated milk in saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Boil 3 minutes.
Remove from heat; add marshmallows.
Stir until melted.
Pour over oatmeal mixture; blend.
Drop from teaspoon onto waxed paper.
Makes 3 1/2 dozen.

title: apple bread
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: yogurt fruit shake
directions: Place ingredients in blender container; blend on high speed until foamy.
Serve cold.
Makes 8 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: cheese dip
directions: Mix butter and flour in a saucepan.
Cook over low heat for one minute.
Take off burner; mix in paprika, mustard, chili powder and pepper sauce.
Add milk, jalapeno peppers (finely chopped), cheese and crushed garlic.
Mix well.
Add rest of ingredients and cook over low heat until thick, stirring constantly to avoid lumping.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut each biscuit into 4 pieces.
Roll pieces in white sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Drop into a Bundt pan.
In a small saucepan, melt brown sugar and margarine.
Pour over biscuit pieces.
Put pan into cold oven, turn oven to 350° and bake 25 to 35 minutes.
Turn out of pan immediately.
Serve while hot.

title: cheese and dried beef spread
directions: Combine cream cheese and mayonnaise.
Add onion.
Add chopped, dried beef and mix thoroughly.
May add more mayonnaise, if needed, for consistency.
Chill.

title: pudding-sweet onion
directions: Stir together first 3 ingredients in a large bowl. Combine flour and next 3 ingredients. Gradually stir into egg mixture. Set aside.

title: apricot-chocolate torte
directions: With an electric mixer, beat eggs with sugar at high speed for 2 minutes.
Reduce speed to low and beat in vanilla, flour, grated walnuts, cocoa and baking powder just until blended.
Fold in chopped apricots and walnuts.

title: whipped cream substitute
directions: Combine water, lemon juice and vanilla; stir in nonfat dry milk powder.
Beat 5 to 10 minutes or until stiff; add sugar. Beat 1 to 2 minutes.

title: cheese and bacon(must do ahead)
directions: Remove crusts and spread cheese after it is at room temperature.
Cut bread in half, roll bread half, wrap with 1/2 strip of bacon and fasten with toothpick.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Cool and freeze.
When ready to serve, heat again for 15 minutes at 400°.
Serve warm.

title: dinner rolls
directions: Cook potato in enough water to make 1 cup.
Scald milk. Soften yeast in 1/4 cup water.
Add 1 teaspoon sugar.
Combine milk and potato water.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add yeast.
Add 2 cups flour.
Let rise until light sponge has formed, about 1/2 hour. Cream sugar and shortening.
Add salt, beaten eggs and about 4 1/2 cups flour; knead until smooth.
Let rise about 2 hours.

title: "it's what's for beserk"(quick dessert)
directions: Arrange small slices of angel cake in dessert dish.
Place your choice of filling on cake.
Top with your choice of topping.

title: hot milk cake
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar.
Let stand for 20 minutes.
Heat milk. When hot, add butter.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add flour mixture, a little at a time, to sugar and egg mixture.
Add vanilla, milk and butter.
This makes a thin mixture.
Bake in tube pan at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: blackberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Let cool a bit.
Add cold water and blackberries.
Let set until firm.
Add topping.

title: potato water rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup water.
In a large bowl, combine potato water, butter, sugar and salt.
When this has cooled to warm, add the yeast mixture and 3 cups of flour; beat well. Gradually add remaining 3 1/2 cups of flour.
Finish by kneading on a floured board until smooth.
Place in greased bowl, turning once to coat top.
Cover and let double in size (1 to 1 1/2 hours).
Knead down in bowl.
Divide into 24 pieces.
Shape into balls and place on greased cookie sheets.
Cover and let rise 45 to 60 minutes.
Sift flour over tops before baking.
Slash tops with shears.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool on wire racks.

title: linda's stew
directions: Cook meat overnight in crock pot; no water just meat.
Add all other ingredients and cook until tender.

title: patchwork casserole
directions: Cook hamburger and drain well.
Add peppers and onion, cook. Stir in all ingredients except cheese.
Spoon 1/2 of mixture in baking dish, top with 1/2 of cheese.
Repeat layers and cover with foil, bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: basic red barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients in saucepan. Simmer 15 minutes. Makes about 1 quart.

title: mexican broccoli
directions: Cook broccoli in 1/4 cup water until tender; drain broccoli. Beat eggs, then add cream of mushroom soup, melted cheese and milk; blend. Put broccoli in casserole dish and pour mixture over the broccoli. Sprinkle Ritz crackers over top. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in large casserole dish at 350° for 30 minutes.
This recipe can be cut in half for a 9 x 13-inch casserole.

title: honey glazed ham
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. Score ham and stud with the whole cloves. Place ham in foil lined pan.

title: honey mustard wings
directions: In a large bowl, mix soup mix, honey and mustard; set aside. Cut wings at joints and discard tops.
Add to soup mixture.
Toss to coat.
Place chicken in baking pan.
Bake at 400°, turning once, for 45 minutes or until chicken is done.
Yields 36 wings.

title: pecan pies
directions: Mix brown sugar and flour. Add eggs, milk and vanilla. Top with crushed pecans. Bake at 350° until crust is brown.

title: lemon sponge pie
directions: Melt butter and cream with sugar.
Add slightly beaten egg yolks, salt, then flour. Beat egg whites stiff in a small bowl. To the other ingredients, add lemon juice and milk.
Now fold in egg whites.
Put in preheated oven at 350° for 10 minutes.
Lower heat to 325° for about 30 minutes until golden brown.
It still will be wiggly.

title: ritz yummy crackers
directions: Mix milk and dates in saucepan together.
Bring this mixture to a boil for approx. 2 minutes.
Take off heat and add nuts.
Crumble crackers on a baking dish.
Spread mixture onto the crackers.
Bake 350 degrees for 7-10 minutes.

title: apple crumb pie
directions: Prepare apples.
Mix 1/2 cup sugar and cinnamon and mix with apples.
Arrange in unbaked pie shell.

title: old-fashioned split pea soup
directions: Wash peas and put in a large saucepan; add ham bone, onion, 3 lemon slices, carrots, celery and water.
Simmer 6 hours.
Discard ham bone and lemon slices.

title: pineapple dream cake
directions: Combine cake mix, oil, eggs and oranges.
Mix with mixer until well blended.
Bake in 3 (8-inch) or 2 (9-inch) round pans that have been greased and floured.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes. Cool on cooling racks.

title: fudgy oatmeal squares
directions: Stir together oats and water; set aside.
In a large bowl, stir together flour, sugar, cocoa and soda.
Add margarine, oat mixture and vanilla; beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Add eggs.
Beat 2 more minutes.
Pour into greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Cool in pan 10 minutes, then turn out on rack and cool completely.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.
Cut into squares.
Yield:
24 squares.

title: marinara sauce
directions: Over low heat, heat the oil. Add the garlic and parsley and brown, being careful not to burn.
Add 4 cans of crushed and 2 cans of the pureed tomatoes. Add the basil.
Chop up one of the carrots into tiny pieces and throw it into the sauce.
Peel and place the second carrot in the sauce to absorb the acid from the tomatoes.
Simmer over low heat for 4 to 6 hours. Discard the whole carrot and serve the sauce with your favorite pasta. Remaining sauce can be frozen for later use.

title: pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium bowl, beat eggs.
Add brown sugar and mix.
Pour in corn syrup and mix.
Add melted butter and vanilla; mix.

title: chicken cakes with creole sauce
directions: Melt butter in a large nonstick skillet over medium heat. Add bell pepper, green onions and garlic and saut 3 to 4 minutes or until vegetables are tender. Stir together bell pepper mixture, chicken and next 5 ingredients in a bowl. Shape chicken mixture into 8 (3 1/2-inch) patties. Fry 4 patties in 2 tablespoons hot oil in a large skillet over medium heat 3 minutes on each side or until golden brown. Drain on paper towels. Repeat procedure with remaining 2 tablespoons oil and patties. Serve immediately with Creole Sauce.

title: zucchini walnut bread
directions: Chop nuts, beat eggs, add sugar, then oil; combine dry ingredients.
Add the first mixture alternately with zucchini; stir in walnuts and vanilla.
Turn into 2 greased and floured bread pans.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Turn onto rack.

title: popcorn cake #2
directions: Melt margarine and marshmallows.
Stir in popcorn and M&M's. Press in buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool.
Cut into squares.

title: cream corn soup
directions: Melt margarine in saucepan and saute the onion and carrot until onion is slightly golden, about 15 minutes.
Add the contents of the can of corn plus the can of milk.
Add salt and pepper to taste and simmer on low heat until hot.
Makes 3 servings.

title: corn bread salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise and pickle juice.
Layer corn bread (crumbled) and vegetables.
Pour dressing over layers.
Store in refrigerator.

title: stuffed zucchini
directions: Slice zucchini in half lengthwise and scoop out pulp; save. Puree pulp and tomatoes in food processor.
Brown ground beef in skillet.
Add onion, Worcestershire sauce, tomatoes and pulp. Season with Prudhommes Cajun seasoning, about 1 1/2 teaspoons or to taste.
Stir in bread cubes.
Remove from heat.

title: steamed mussels
directions: Steam for 5 minutes.
Dip in melted butter.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients separately.
Combine milk and egg.
Stir in oil.
Add liquid to dry ingredients.
Stir only enough to mix. Pour into greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 400° about 25 minutes.
Serve with butter or syrup.

title: festive fruit flan
directions: In heavy saucepan on medium heat, cook 3/4 cup of sugar, stirring constantly, until melted and golden brown.
Immediately pour into greased 2-quart casserole flan pan.
Tip dish to coat bottom of dish.
Place in large baking pan.

title: caramel pecan pie
directions: Boil condensed milk in can in boiling water for 4 hours.
Make sure water is covering can at all times.
Let cool in can.
When cool, pour into pie shell and top with Cool Whip.

title: lazy chicken
directions: Combine bread crumbs, sugar, onion powder, paprika; set aside. Combine egg and mustard.
Roll chicken in egg mixture and then put the bread crumbs on the chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix together with mixer the cake mix, 1/2 cup evaporated milk and 3/4 cup soft butter.
Pour half the mixture into a 13 x 9-inch greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 5 minutes.
Melt caramels and 1/2 cup evaporated milk.
Pour over baked mixture.
Sprinkle pecans and chocolate chips over mixture.
Spoon rest of batter over mixture and bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.
(Do not try to spread or stir.)

title: nacho cheese dip
directions: Brown ground beef and drain fat.
Combine meat, soup and cheese.
Heat until melted.
Serve with nacho chips or Tostitos.

title: angel salad
directions: Mix jello with 1 less cup of water and let come to a thin mold.
Have cream cheese real soft and mix into jello.
Add crushed pineapple and mix.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Mold and set.

title: fettucini alfredo(spicy)
directions: Melt butter.
Pour half and half into pan.
Boil slowly.
Add red cayenne pepper to taste.
Shred Parmesan cheese and add to sauce mixture.
Stir cheese with wire whip until melted (cooking time about 20 to 25 minutes), turn off.
Boil noodles until done (7 to 9 minutes); drain.
Right before you pour the sauce on the noodles, heat it up to get the lumps out.

title: easy biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Cut margarine into flour until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Add buttermilk to make a soft dough. Stir with a fork until dough leaves sides of bowl.
Turn out onto lightly floured board; knead just until smooth.
Roll dough to 1/2-inch thickness; cut with floured 3-inch cutter.
Place biscuits on ungreased baking sheet.
Brush tops of biscuits lightly with melted margarine.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes, or until golden brown.
Makes 12 to 14 biscuits.
These may be frozen.
Bake for 5 minutes; seal in bag.
Finish baking when used.

title: fruit salad
directions: Pour all of juice from fruit into bowl.
In another bowl mix fruit.
Measure 2 cups of juice and mix with pudding.
Pour over fruit and stir.
Refrigerate 1 hour, then serve.

title: whole wheat muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease bottom of 12 medium muffin cups. Beat egg, stir in milk and oil.
Mix remaining ingredients, until flour is moistened.
Fill muffin cups 2/3 full.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes until golden brown, remove immediately.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook noodles; brown meat and onion.
Drain grease.
Stir in spaghetti sauce and spices to hamburger.
Use buttered baking dish; put 1/3 noodles, 1/3 sauce and 1/3 cheeses.
Repeat 3 times.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Let stand 10 minutes before cutting.

title: mexican pile-on(good for large groups)
directions: Make your favorite chili recipe, enough for the number of guests you will be serving.
Cook white or brown rice, enough for number of guests.
Serve rice with chili on top and allow guests to top as they like with the additional ingredients.

title: hamburger cheese bake(serves 10)
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions.
Drain well. Brown meat with onion, green pepper and garlic.
Add salt and pepper.
Stir in oregano and tomato sauce; set aside.
Soften cream cheese; blend with sour cream and cottage cheese.
Place 1/2 of noodles in large casserole.
Cover with cheese mixture.
Place remaining noodles on top.
Cover with meat mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until heated through.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix sugar and eggs.
Add oil and pumpkin. Add spices and dry ingredients.
Add raisins and chips.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Makes 6 small loaf pans.

title: pina colada cake
directions: Bake the cake mix according to directions on box in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix milk and cream of coconut well together.
While cake is hot, punch it full of holes with handle of wooden spoon. Pour the milk mixture over it.
Mix Cool Whip and coconut together.
Cool cake completely and cover with Cool Whip mixture. Refrigerate and let set at least 24 hours before cutting.
Best when made 3 to 4 days ahead of time.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Beat together all ingredients except blueberries, until blended.
Mixture will be lumpy.
Fold in floured and washed blueberries.
Pour in muffin tin.
Makes 1 dozen medium size muffins.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: barbecued country spareribs
directions: Brown ribs in broiler.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over ribs.
Bake approximately 3 hours.

title: temptation cake
directions: Bake cake mix in a large oblong pan, using milk instead of water. Punch holes in the top with a toothpick when done. Bring to a boil the sugar and pineapple.
Pour over cake while hot and let cool at room temperature.

title: chicken spectacula
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Pour into a 3-quart baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. May be frozen before baking.

title: white pizza
directions: Saute spinach and crushed garlic in olive oil.
Pepper to taste. Spread spinach over pizza crust.
Top with crumbled Feta cheese and Parmesan cheese.
Preheat oven to 425°.
Bake for approximately 10 minutes until cheese is melted.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Slice enough cheese to cover bottom of 8-inch glass pie dish. Peel zucchini and slice medium pieces over cheese and then sprinkle with Italian breadcrumbs.
Repeat.
Remember to start and end with cheese.
For added appearance, top with slices of cherry tomato. Cook in oven at 350° for about 1/2 hour or until brown on edges and bubbly.
Cool slightly and serve.

title: no bake cheese cake(make one day before serving)
directions: Line 9-inch spring-form pan (sides and bottom) with ladyfingers (reserve some for next layer).
Whip together heavy cream and vanilla.
Mix cream cheese and sugar.
Fold in whipped cream.
Spread 1/2 of mixture onto bottom of pan, then layer of ladyfingers.
Spread remaining mixture.
Refrigerate overnight when ready to serve.
Top with cherries.

title: crock-pot chicken
directions: Layer in order and cook on low for 6 to 8 hours or on High 2 1/2 to 4 hours.
(This can be put on before going to work.)

title: corn and bean casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Top with 1 cup cracker crumbs mixed with 1/2 stick melted margarine.
Bake until bubbly, about 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: sharon's raspberry bars
directions: Mix together the cake mix, margarine and oats.
Put three-fourths of the mixture in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread jam on top of cake mixture and put remaining mixture on top.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes or until brown.
Cut into bars when cool.

title: apricot nectar cake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Grease and flour tube pan.
Combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Bake 50-55 minutes.

title: hellmann's chocolate sensation
directions: Grease and flour 2 (9-inch) cake pans.
In large bowl with mixer on low speed, blend all ingredients for 30 seconds.
Beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Pour into prepared pans and bake for 30 to 35 minutes in 350° oven.
Cool 10 minutes before removing from pans.
Cool on wire racks.
Frost as desired.

title: baked apple dumplings
directions: Roll dough to 1/4 inch thickness on lightly floured surface. Shape into rectangle and cut into six 8-inch squares.
Reserve excess pastry.
Place an apple in center of each square.
Combine sugar and 1 1/2 teaspoons of cinnamon; mix well.
Fill each apple core with mixture and dot with butter. Moisten edges of pastry with water and bring corners to center.
Pinch edges to seal. Place in large baking dish.
Roll out reserved pastry.
Cut into decorative shapes and arrange on top, if desired.

title: spaghetti with fresh tomato sauce
directions: Heat the oven to 350°. Cut the tomatoes in half lengthwise and set aside. Remove the papery outer skin of the garlic and chop the cloves into tiny pieces. Set aside. Cut the basil leaves into tiny pieces and set aside. Place the tomatoes, cut side up, in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Salt and pepper lightly. Mix together the garlic, 1/3 cup of the parsley and 2 tablespoons of the olive oil in a small bowl. Place the garlic mixture on the tomatoes and drizzle 2 more tablespoons of the oil over all. Bake, uncovered, until the tomatoes are mushy, about 45 to 50 minutes. About 20 minutes before the tomatoes are done, put a large pot of salted water on for the spaghetti. When the water is boiling, add the spaghetti. Stir. After about 12 minutes, start testing every minute or so until the spaghetti is tender, but firm. Drain. Mix together the remaining parsley, olive oil, the butter and the basil in a large bowl. Add the tomatoes and spaghetti. Toss to mix well and serve. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oatmeal and let stand for 20 minutes. Cream together white sugar, brown sugar, oleo and eggs and add to oatmeal mixture (or add oatmeal to it).
Add dry ingredients and Mix well.
Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch cake pan. Bake for 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: enchiladas
directions: Heat chili in saucepan and dip each tortilla in the hot chili. Place cheese and onion in center of each tortilla.
Roll each tortilla and place, seam side down, in shallow baking dish.
Cover with remaining chili.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake in 350° oven for 15 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: french onion soup
directions: In covered large saucepan, cook onions in butter over low heat for about 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add consomme and Worcestershire sauce; heat to boiling.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer for about 30 minutes.
Place 1/2 slice toasted bread in each of 4 soup bowls.
Pour hot soup over bread; sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Makes 4 servings (1 cup each).

title: blackberry poor man's cake
directions: Beat egg and sugar together until light.
Add milk and then the melted butter and vanilla.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder twice.
Add to liquid mixture and mix well.
Add blackberries, stirring gently.
Pour into greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: peanut butter and jelly pie
directions: Combine cream cheese and peanut butter, mixing until well blended.
Add sugar and milk; mix well.
Spoon mixture into pie crust and chill.
Spread preserves onto chilled pie and top with whipped topping.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Combine and mix together all of the ingredients (except the chocolate chips).
Fold in the chocolate chips.
Spoon into a Bundt pan and bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Cool and serve.

title: quiche lorraine
directions: Heat oven to 425°. Prepare pastry for 9-inch one-crust pie as directed on package. Sprinkle bacon, cheese and onion in pastry-lined pie pan. With rotary beater, blend remaining ingredients; pour into pie pan. Bake 15 minutes. Reduce oven temperature to 300°. Bake pie 30 minutes longer or until knife inserted 1-inch from edge comes out clean. Let pie stand 10 minutes before cutting. Serve in wedges. Makes 6 servings.

title: marjorie's bread
directions: Activate yeast in 1 cup warm water and 1 tablespoon sugar. Stir good and let sit 10 to 12 minutes to dissolve.
It will foam up.
Rub 12 cups of flour and 1/2 stick of butter and 1 tablespoon salt and 1 tablespoon sugar until butter is rubbed into flour well. Make a well in center.
Add yeast mixture.
Stir in a little.
Add 3 1/2 cups warm water and mix.
Knead in pan 10 to 12 minutes adding flour underneath and turning.
Oil bottom of pan and turn dough so it is oiled top and bottom.
Cover and set aside in a warm, draft free place to rise until doubled (45 minutes to 1 hour).
Turn out onto floured board and divide into 4 pieces. Shape into loaves or buns.
Let rise until double in bulk.
Bake in oven at 400° for 30 to 45 minutes.
(Sounds hollow when you tap on it.)
Makes 4 regular loaves.

title: sugared pecans
directions: Mix together flour, vanilla and brown sugar; add to egg white. Add pecans and stir to coat.
Lay pecans on greased baking sheet and bake at 250° for 30 minutes. Turn oven off and leave nuts in for additional 30 minutes.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix all together; put in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Put crust on top (I use regular pie crust).
Cut vent holes in top.
Bake at 350° until bubbly and crust is golden brown.

title: star chicken
directions: Layer chicken, cheese, soup and stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: hobo beans
directions: Mix beef and onion.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer on top of stove for 45 minutes, or cook in crock-pot for 3 to 4 hours on high.

title: ham delights
directions: Combine margarine, onion, poppy seed and mustard in saucepan. Simmer until onion is tender.
Split rolls and spread cut surfaces with seasoned butter.
Layer ham and cheese in rolls and place on baking sheet.
Bake at 400° until cheese is melted.
Yields 4 to 6 dozen.

title: italian pepper twist
directions: Mix 2 cups of the flour and the yeast.
Stir together water, sugar, salt and pepper until sugar is dissolved.
Add sausage or pepperoni.
Gradually blend into flour-yeast mixture until well mixed, about 2 minutes on medium speed of electric mixer (or 300 strokes by hand).
Add 1 cup flour and beat 1 minute on medium speed (or 150 strokes by hand).
Stir in more flour to make a stiff dough.

title: southwestern roll-ups
directions: Combine spinach and fajita seasoning in a large nonstick skillet. Add broth. Cook over medium heat, stirring often, 5 minutes. Stir in chicken and next 3 ingredients. Simmer until cheese melts. Spread 1 cup chicken mixture on 1 side of tortilla, leaving a 1/2-inch border around edges. Roll up tortillas tightly and wrap in plastic wrap. Chill 30 minutes. Unwrap roll-ups and cut into slices. Serve with salsa.

title: sour cream cake
directions: Cream sugar, margarine, flavorings, eggs, salt and soda.
Add flour and sour cream alternately.
Bake in greased, floured pan (no paper) at 325° for 1 hour.

title: weekday potato bake
directions: Heat oven to 350.
Spray 8 inch square baking dish with nonstick cooking spray.

title: frozen pineapple rolls
directions: Whip whipping cream and set aside.
Drain pineapple.
Heat pineapple juice until it boils.
Stir in marshmallows until dissolved.
Let cool.
Fold in whipped cream, pineapple and nuts. Put in paper cups in muffin pans.
Freeze for 6 to 8 hours. Remove papers and roll in graham crumbs.
Top with whipped cream and put a cherry on top.

title: freezer slaw
directions: Sprinkle cabbage with salt.
Let stand 1 hour.
Add celery and green peppers; let stand 20 minutes longer.
Drain well.
Combine sugar, water, vinegar, celery seed and mustard seed.
Bring to a good boil.
Pour over cabbage mixture and mix well.
Cool well. Put in freezer containers and freeze.

title: chicken enchilada casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except tortillas, together. Add enough milk to make mixture soupy. Butter bottom of casserole dish. Put layer of tortillas in bottom, the soup mixture on top, alternating until soup mixture is gone.
Bake at 300° for 60 minutes.

title: coconut cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add baking powder, flour and milk alternately until all is used.
Add coconut and vanilla.
Bake in 2 (9-inch) round pans or 9 x 13-inch long pan for 30 minutes at 350°.
Serves 20.

title: parmesan pepper butter
directions: In a bowl of a food processor fitted with a metal wing blade, place butter, Parmesan cheese, salt and black pepper; process using on and off motions until combined, about 30 seconds.
(Or place all ingredients in a medium bowl; stir until combined.)
Serve with hot cooked corn-on-the-cob or other steamed vegetables.
Makes 1/2 cup.

title: stir and roll biscuits
directions: *May use 2 cups self-rising flour in place of the flour, baking powder and salt.

title: low-fat angel food cake and fruit
directions: Pinch 1/2 cake into bowl.
Mix vanilla pudding and pour over cake.
Layer remaining pinched cake.
Pour fruit mixture of pineapple and strawberries over cake.
Top with low-fat Cool Whip.
